Got ZERO peanuts. Asked for sauce. Wish I hadn't. The sauce for he vermicelli was TERRIBLE. Omg never never never ever again. Funny thing is, when I got my receipt, all of the modifications were there. I was expecting to pay extra but I didn't Bc they didn't do any of them.

I have been several times and it has been adequate. The last two times I have been there it has been TERRIBLE. The portions have diminished and the quality of the dishes have followed suit. I mean to a detrimental degree. I would not recommended dining here.

This is the worst Chik-fil-A I have ever been to. On multiple occasions I have waited over 25 minutes to get my food. Their response is "Sorry, we got backed up." It seems they are backed up on every occasion. They even have the sandwiches pre-made waiting to go in the bags but somehow, among all 10 employees behind the counter, they are so backed up that a five minute wait turns to a 25 plus minute wait. Avoid at all cost. Much better options at the Union!

I was in the mood for a quick bite at McDonald's.
I thought this was the place to go. I went to this McDonald's and got me a nice big Mac, fries and a soda, cost me about nine bucks. No biggie but I told the manager specifically, I wanted hot fries from the fryer.  But she served me cold fries that's been sitting out for at least 10 minutes. I complained but she was mean and rude. All I wanted was hot fries. Is that too much to ask at a McDonald's? She refuse to give me the hot fries and argued with me that the fries were hot. Really?

Wasn't that busy they might have had 4 servers on. Our server took forever to get us CANNED BEERS, we NEVER GOT OUR WATERS. Our appetizer came AFTER we finished our food. They comped it, but didn't try to make amends about the rest of horrible experience. We will NEVER GO BACK.

So disappointing. Stopped by for the first time Friday night.  There were 3 people at the bar. The rest of the place was empty.  Sat down, no acknowledgement from the staff.  Went up to the bar and took a menu, still no acknowledgement from the staff.  The guy behind the bar walked right past us to get a bottle of wine for the people at the bar, still no acknowledgement.  Finally after 15 minutes of being invisible, we walked out, and still no acknowledgement. We are new to the neighborhood and are wine drinkers.  We really wanted this to be our new hangout. However, we will look for a place that wants to provide service, where we are happy to spend our money.

I went to Fez with my family and we were pretty excited to eat some good Moroccon food! However, it was a horrible experience.
1) food was below average.
2) overpriced for very small portions
3) slow service
4) I was surprised for the price they didn't even serve  free pita/ appetizer or Moroccan tea/coffee 


 The only good thing was the ambience and that's it! 
Wouldn't recommend it and wouldn't go back!

It was a horrible dining experience. The food is not good. They're a very un .organized . I seen a lot of unhappy people I'm sure the owner is very unhappy,Getting all these horrible reviews. But my experience is true . change things ! Hurry or you won't be there.

I was really excited to try this location since I grew up eating at the downtown location.  I was horrible disappointed.  The atmosphere is nice. It's a quaint little area but  the quality of food that I received was far from what it used to be.  I order Alfred penne pasta with chicken and the chicken was tough and the noodles where so far over cooked it wouldn't even stay on my fork.  It slid right off in pieces. The Alfred was broken and oily.   The Caesar salad I received with it was just an average caesar nothing to talk about.  The garlic knots were hard. The wings I ordered were over cooked and unseasoned and dry.  My husband ordered a calzone that was soggy and greasy.   I'm truly sad and disappointed with this experience especially since the prices seem higher than the downtown location.  I'll just hold on to my memories but I won't be back.

Service wasn't good, wait time wasn't bad but it seemed like our food had been just sitting up in the window because it was so cold. My steak seemed really raw for medium rare. Got no butter with my now tiny rolls. Was really sad paying 40$ for mediocre food. Friends sides came in a styrofoam bowl. Not planning on returning. Sad thing is that it used to be so good. :(

This is your typical large conference hotel. I came here for business and stayed six nights. I found that the staff was not customer service centric - probably because their occupancy was so high and maybe they felt like they didn't have to earn our business. 

Here are the things that could have been better:

-I pre-ordered breakfast everyday via room service. It was consistently late (everyday) and they overcharged me - twice. When it came to check out, I expected the front desk to at least offer some kind of compensation for their oversight but they didn't. 

-The printer at the Business Center ran out of ink. They said it would take a week to replace the cartridge. 

-Front desk staff didn't seem to have a customer focus.

Went two days ago and the bartender was extremely rude. Left without having anything to drink or eat as a result. Went to The Institution a couple blocks away and they were extremely nice! If you have a similar experience I'd recommend going there as an alternative

1 star for awful service at the front desk. So rude. 

5 stars for my waxer Jess who was super sweet and did a great job.
Got shots legit shoved down my throat the second I walked in then was asked to pay for them... all in all I hate this place and have never felt so uncomfortable  or violated.

Strike Two - we won't be back.  Yes, we tried Brickhouse twice.  Visit 1 was on a Friday night about two months ago.  Visit 2 was today on a not busy/not slow Sunday.   I could go into a long review of why this place is not worth your time nor money...but, I'll keep it short(er).    If you go, be prepared to wait for your drinks...to wait for your food...for your food order to be screwed up...and for the excuse that "we are understaffed".  Understaffed is no excuse for the three additional servers sitting in the corner booth doing nothing...or why the appetizer comes out AFTER the main course....or why the chicken on my sandwich is refrigerator cold...or why three (3) Philly CHEESEsteak sandwiches are served with NO CHEESE...or why a burger ordered very well done/burnt comes served medium...  Nothing from the manager except "I'm sorry".   This place has a great great atmosphere...but that is where it stops.

Maybe I need to avoid this location all together. 
Every time I go I order a ham & Swiss and it seems like either they are out of Swiss or don't listen because my order is always wrong. Smh irritating af

Horrible service. Absolutely NO manners. Absolutely NO respect for their customers.
Food is "ok".
But the rudeness of staff forces me to NEVER eat at this place again.
Time for new management and new training program.

Wings here are delicious! The service may be a bit slow, but I say it is worth the wait. Just be prepared. Don't mind the flies...they may bother you but they won't eat much...there is a bright green neon paper plastered on the front door stating that this business is currently operating without a permit...

I have to rate this place 2 stars because the only thing good here is the food. If I was you I would visit origami sushi for the best sushi and customer service in USF AREA also, I would recommend the business to hire more staff.

Ordered from here 2x for lunch (delivery). My first order was pad kee mow. I'll give it an ok-to-good rating. 0 spicy even though I ordered a 3/medium. My second order was a grilled chicken salad. The chicken was rubbery and completely inedible - literally the worst chicken I've had in years. Plus the dressing (although in a small container) was spilling everywhere, so it was a major mess.

So ive been to place several times over the years. I was just basic.I just don't really know about this place. I was in there a week ago(after about a year since my last visit) and had a good meal and great service. The young man who was in charge at the diner area was awesome. The Food was perfect. Hot tasty I left very happy. So being in the area again I decided to go again but this time were back to the old ways. Cold bland food and the hash browns, why can't this place get hash browns right.  They look crispy but then they are just not cooked properly through and through. Service was horrible. The old guy at behind the  counter really needs to give it up. He just tries to do everything  but can't do it right. 1 glass of water the whole meal because he's busy worried about everyone else.
The week before he was NOT there, so maybe that's why everything was great. I am just done with going here.

For the 3rd time I've ordered my favorite meal from this Taco Bell, and they just can't pull of the correct ingredients with their equipment. I get a #6, which is 2 chalupa's, hard taco, and a drink. I always get chicken, no tomatoes, add nacho cheese, hard taco and MTN DEW BAJA BLAST with hot sauce. Tonight I got beef chalupas, tomatoes, onions, (don't come with it in the first place) a soft taco, an Ice tea of all things, and surprisingly hot sauce. And the fact that chicken and nacho cheese cost $2.50 more is not why I'm mad, all 3 times there was nobody in line, and not even inside. So from now on I'm going to the one and keystone and 62st street. Sure I'm going to wait in like for 20+ minuets but at least I know my order will be correct. Even when it's a cluster at 1am with all the drunks, I'd rather deal with that than a terribly inaccurate order of Castleton tbell.

Ordered pancakes, eggs, potatoes, bacon & sausage breakfast.  Eggs cooked as ordered, pancakes ok at best (not cooked quite enough), bacon ok, sausage good but the potatoes were terrible!  not seasoned, not cooked right at all, just a mess of bland potatoes most not cooked enough.  should of gone to lucky's

We have used Uptown for almost 10 years.

The car wash part is fine; no problems.

But the auto lube/service is just AWFUL.  Every time, there is some problem:  forgot to re-set car computer, didn't replace tire valve caps, didn't complete oil filter replacement, etc.

Even if I ask them to take special care to inflate tires properly, then snug caps back on, they don't.

After this long, and many complaints, I have to find fault with management.

This is so SAD, because facility is nice & convenient to our errand routes.

Sign me "FRUSTRATED"
Rick

We have always enjoyed our dinner here, but tonight we walked in sat down waited 10 minutes without being waited on.  Finally we walked out. No one even acknowledged us as we were walking out the door. Just a blank stare from the staff...

I was denied service dog access by the manager the Sunday before the last. I had documentation of his services but he denied me access because he said "the dog is too young". This is inaccurate and it goes against Federal law. I had to leave the dog on the boat and had to stick with my group in order for them to aid me. I never even attempted to go inside the establishment wit the service dog I was outside in the patio with him ...I felt horrible after this event.

This is the most money hungry place!!!! when you order wings 20 plus I think you should be able to get half plain and half with sauce if f you like... they will charge you a extra $2 for a container.... the food is here OK nothing special or extra. I've ordered here 2 different times and had bad experiences (1st time order was completely wrong Not to mention they put mustard on the food and I'm severely allergic) The only good thing on the menu is the salad with the garlic bread.

Forget the star, I wish I could give crossbones. They Steal Here. It pains me to say it, but I in fairness must. I checked in with a pair of "Beats" headphones. When I checked out, they (whom ever, I suspect housekeeping) had "borrowed my Beat's Headphones. My suggestion is if you can't carry it in your pocket, don't bring it! Naw'l better still stay where they don't steal! Never again will I stay at this overpriced, underwhelming dump! PS. They steal here!!!

I was very disappointed with this location.  I'm used to the Children's Museum in Atlanta, GA so I expected to visit something along the caliber.  This location is housed in an old house and setup with centers in a U formation like a in home daycare would be.  There are signs posted stating that they will be having a "Grand Re-opening Event on October 6th from 9:30am - 5:30pm....needless to say I will not be bringing the kids back here.  

Don't waste your time.

We stopped by for dinner, were seated in the only open table. Menus were given to us, and then we never heard from a server again. Waited 25 minutes before leaving. Perhaps servers would be more prepared if you accepted reservations. Hoping to give it another chance soon!

I've had two experiences with this place, both have been rather unpleasant. The first time I dined in and ordered the vegan ramen. The food was fine although when I asked them if they could make it spicy, the answer was no. So that was a bit bizarre, but no worries. What got me is that while we were eating our water was never once refilled and when we asked for the check, it took 47 minutes (I timed it) to arrive. 

The second experience was last night. I decided order via the waitr app and ordered a poke bowl. The app allows you to select ingredients from a menu and add them to a dish. When the food arrived it filled less than half the normal sized container it arrived in. It was also missing half the ingredients I had selected. I have never been so disappointed in a meal in my life. The portion wasn't even enough to feed a child. This is the first time I've felt inclined to leave a poor review and I think it's extremely warranted.

This company is absolutely horrible!  They are Flaky and definitely undependable!  They booked my daughter's wedding over 6 months ago with a signed contract and just flippantly   canceled 30 days prior to the wedding day! I've never seen anything like this. This company won't last!   The Owner was rude and had a lame excuse that there were too many stops for them. Beware of this company.  Obviously Kirk the owner doesn't seem to care if his reputation is ruined  and it will be.  This is unacceptable.

This store has a great staff (SteveFisher) that helps you decide on window coverings. But if there is a problem, the installation team falls so short it isn't even funny. I ordered vertical shades on a relatively small sliding glass door. It does not work properly. They were installed the end of February and they still do not work. There is no communication between the install person and the managers of the department. The team takes copious amount of notes and can never find them. I am losing my patience to get this problem resolved. Next I will call the company. Do not order big items from here

Bland. Everything was bland. I have eaten there twice and both times was disappointed. Even their beer is bland - tried one of their pale ales and the flavor was shallow and fake. They were out of the local brew I originally ordered. Lettuce wraps lacked flavor with slimy chicken. "Spicy" peanut chicken noodles had no flavor. Boring food, boring atmosphere, just boring! Won't be back.

Walked into Milk & Honey on Saturday, 3/24 around 1:30pm and asked what the wait time was for a table of 2. The hostess indicated it'd be about an hour and a half wait. I said "ok, thank you, I think we'll go look somewhere else" to which the hostess felt it necessary to reply "have fun! Maybe try Applebee's" in an incredibly condescending tone. 

Curious whether it's just the hostess that believes being rude to customers is acceptable, or if it's standard practice at this restaurant. With all the fantastic food options available in Nashville, I don't think I'll be coming back here.

I do not now but the communication issue is with this Chick-fil-A as compared to the rest that I've been to. Ordered a $40 meal for the family via the Chick-fil-A app. When I arrive to pick it up I informed the first employee that I need to add an additional shake. I've been informed the second employee that I needed to purchase an additional shake. And then I am formed the third employee that I needed to buy an additional shake. They were so confused about the simple request that I ended up driving away.

In short, the parts of my experience was better than the whole. I ordered the fishermen's special which isn't on the menu. It's supposed to come with avocado, which they were out of. Asked for lightly toasted bagel, it was burnt around the edges. It didn't taste like it had scallion spread on it and for $10.74, it seems overpriced for what I  received. The nova was okay as was the whitefish salad which I picked off because my bagel was burnt.  Back to REAL Jewish delis. Trying to diversify?

I never post issues really when it comes to eating out, I speak with someone directly when able, 

On 08/02/18, I went here for my quick 30 minute lunch break, ordered two items and kept it moving.

Closest light, I took a bite of my food to save time on the distant drive back to work, upon biting my chalupa, I bit into what I thought was a extra long piece of lettuce, after it continued to come out I knew it wasn't lettuce, but a large piece of plastic, normally I go to the restaurant and talk with the store manager myself off to the side and confront them with these issues, I didnt have time to do that at the moment due to time sensitivity, I did have time at work to get with corporate and leave my email for them to contact me about this issue even describing what happened and the location which it happened hoping a regional or general manager in the area would contact me same day if not next day, after work I confronted the shift manager off to the side what happened and showed my receipt and plastic, there was little to no care that this happened, I managed to get a "we're sorry about that" and not much anything else verbally, I did ask if I could get a general manager or regionals phone number to resolve this issue, I was denied, then handed a receipt with a supposed phone number to call, and the regionals name on the receipt she said, when I asked where, she stated the Cashier: Julio, was the regional off the receipt she gave me, Doubtful.

I wouldn't come here if you care for quality, I waited 3days for a reply email, nothing.

So many asian fusion places popping up in this city, unfortunately this one is not one of the best ! It has a wide ranging menu from Vietnamese to Thai, taco's what not, but, overall food was average. Flavors of asian cuisine were scarce to say the least . Owner spent a good amount of money on the ambience( a bit gaudy) to have it qualified for a fusion restaurant , but, still doesn't get the score right. Service was slow and mediocre. The shrimp fried rice is definitely a must at this place , rest of the items were sub-standard . Hopefully, Reno starts getting some restaurants that stay true to its cuisine !

I do NOT recommend this hotel to anyone!  My family and I flew in from Miami, Florida and we checked in on Thursday, May 24, 2018 and were booked to check out on Tuesday, May 29, 2018.  (We booked 4 rooms) We were looking forward to enjoying family time together in the hotel until Saturday our big event were to take place.  However, that family time included us enjoying the pool that was on premise.  The day we went to go to the pool area we were told by staff that the pool is not available; that it was reserved for a girl's soccer ball team.  I have never EVER heard of such crap like that!  We thought maybe it was just for that day but later on was told that it was not available for the entire 5 days we were booked to stay there.  I'm now thinking "This is absolutely INSANE!"  So not having the pool available left us with not much to do but stay inside of those small rooms we rented.  Therefore, we decided to check out earlier then we originally had plan.  This cost us extra money to change our flights but in the long run I feel it was worth it.  Why give "Element" anymore of our money.  I tried to check out much earlier but the Marriott Courtyard that was across the street were a bit pricey due to the Memorial Holiday weekend.

Front desk staff at this location needs more professional training when dealing with the public.

Ok, I was willing to give it another chance. I stopped by and I saw a better working team. Even the manager was focused and involved. The place was much cleaner and spiffy. I ordered the 8 piece bucket Original recipe. The worker pulled the pieces from what looked like freshly fried tray. I am thinking YAY! Now why is the mash the obligatory side to have? I asked to swap for spears and was told it was extra. I was like, let's not spoil this good moment and I said OK. No biggie. Got home and was ready for some good stuff, so I thought. So far, so good until I took a bite. Did someone at KFC change the recipe? I was looking for that Original recipe bite and goodness. What I got was so bland! It is like no one seasoned the chicken! Well I'll be a damn.... And the consistency was like boiled chicken, refried and breaded. Quality control is clearly lacking here. Kudos for the team, MEH for the chicken. Publix Fried Chicken still the winner!

Summary: the menu has the word "curated" on it. Either you're into this type of place, or you're not. I'm not, but I did pay $7 for an environmental disaster of a dessert, so here's my take. 

First off, this place is pretty overpriced. $7 for a small cone of soft serve and cubes of cake is hardly a good value. I'm not sure if I'm able to fully judge the desert, I got a curated chocolate flavored cone that was supposed to come with chocolate ice cream, chocolate cake, and chocolate ganache. There was no ganache in or on the cone, which probably would have helped overall. 

The dessert is sold in a cheap, fragile clear plastic cone. I suppose this is for Instagram users, but I would assume most of these people would be concerned about the massive amount of garbage this is creating, for no benefit other than AESTHETIC. This aesthetic would be served better by serving the dessert in a glass reusable container that doesn't crack in your hand under a slight bit of pressure. 

This establishment would do well to invent something portable, cheap and delicious to house the dessert if they don't want to use glass. I'm imagining maybe throwing waffle batter in a really flat griddle, made fresh for the customer, and rolling it into a cone shape while it's still malleable. You could call this thing a "waffle cone". If the staff is overwhelmed, maybe the dessert curator could come in and make them while the severs fill them...
Trendy place. The food is great but when asked to removed eggs from a burger they said "they aren't allowed to make alterations..." really?

Nothing great. Another Run-of-the-mill restaurant that has nothing great to offer. The first 2 visits are good in terms of taste and quality. So i thought i found my next food destination. But, No, after couple of weeks the standards came down real quick.

And last week, i ordered a onion dosa and the dosa came out snow white. I asked the waiter and he explained that since they opened an hour ago, the skillet is not hot enough, so the dosa i white. This is HEIGHTS!!! When they now, there is a problem, they shouldn't have taken orders for dosa and they shouldn't give me half baked product.

The lady sitting next to me also got a snow white half baked dosa and she really got confused that she received a wrong order while she ordered Onion dosa. She was also told the same story.

People don't come to restaurants to eat half baked stuff and pay $10 an item.

Their Biryani is a real joke. I expected atleast this to be good as the restaurant name itself is Biryani Hut :) 

I'm not going again.

This tasting room was recommended, cool scene but terribly aloof and pretentious. Poured the wines and never came back and out of 2 flights only 2 wines were local! What's the point of coming here? Had such better experiences pretty much everywhere else!!! And the wines were not good, local or otherwise!

The food here was "just OK" in my opinion. I had the Pad Thai and it just didn't have that authentic flavor I've had many times before. It wasn't a stand-out. Spring Rolls were very good. Friends had the fried rice and stir fried veggies with brown sauce and they have had better at other Thai restaurants. They weren't impressed either. Nicely decorated restaurant....food wasn't that great.

I called to make an appointment and the man on the phone was very rude. He rushed me off the phone when I asked him how much his services were for a full set. he hung up on me in mid sentence. He was disrespectful and I will spend my money somewhere else.

We had a reservation and the hostess told us to wait (outside) while she seated walk-in's that arrived after us. On being seated (at a tiny table against a wall where only one of us could watch the band- if you are a party of 2 beware- they don't want to give up the 4-tops for you), we were informed that "as we were told when we booked, we hold this table for you for one and a half hours, then you can stay at the bar." We booked online and no where was that information conveyed to us. We soon realized the restaurant the band was NOT as advertised on the restaurant's website, and we were not given any kind of indication prior to being seated. Service was slow (surprising since we only were allowed to stay for 1.5 hours) and the food was overpriced (I mean really, 3 dates for $8 for 2 people? At least make it an even number. Half portion for full price no thanks). Food wasn't bad, but not good enough to make it worth a return. This place doesn't appreciate your business go elsewhere.

A very poor first response.
The service was so slow and the food was just okay.
Another restaurant in Santa Barbara that thinks mediocre food and service can be accepted by the tourists and who cares about the locals.
This place is awful. The whole staff talking bad about everyone who walks in and then are just rude when you are there. Definitely don't go here

This hotel establishment was a bit to hipster for us. The lobby was extremely loud we assume because there was a restaurant on one side and bar lounge on the other. The front desk personnel were a bit snotty and were not attentive mostly cause they were busy on their phones and messing with paperwork. The only person we felt was attentive was the gentleman that took our bags to hold cause we got their early. Once we got to our room we were pleased with the "look" of the room but the bed felt horrible! It felt like a cheap box spring...no cushion at all, we had ask for extra pillows and even then it did not help! Asked for a late check out and it was denied

Horrible! Joke of a business. Bought a groupon and will probably have to fight to get it refunded. 

I guess there is only one person who can provide the groupon service who doesn't answer her phone & only texted to say she couldn't help me. She is also working during the day at a different job so she can't even talk to me to help.

She also mentioned that Adonias phone was broke? So it is impossible to make an appointment or use this Groupon basically.

VERY unprofessional!

This review is for the brunch only. 

Pros: 
* UNLIMITED (albeit ever-so-slightly watered-down) mimosas.
* Delightful french fries (not as good as Baggataway in Conshohocken, but still a solid 7/10).
* The french toast that a neighboring diner ordered LOOKED and SMELLED tasty... from where my husband and I were sitting, anyway...
* The not-brunch menus may be much better than the brunch menu...

CONS:
* Give or take a couple of items, their brunch menu consists of french toast, mushy fish-n-chips, and about five slight variations of the same breakfast sandwich.
* The aforementioned breakfast sandwiches sound tasty, but (at least when we went) are so poorly executed that they are inedible.

I ordered one of their breakfast sandwiches and couldn't finish it. I love heavy and flavorful food as much as the next [sane] person, but the cheese on this sandwich was *caked on* and grease literally ran down my arms and face every time I picked up the sandwich and tried to take a bite of it.

Meanwhile, my husband had fish and chips, but could not eat more than a few bites. We surmised that the fish had been very badly overcooked because most of it (about 80%) had the consistency of lukewarm lard. (I say "lukewarm" because that was the temperature at which it arrived when we finally received our food.)

The experience was especially disappointing because it took *well* over 45 minutes to get our food in the virtually-empty restaurant.

BOTTOM LINE: Decent bottomless mimosas for brunch, but stick to those and perhaps a side of fries. *****Again, this review applies to the BRUNCH menu ONLY*****

We will try their non-brunch menu at some point and write another review then (hopefully a positive one, as I have heard that their dinner menu may upgrade soon).
OLD FISH beware the five dollar rolls after 10 they're using unrefrigerated fish, straight outta prep cook bins
Doesn't even deserve 1 star don't care about anything alive except themselves...this location need to close, bad juju!

I'm a bit surprised in the 5 star or high reviews as well. They are a bunch of snotty rude aholes. I call with a question about a piece and they hang up. I call back several times they let the call go to answering machine. They don't care about costumers and should realize this is why people are going to the big stores. I would never go to this wanna be high fashion dump.

This place sucks! and never gets my orders correct. I have notified the manager several times but there's No customer's service to resolve the issues. Therefore, I won't spend my money there and I will share that with my friends and coworkers that eats there regularly.

Las Palmas in Franklin is CLOSED. I saw this coming as the food, service level, management engagement, and quality has been sliding downhill for a couple of years. A sad ending to what was a great location and restaurant experience.

Let's talk about customer service ... you knew that what I had bought was to be delivered yesterday. Then when it didn't arrive, you did not call to inform me of my delivery being late. When I call you this morning to follow up to see if my order has arrived for my to pick it up your response is " Oh I just found out today." I'm sorry, you found out today, but yet the due delivery date was yesterday and again you failed to call me as the customer?! Then you begin to tell me it won't be until NEXT week that my order won't be in the store for pick up?! To top that off when I ask for a manager I get "Oh there not here..." you've got to be out your mind to talk to a customer like that! My order will be returned, I expect a full refund and the number to your corporate location to escalate this further.
#PoopInShrimp Store manager is rude. Hope this lessens the 2 star ratings... Poop poop poop it's awful

This has been the worst experience I've had! I called ahead to see if I could come in for an oil change. I informed them I had a Groupon and he said I would not be able to come down till tomorrow then if I was using the coupon. I told him I was leaving town so he said come down anyway. I waited 2 hours for them to come out and say I needed all new brake pads/rotters/cabin filter and Ac filter for $970! But since I waited so long they would knock it down to $670. Not knowing for sure if I should get my rotters done I asked a gentleman and he look at my van 2013 and saw the rotters and said no you shouldn't have to replace them. All said and done I only did the brake pads to find out that the parts were not here!! So I had to wait longer! I will never go back and would not recommend this location.

How did this restaurant disappoint, let me count the ways. First, they "lost" our name on the wait list. Not a good start. As we waiting to order, we pondered what this restaurant was trying to be. It's Sunday after 3, the sound system is blaring dance music. We can barely talk to each other. There are many tv's showing a variety of sports shows. The waitresses is revealing is her navel. What is this place trying to be? Not a destination location for fine food. My eggs benni was mediocre. The eggs and sauce were nice, the English muffin, not toasted and soggy. And the potatoes(?)' Savory white and mashed sweet potatoes. Not a good pairing for breakfast. All in all, I leave poorer, and still hungry. Seek alternate routes
This place was very unwelcoming I won't be back first time I came in to see the new renovations which are beautiful but I'm not liking the staff I came in contact with tho

Have become increasingly unimpressed with the Asian food on Delmar. Got the chengdu spicy chicken which tasted no different than chicken from a fried chicken place. Rice that came with it was incredibly boring even for rice. Servings were way too much. Server was not attentive to table enough and appeared there was only one server for full restaurant. The only thing justifying one stars was the inside of the restaurant was nice.

This place does a thorough job cleaning. However, the staff there can be snippy and rude at times. A couple times I wanted to get a full detail and the ticket attendant snippily said "it's too late" the first time I said OK and just got a regular car wash; the second time I came about 1pm and he said the same thing, I asked him what a good time was and he just ignored me and asked what car wash I wanted to get, so the lady at the front desk tells me to come before 12 next time. So my last run in with this same ticket attendant was yesterday, I was pulling up to the car wash under the direction of his hand motion and once I got out he told me in snippy and rude tone not to watch the front of my car and to watch him, Which I don't understand, I'm not going to drive forward when there's a car in front of me under your direction and not look at what I'm doing. So I go to the manager because at this point I know this guy is a bit rude, the manager tells me "well he's been here 19 years and longer than me and I haven't had any complaints" I said "well that doesn't have anything to do with my experience and why I'm standing in your office at this moment and I'm coming to you because I'm giving you an opportunity to rectify it rather than just going to social media or writing a bad review" he says "well you can do that, we have thousands of people come through every day" So here I am! The managers attitude was an "I don't care about your experience because we have enough customers, we can lose one" That will be my last time giving them a chance, I'm sure there are other car washes with thorough work and great customer service skills as well.

Our server was wonderful! she was attentive, sweet, knowledgeable of the food and its preparations. This place operates like clockwork.  The host was welcoming and the support staff was attentive and aware what was going on around them.  Staff gets a 5 star or (Starr)..lol
Now lets talk about the food. First off, our meals were not bad. They were average.  They did however, lack flavor.  It might sound strange to say this, but our food and the space lacked identity. I feel like all Starr restaurants are known to have an identity and the food reflects that identity. This was definitely a weak point. This place was "good" but not what I assumed a Starr restaurant would be about.  We did attend there brunch a few time and thought it was very good, our meals at dinner were uneventful and a little  disappointing.

First time going in, and this will be my last. The service was subpar at best. Our server was barely at our table and took forever to get our food to us. We were there for lunch and it took 20 minutes to get a side salad out (and it ended up coming right before my entree). I ordered the salmon and I took 1 bite and noticed something was off with the taste. It was so noticeable that I had my sister try it and she noticed the taste too. I couldn't even finish my food.. At the end of it all our server brought boxes for us and the one on top had food in it already.. Needless to say we will not be returning.
I wasn't extremely impressed. The banana pancakes where meh. And the hash browns were also meh. Although the hair that came with them was disgusting. I don't know that I'll be back. ‍

Was in town for business and after checking in to my hotel late I noticed a Cheeseburger in paradise next door and got excited. All the ones in Columbus where Im from closed down a few years back. 

So I headed over before they closed in hopes of some carry out. 

I walked in and thought... wow... is this the right place? Looked more like a run down independent mom and pop joint than a notional franchise location. Decor was kinda blah, and not a whole lot of "Jimmy Buffet" stuff if any. 

I got a menu from the barmaid and looked it over..... didnt take long since there wasnt a whole lot to offer. 

I ordered a Bacon Cheeseburger, figured it was a safe bet. 

took it back to my room to eat it. It was ok, not as good as I remembered them being back home. Fries were good, and they seemed to give me an extra amount. 

Considering that the place looked like it was a few weeks away from closing, I dont think ill be stopping in again. 

Its too bad actually.

Took the family to get lunch. After ordering and waiting for the food through the drive-through I looked at the receipt. Found that they had added a bread that I did not order. I confronted them about the additional bread and they had no answers. It seems as though they added this in hopes that we did not recognize it's on the receipt. was very concerning that maybe we were not the only ones that were overcharged for something we did not order. As I had all the kids in the car and we did not have time to stick around to figure out why they charged $.75 more we told them that this was unacceptable and told them that I would report this on yelp. So watch your receipts.  It seemed like a good scam that most would not catch. When we got home I found that I did not even get that chips that were supposed to be my side.

I was not pleased with this restaurant at all. The service was slow. The cole slaw was rotten and slimy. My husband took a bite and had to spit out. Told the waitress and she said that it was for garnish not consumption. Talked to another person that asked how things were and she said that she tasted it and nothing wrong. I just hope no one got sick. They were not willing to offer anything else except the same slaw that was rotten. I will never go back to this restaurant again.

Took a tip from a local in Dunedin who suggested this restaurant and our experience was far from what she described. This was our first and definitely last time coming here. There was only two tables when we came in but it still took the waitress 10 minutes to seat us. The menus are about the size of a phone book and heavier than one too, but they do have lights inside of them which I thought was pretty cool. We asked for the fresh cooked bread for the table to snack on while we decided what we were all going to eat. When the waitress brought out the bread, she apologized and said they ran out and had to buy the bread from Winn Dixie...my whole table was a little taken back that she even was upfront about that. Not sure how an Italian restaurant can run out of their home made bread, especially when the place was dead. In the middle of ordering the appetizer our waitress just walked away pretending not to hear us. She did that a couple more times when we asked for a few more things for the table like steak sauce and lemons. I would NOT recommend the calamari, it came out shriveled up and dry. It took the waitress another 15 minutes to realize everyone's drinks at the table were empty before we had to flag her down to grab us all refills. I do have to say the shrimp scampi and the steak dinner special were really good and the cannoli was also. Management here should truly train their staff better, because the service was complete crap. There are a handful of other Italian places around Dunedin and I would for sure recommend to spend your money elsewhere instead of wasting it here.

I always liked cracked barrel  but today was the worst! 
wait time to give your name so they can get a table  ready 15minutes. We get seated and wait 20 to 30 just to get our food we ordered. took our waitress 15 minutes just to come to our table to apologize for the wait time.
We finally get our plates and one was warm and the other was cold,they take the plate back to kitchen and replace the pancakes and rest were put in a microwave,let's just say the eggs,sausage and bacon was rubber

First impression not worth the hype of reviews. Waited for about 10minutes after I was seated before anyone came to even offer me a drink. Only person that did was the bartender. The tables on either side of me were served, but I was ignored. Bartender, she was very nice and attentive.
Food is meh. Not worth the prices

Thursday night at 7pm shouldn't be too bad right???? NOPE! 25 minutes so far in the drive thur! Two cars still ahead of me and it's not like I can just leave. Love Del Taco but you are turning into Taco Bell with this crap!

I came with a friend a few weeks ago. There was one other party in the entire restaurant, but they did have a lot of Togo orders. It was frustrating because we ordered miso soup and chicken and rice soup and mine came out good but my friends was like warm and the chicken was not good, very flavorless, not to mention it literally took about 30 minutes for just our soup to come out. While they had time to eat and talk and take care of Togo orders, while we wait waterless and impatient for soup that came out 30 minutes later and not even warm. Then we waiting another 15 for our rolls. They were fresh and we enjoyed them. Just annoying to feel like we weren't taken care of when they easily could have with how slow they were and with the three people that were on. Probably won't eat in again, obviously the Togo orders take priority over the guests in your restaurant.
I came in to get acrylics twice and both times they made me bleed! Very painful, but the end result was okay.

Friday May 11 was such a beautiful evening that my husband and i decided to go somewhere with outdoor seating.  We were both excited about coming here as we had been to the previous restaurant at this location and were very pleased.  We thought we would be WOWed after reading the menu.  What we found was a pleasant but inattentive server and bus boys that seemed to be clueless.  The food was mediocre at best.  I had the poached pear salad.  The flavor was very good on the pears but for $8.50 I wanted more than 4 thin slices.  it was supposed to have smoked Gouda.  I think there was 6 pieces that appeared to be box shredded.  I could not find the craisins or walnuts and the greens were starting to turn brown.  My husband had the wedge salad.  Again, over priced for the quality and amount.  I had, as an entree, the Jumbo Lump Crab Cakes.  They had no flavor.  The mashed potatoes had a lump of cheddar in the center and were overpowered by Old Bay seasoning.  My husband had the Seafood Pescatore which he said was OK.  I will say the desserts where beyond excellent.  We were told they were homemade so KUDOS to the baker.  We shared a Chocolate Mint Torte.  My mouth waters thinking about it.  The server, while she was pleasant, came over to take our order and then we did not see her again until she gave us our bill.  We asked for flatware as our food was served with no implements to eat it with.  Had we had the set ups at arrival we may have had a luke warm rather than cold meals.  When we asked for red wine glasses it too over 20 minutes for a bus boy to provide and when we asked for water you would have thought we had three heads each.  We will not be returning however, if the person who made the desserts opened a dessert eatery, we would frequent that establishment.

I was always very fond of this restaurant and would regularly go here with my friends. However, last week I came to the restaurant and was double charged. To elaborate, they charged me TWICE for my order. Needless to say, I will not be returning to this restaurant.

I was condescended to in store when I came in for an oil change because my brakes needed obvious attention. I could clearly hear them joking about it in the workshop, and they could literally see me looking back at them through the glass. Not only that, but the kid who was taking care of the transaction, Michael, was holding back laughter, after I told him that clearly my brakes need attention, but that my dad does that type of maintenance on my car. 

They also offered me packages that were more than twice the price of the one I needed, but gave me the one I needed when I asked for it.

I also observed the same associate blowing off a customer before me when he said the name on his receipt was wrong. Manager Curt was more helpful.
So Patriots fans give you so much business but you close out half the bar for Eagles fans during the Super Bowl. Lame dude. Lame.

Terrible.. asked for delivery, was told they would deliver but received a call 5 min before it was to arrive, saying they don't deliver and that I'd have to pick it up. Mind you, we can't just leave work (hence the delivery) and clearly the order had been made. Just seems like it would've made more sense to just go on with the delivery and advise us that we are out of their delivery zone even though we've receive deliveries numerous times. Apparent I'm located between 2 locations and neither want to deliver.

Save your money and time. The drinks are weak, the tables are sticky, the floors were dirty. It's definitely not a place that represents ybor city well. 

The staff was very nice, but outside of that, the establishment needs help being consistent with other competing bars. 

We had a margarita pitcher that was sweet and tangy. The tequila was suppose to be inside, but we didn't taste a hint of it. That was disappointing. This was our first impression of the bars in ybor city. Not good at all.

I am an ex-server for olive garden. It is one of my favorite restaurants and I drove over half an hour to eat there with two of my friends on Thursday may 31st. Our servers were Tracey and mikayla, whose was training, and I was extremely disappointed in the service that we recieved.
I'd like to highlight first the some service that met the outstanding expectations that I know olive garden expects.
When we arrived we were seated right away and our server in training introduced herself fairly quickly. We were given adequate time to look at the menu and make our selections. Our first round of salad and bread sticks, along with our appetizer very quickly. After this though the whole atmosphere and attitude seemed to change.
Our tray of breadsticks and salad stood empty for almost 20 minutes after that initial  round. One of the reasons I love olive garden is because of the refills on salad, soup, and breadsticks. While we waited on someone to recognize that we needed refills, a tray of dirty dishes sat out in the dining room for approximately 30 minutes across from our table. Our main courses came out before our second round of salad and breadsticks and when I recieved my entree the sauce in the ravioli de portabellas that I had ordered congealed and the entree was cold. I flagged down a server as no one had asked us how are meal was. Although my meal was replaced with no question, it came out after both of my friends were finished eating and had recieved to-go boxes, so I was eating my meal alone. After we were all done eating, everything was boxed up, and dishes were cleared we then waited over another 15 minutes for my dessert to-go and our check. Finally when we did receive our check it was the wrong one. Thankfully I was planning on paying with a credit card so I didn't just leave money on the table and walk out. 
Again I am very disappointed in the service I recieved tonight. The problem with our service is that there was no direction from the server that was training the new employee. Tracey seemed to be more worried about a large party that was sitting behind us but made a point to mention in passing that mikayla better do good tonight because she was making her money. Now I understand the basis behind why trainees give their tips to their trainer, as I went through the training myself, but tracy was not guiding her, checking on the table or shadowing her anyway. I feel like mikayla was sent out to the wolves with no food.

I came for a conference. The total charge for my three night stay was over $1100 after taxes and resort fees. Even after paying this astronomical amount was I was still charged $8 for a microwaved breakfast sandwich and $16 for a small tube of neosporin. Lets not even talk about the restaurant prices. Lunch at the cafe for two- just ordering 3 small tapas plates (1 California roll was $12!!!!) and 2 alcoholic beverage each was a whopping $70 (not including tip). The resort was INCREDIBLY difficult to navigate and it took me and my coworkers over 20 min to find our rooms. There were limited breakfast options and the grab and go options had massive lines due to being understaffed. Even the shuttle to the airport was not complimentary. Taxis to downtown Nashville were $30 each way. Rooms were clean but needed to be checked better. I had no room service menu, the iron was cheap and leaked water right out of the holes (they brought me a brand new one and it did the same thing)- ruined a dress of mine. Lamp with appliance plugs was broken. I could hear screaming kids up to 11pm at night. I didn't even know how to get to the atrium outside my room. I felt trapped in a biosphere and would never return willingly to this place again. Overall, it completely overpriced and not a relaxing stay at all. For a "world class resort" here in the United States it pretty shameful. I've had a completely better stay at resorts in other countries that are 1/2 the price, go there instead!!!!!
I ordered an acai bowl. It was watered down and melted into a soup. For the $10 price I would have expected real acai. Disappointing.

This was really disappointing, normally diner food is really enjoyable and one of the people in our group had eaten here before. I ordered a breakfast sandwich, which we had to wait for because the kitchen gave away the first one and tried to give the second one away until our waitress caught it. 

My sandwich was okay, but I did notice the bread had mold on it which we quietly brought to our server's attention. She was very apologetic and brought it to the kitchen. She then came back out and explained the chef said it was from cutting spinach for the Eggs Florentine we had ordered. The spot was no where near where the bread had been sliced, and the color was more blue than green. It took a brief discussion with our server to have the sandwich removed from the check. So they're either cross contaminating the knives they're using or they're trying to serve their customers mold. We also never received the grits we ordered which they removed with no issue. 

Jessica the waitress was very apologetic the whole time, and very sweet. The kitchen staff should be ashamed.
The Mama's really good spaghetti and meatballs pasta was not "Really Good." Hardly any sauce, and the sauce was really boring.

I parked right in front of the restaurant and a staff person came out and yelled at me for parking then berated me about how long I was going to be there. My son attends music next door and I had planned on catching a solo bite to eat at Mythos while he had his lesson. Instead the utter rudeness of the Mythos staff completely turned me off of dinning there. The Mythos staff missed turning the increase of visitors to the strip mall into an opportunity and created an unwelcome and angry vibe dissuading people from checking them out.
Glasses smelled bad. Food was not very appetizing. Seemed like friendly and responsive staff but food standard and hygiene needs to improve.

It's going to be pretty hard to leave this review considering I couldn't even eat what I wanted to order. I came here for breakfast at 10:30 with my boyfriend only to find out that they ran out of eggs, so we choose to leave. It's hard to choose something else to order when your heart was set on breakfast food. Very disappointed.
I just order 5 meals 1 of which was never even entered. So I never got it. But the 4 orders I did receive every single one was incorrect. Pretty disappointed.

Pros: new presentation 

Cons:
Limited menu
Ordinary food, certainly not 4-star 
Small portions (considering price)

They came up first on my Yelp search. In hindsight, it might be better to go for others. Probably explore a bit more
Disorganized service for large parties... food was cold the place was cold... food had no flavor... shrimp was over cooked on the shrimp (rubbery) extremely small portions for high cost of food.
So unorganized. 5 different people wait on you. Just don't come here. There are so many better salons you can choose

The wife and I were on our own last night so we decided to try something different then the usual Applebee's or Outback Steak so after hearing several good reviews of this place we decided to check it out. First they offered outdoor seating which was a nice atmosphere for our "date night" until they seated someone behind us who decided to bring there dog out to eat. While this isn't necessarily a fault of the restaurant, it was an annoyance hearing the dog panting and choking on whatever scraps they were feeding it. Now onto the food. I ordered the chicken parm with broccoli as my side. I was told by the waitress that the chicken parm was out of this world. I've had better chicken parm from the Olive Garden. It was an oversized chicken finger with a boatload of cheese on top. The broccoli was very crunchy and tasted like biting into a garlic clove. The wife ordered Gnocchi's. She said they tasted like biting into a chunk of parmigiana cheese and the sauce was so thick it was hard for her to choke them down. The best part of the meal was the Cesar salad which was big enough for us to share. Since we didn't really eat our meal we did have room for dessert. The chocolate cake was pretty damn good!

I'm really surprised by all the great reviews. That's what made me want to try this place out. The service was friendly, but the food was just bad. I ordered the country fried steak. The steak was dry, tough, and gristly. The breading wasn't crispy at all, and the gravy was bland. My food came with toast. It was warm but didn't seem like it was toasted and wasn't spread with real butter - I'm guessing margarine? My husband had the eggs Benedict. He said it was okay, but that the English muffin wasn't toasted at all.
Enjoyed the cruise, the band was good but food is AWFUL!!! I've had better TV dinners.   Dinner cruise is definitely not worth it.  Take the cruise; save your money and buy snacks from the snack bar.

Building and atmosphere was great, but food and drinks did not meet the mark. Beware if you are going to order the jerk chicken. It does not say it will be the spiciest dish of your life, but you will leave in tears with a numb mouth. My boyfriend is a self-proclaimed heat enthusiast and could barely finish the dish. Everything else was just okay. Vegetable soup was like something you could get out of a Campbell's soup. Tomato salad was 4 big chunks of tomato. Zucchini and squash noodles was probably the best dish, but still not that exciting. The watermelon drink was god awful. We actually had to send it back because it tasted like a dirty sock. If you come to the wedgewood Houston area, go to Bastion for dinner and flamingo club for drinks.

I just called and he quoted me $330 for a Note 8 screen repair. I then asked for quote on yelp (by accident) and he wrote back it would be $420. Uh, what happened?

At uBreakiFix cost is $260 (plus tax) for new LCD screen and labor.

Extremely disappointed. I bought their special Harry Potter red velvet cake with butterbeer frosting slice. I wouldn't even call it a slice and they charged $10 for this. I wish I would've taken a picture but after splitting it in half with my son I got a whole six small bites of cake. The picture of the slice they showed on Facebook is very deceiving, it's that height but cut like a piece of bread not cake. And the cake itself was dry and I didn't really taste the butterbeer but the frosting was good. We did also buy an Oreo cookie covered with chocolate and a cake pop which we haven't tried yet. I really liked the theming they did for Harry Potter but I don't think I'll be back. Too overpriced for what I got.

I've been here twice now and both times my gel manicure lasted only a week before it started chipping whereas they usually last 2 - 3 weeks. 

I also don't understand why when I was there the second time, one woman did my manicure and then my pedicure when there were three employees there literally doing nothing but checking their phones. In every other salon I've been to, if there's the ability to do both simultaneously, they will. I don't think I'll be back.

We got a late dinner here around 9pm and the food was not appetizing at all. The mash potatoes lacked flavor and salt, my seafood fra Diablo pasta was very dry and all of the seafood was over cooked. Very saddening when my scallops are as chewy as a piece of beef jerky. We also got the surf and turf and the lobster wasn't very tasteful, but the steak was cooked right around medium rare which is how we like it. The server we had was very nice and the management was accommodating and corrected the kitchens mistakes for our low quality food. Overall staff was pleasant and made a bad evening of food turn into a decent one with their professionalism and handling our predicament. Happy to say the low quality food didn't reflect the work ethic of the employees/management.

Lively diner in the heart of the french quarter. Lots of locals inside. That aspect of it was fun.

But I'm not sure why this place gets good reviews. None of the people in my group liked the food. We came here for breakfast. My pancakes were average and came with fake syrup and margarine instead of butter, both in little packages. One of us ordered eggs over medium and they were not over medium. The little round sausage patties were dry and overcooked. The coffee was awful too but I pretty much expect that from a diner. 

There are too many great places to eat breakfast in the quarter to waste time on this place. Maybe they have good lunch or dinner but I wouldn't return here for breakfast.

Yesterday I came here to shop for the semi-annual sale and wanted to use my coupon, but the cashier told me it doesn't work when it wasn't expired and hasn't been used. She didn't scan my app for the reward points, but only scanned the coupon from it. She didn't really know what she was doing.

Have been to Dave & Buster's in other cities and were very impressed.  This one not so much.   Went with kids and their friends, all teenagers.  When we got there only 2 small groups were in line ahead of us.  It took 30 minutes to pay and get our cards charged.  The personnel behind the desk did not seem to know what they were doing.  The games all seemed to work fine and we did not wait for any games.  It was happy hour so I decided to order a Margertia.  It took 20 minutes after I ordered to get the drink brought to our table and there was no alcohol in the drink at all.  I can only surmise that the bar staff is as trained as the front desk staff.  In the future I will stick to Dave and Buster's when traveling.

Worst nail job everrrr. JACKIE did my nails. I called only bc it was an hour until closing and also bc I would be coming as a walk in. (I Understand, hence why I called FIRST) I was told ok on BOTH parts. I get there literally 10 mins later as I'm down the street. As shes doing my nails, i explain i am a stickler for shape and I'd like them all even. As time passes she continuously asks me where I got my nails done, why dont I like it, etc. (UNPROFESSIONAL #1.)  Shes heavy handedly scraped the gel off.... I asked her to soak them a little longer as these are my REAL nails with just a Gel Polish.... And that's where it began.... after that, I was then told I was too picky (UNROFESSIONAL #2) I ONLY came in bc my nail was broken and needed it to be fix. I'm having license issues so I cant go where I normally go, (something mentioned bc she asked WHERE was my car since I was dropped off) (UNPROFESSIONAL #3). At then end she placed a scalding hot towel and then was told I could go now. I had to clean under my own nails and file the same one I asked her to fix. Like Worst Effing Place Ever. If this was me 10 yrs ago, She would've to been cussed out all the way to high heaven. GO ELSEWHERE!!

Take out. The food was ready in 15 minutes. The Thai basil stir fry with chicken was very watery, too spicy, not flavorful. There was so much liquid in the dish that my side of rice was not able to soak everything up. This is not what I expected to see. It was spicier than I expected as well - on the phone the restaurant said it was a little spicy. I think the extra spice hid the fact that the dish was not flavorful. It was almost as if the stir fry was done half heartedly and then water was added after the fact.

Maybe with another dish or dining in the food quality would be better. I'm willing to give this place another try but I was not impressed with what I had.
Terrible place.  My lashes were put on incorrectly and caused a horrible reaction.  I had to see a dermatologist and opthamologist for the infection.  Stay far away from this place!

If I could, I would give this place ZERO stars. I know a lot of people might say racism doesn't exist anymore, but being in Philadelphia for two days & I haven't seen it more in my entire life. Walked into this place & was told the wait for dining would be about 20-25 mins, no problem. My boyfriend decided to get some beer from the bar where we were neglected by the first bartender. When we finally got seated, we placed our food order right away which was about 5:00PM. A couple who came in after us was able to get their food & drinks about 10 mins after walking in yet we still hadn't gotten ours even forty mins after. In that forty mins we asked our server twice how much longer it would be till our food was ready, both times he told us 'shortly'. After realizing another couple had gotten their food already & we asked him again which he then told us 'I have no control over the kitchen'. At this point, we walked out. I'm saying this is racism because after I took a good look around, I noticed my boyfriend & I were the ONLY colored couple there. People should realize we are humans just like them, & just like everybody else we pay money for a service.

Not impressed. We came for restaurant week. I wasn't impressed by the menu - overpriced for what you got. I ended up ordering off the tasting menu and my steak was over cooked. My girlfriend got the tasting menu and didn't feel like any of the dishes had much flavor. I think there was a reason it was easy to walk in and get a table.

Came for few days for conference. I would never voluntarily stay here. Basically the quality of a holiday inn but with large fake garden in it. Food is very low quality. You always expect to pay more when stuck somewhere, but Gaylord charges exhorbitant mark up. Breakfast of scrambled eggs with home fries and milk...$30. It has all the kitsch of Vegas or Disney, same prices, but no casino or entertainment. Not close to downtown Nashville. Would not voluntarily subject myself to the Gaylord opryland.

The food can be better. 
There were lot of dishes and lot of choices, both in vegetarian and non-vegetarian. 
The ambience of the restaurant is grand. 
The taste of food is not matching the grandeur of the restaurant.

Not sure whats so special about this place. Ive been there twice. The first time the service was good the second time, the cashier obviously did not want to be there which isnt a huge deal but ok. I paid 16 dollars for cookies and 2 small ice creams. I could understand if the cookies were something special but honestly ive had better cookies at frys. How is your whole business model based around cookies and there is absolutely no creativity in the cookie choices. The "premium" cookies have some flair but maybe try something other than chocolate. This place is way overpriced and not even that good. Im not wasting my money there again.

On 8/18/18 I was sitting at Coyote wash waiting for my laundry to dry when Marge came up to me and said "I don't know why you are mad at me, but stop trying to get me fired, just shut your mouth. JUST SHUT YOUR MOUTH." I then emailed the owner to let him know how I was treated by one of his employees that was off duty. On 8/24/18 I called to talk with the owner. He said that he did not believe me because it did not sound like Marge. Marge has pulled the wool over the owners eyes too much. Other customers have told me that she has been rude to them, but they are afraid of her. The owner will do nothing to correct the problem. I can still press charges on Marge and I think I will. She did harass a federal contractor which would be a felony.

I ordered take-out again from this restaurant on Aug 07, 2018. The calamari appetizer was extremely disappointing. For $9.99, most of the container was filled with fried crumbs. There were only about 10 tiny fried calamari rings. Such a rip-off! I will definitely not order this item again.

I know that working for fast food restaurant tends to be something that is done in high school wow the frontal lobe is still developing. But it is extremely interesting to me how little attention to detail and how on responsive to customers the staff at this location can be fit I know you get what you pay for but holy smokes some new hiring policies might be entertained here.

We had friends in town yesterday and decided to try Tank 13. I have eaten BBQ all over the country, and I was excited try some ribs from their smoker. I could not have been more disappointed. First, the ribs were not smoked--they were baked. There was no smoke flavor or smoke ring, and the ribs were completely inedible (I was asked if I wanted a box for my uneaten 1/2 slab... no thank you). When they arrived, I noticed that three of the ribs had been completely removed from meat. Smoked ribs done right should not be "fall off the bone." They should have a little bite to them. These were easily the most disgusting ribs I have ever seen, and I would never have served them to any guests at my house (I regularly smoke meats in my own smoker). That I paid $14.50 for this terrible meal is a mistake I will never make again. And to top it off, the service was subpar--no one bothered to ask how our meal was, and it apparently wasn't strange that I left a completely uneaten 1/2 slab of ribs on my plate, when that was all I ordered. Will never recommend this place to anyone for food. I assume the beer is good (I didn't have anything to drink), and it would be a decent place to watch a ball game. But stay away from their BBQ... it is among the worst in the city (in a city with generally terrible BBQ), at least on the day I visited.

I usually come to this place a lot and enjoy there smoothies and acai bowls all the time. Sometimes the wait can get pretty bad but nothing too crazy until today.  I ordered a Hercules smoothie which I get all the time and the wait is usually 5-15 mins. Today I waited 30 mins for a smoothie.  I go up and ask about my smoothie after waiting 30 mins and found out they haven't even started it.  After that I watch the guy behind the counter make my smoothie in less than a minute.  Honestly probably one of the worst smoothies I have ever bought and I dont think I will ever come back.  I could have made a better smoothie.  Just very disappointing.
Food was horrible. No flavor and a bit cold...how do you have Mac and cheese and no real cheese ? Can't say i would be back

High prices, slow service, & wrong orders.
Never again.  Don't throw your money away.

Really disappointed with this place. We paid $20/person to stand in the back of a tiny packed room. I was still able to see the band just fine though. We went for the last show at 10pm on Saturday night. The whole band was half asleep. No energy. No soul. Sour faces. Reluctantly getting up to play. Eyes closed when they aren't playing. All frowns. It was really sad...like they were overworked horses. It really killed the mood. Understandably, the audience was all stiff because of it. Didn't feel like a jazz band at all. The band leader on piano kept talking, but we couldn't hear any of it because he's so soft spoken. No drinks sold inside, but they let you bring in drinks from outside. 40min show. Honestly, I enjoyed the free bands playing outside more.

Umm, I would say, they are a little high amd toyty . They are natzis as far as smoking even 25 ft out side of their entrance. Def would choose another place for expensive food. The food wasn't bad, but can get it anywhere else with out them being  the governor of the side walk. Thanks !

Before I can get to the attitude of this place. Let me tell you we walk in when there is no one at all -maybe one person and they seat us near the restroom. The waiters couldn't seem to be able to find their way to our table for like half hour. Also it took the staff 40 mins to bring us the food after we ordered. Some of the food was completely cold. I wish I could say the food was bad, but the food that was not cold was pretty good. But I cant give it a good review

This place NEVER HAS BRISKET!!!! We went for the first time to try it out. (We've gone but they never have brisket so we leave) so I decided to try it out. Heck I was starving so why not.  Turkey was not good at all, my son hated the mac n cheese, he hardly touched the turkey. I'm telling you coming from a prior TX resident. Do yourself a favor and don't try this place. What a let down.... will NEVER GO BACK!

Went for Italian nite Wednesday. I had eggplant parm. and it was so salty that I was cringing from the saltiness. The eggplant was cut pretty thin and layered,which makes me believe it was not fresh. I didn't want to complain because we had brought a relative from out of town. They took the dish away and brought back noodles and salt taste was almost gone. My relative had fettucione and clams. He too complained about the food. 
Italian Nite did not go so well. Maybe they should stick to the fish dishes, etc. Always enjoyed the food on previous visits.

The food is okay. If you are having a ridiculous Mexican-food craving, it will get the job done.
My problem is, they get my order wrong every. single. time. And they are not small mistakes. Something is missing or completely off (e.g. I ordered a bowl and got a burrito. Didn't realize until I got home and ended up scraping the food from the tortilla into my own bowl. Horrible waste of tortilla, I know, but I just don't eat it and didn't want it.) I didn't speak up the first time but have begun to now, and the staff honestly could have cared less.

My girlfriend and I went to happy hour yesterday,  14 Sept 2018, at a friends suggestion.  Ordered oysters to start,  couldn't really figure out what was wrong with the cocktail sauce,  it was so runny that you couldn't get it to stay on the oyster.  I asked for some ketchup and horseradish on the side,  so we could mix it to taste but got the same runny crap. The bartender / waitress was oblivious to our request for better service, and by the time she was done ruining to the back, for anyyhing she needed, the oysters were getting warm due to the fact they were not served on ice. In my humble opinion ice should not be an issue for a restaurant/bar, this of course forced us to eat them quicker than we would have liked.

I inquired about the Bistro burger which says on the menu ask server for details,which I did she explained what a wonderful burger w all the toppings, not one time did she describe it would be two thin patties over cooked. I distinctly asked if I order it medium it will be pink in The middle correct? Perfect time to inform me it is two thin patties...sorry misinformed,over cooked, over priced. Would have been happier w a thick burger from Hardee's

Twice I've came here and witnessed workers with non gloved hands eating tortilla chip right out of the chip tub behind the counter. . So gross! Both times they looked right at me and kept on eating them as I picked my shocked mouth up off the floor. Also got charged for guac I didn't buy. Gave me a refund to my debit card only for me to see the receipt said refund -CASH, which they didn't give me.  I'm going back w the receipt for my money

Customer service is terrible... bar tenders are not always attentive...  at times, they seem to want you to beg for a beer...  
The bar isnt that busy to be ignored as much as they have.
Food is ok...  portions tend to be small

I wife and I were out doing things Sunday at water burger and we stopped at Burgerim.
It was a mistake. First the good. The white castle size burgers were actually quite tasty. The fries were not good and the service made you think the restaurant was a vending machine rather than something with actual people. Definitely not worth another visit. Oh yeah,Pricey for what you got.

-------Update as of 4/25/2018.-------

The knocking sound coming from my car sounds like this ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ii5Xf0g4em8 ). I came across this before ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BgI6MPnfV1g ) and after video ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FeQipBgs8BY ) of someone elses forester. You be the judge. 

I had dropped the car to another Subaru dealership and they couldn't find any issues with the car either.  Unfortunately, I know the issue is still there and looks like it will not be resolved because no one seems to be able to replicate the issue. 

I do not blame Glanzmann at this time for not being able to diagnose the issue.

-------Update as of 4/18/2018.-------

I have sent a message back to Jeff after reading his comment.  The reason for Glanzmann not being able to replicate the issue is because the car engine temp needs to be around 210 and usually in winter about 15 mins of test drive does not make the temperature that high unless the car is warmed up.  This is very reason I missed this issue when I went for the test drives a couple times. 

P.S I do appreciate the owner trying to get in touch with me to resolve the issue.
------

------


Original review:

I have some issues with the certified pre-owned car that I bought but I am going to work with the dealership to get it resolved even though the issues was not resolved on the the initial visit. It is entirely possible the issue was not fixed because of weather conditions and temperature.

I gave this hotel the benefit of the doubt and spoke to the front desk about my frustrations. We checked in Friday, July 6 and as of Sunday night at 11pm, our room had been cleaned once (even though we have been gone all day). 

Our supposedly "upgrade" sent us to a room that had a tiny window that was a looking directly to the neighbors patio. As in, their chairs were facing our bedroom window. We had no natural light besides this. Insane. 

The wallpaper was falling off the wall. We complained about this, and nothing was done about it. 

There are no fitted sheets on the bed. Just mattress pad and flat sheet. So when you wake up... you're on the mattress pad. 

When I talked to the front desk (before posting complaint), nothing was done. Instead the excuse was given "sorry this is our first time working at a hotel". The night manager, Curtis, said "Is this the first time complaining about this? I don't know the difference between fitted sheet and flat sheet."

I am from Houston and usually only stay at boutique hotels when visiting places. This was a poor decision on our part. We should have stayed at a chain like the Omni because this stay has been so disappointing. 

ONLY good service were the guys working at the front door helping with bags and doors.

What a cool atmosphere full of BS! Half the restaurant was empty yet the rude hostess would not seat us. The drinks took 15 mins to make and cost $15 each, which is fine for a craft cocktail but these simply tasted bad. The guests who were allowed, yes allowed to eat all left food behind and told us not to bother waiting for a seat for 2 hours because the food was "gross". Hire some nicer people, get a location where you can use all the space and don't have the bar be a free for all where rude people take a 70 year old woman's seat. Gross!

I really wanted to like this place, but when we went, they ran out of so much food, food that was essential to the meal we ordered. They ran out of biscuits for the chicken biscuit, so we asked for an everything bagel. They came back and said they're out of the everything bagel as well. My friend ended up paying the same price for a plain bagel with a chicken in between it. Our waitress also encouraged us to upgrade our latte size from a small to a large because it's only a $1 more, so we did. However, the coffee cup wasn't even full. What was supposed to be a large milk and honey latte was just a small milk and honey latte in a large cup..but the price of a large. Overall, the food was very average for the price. I much prefer biscuit love next door. I don't see myself coming back. If I do, I'm coming back when it's not busy. However, they're always busy. Also we waited 50 minutes. Not worth the wait.

It's basically The Habit. The Burgers were a bit larger but double the price, quality was equal. Service was slow. Took 20 mins to meet our waiter. They forgot the waters twice. Took 15 mins for the bill after asking for it. 99 out of 100 you will find me at The Habit. Wasn't a good experience.

I never write reviews, but I felt compelled to do so today. I was here for Essence Fest and wanted to check out some black owned restaurants while in town. We waited for over an hour to be seated, had several celebrity sightings (all of which were seated before us even though we were in line waiting) but the kicker is that the food was mediocre at best. We have to do better people! We ordered a total of 6 different brunch menu items and all were horrible. 

The spinach and feta omelet was the best thing. The shrimp and salmon were over cooked. The grits were waayy too stiff. I could go on but I won't. Very disappointing.

So disappointed in this cafe. For starters our server Kate had the personality of a slug. No smile, no kind words, she only spoke when it was absolutely necessary. The server brought 2 plates with ice cold fries. The french bread requested for the red beans and rice was bought out with globs of ice cold margarine. Overall food and service was absolutely sub- standard. Most definitely will not return.

I live just down the road from this place so I was excited to find a good pie shop near me. I went with my family and felt disappointed. The pizza was average at best.
