My wife and I both felt that it wasn't worth the money. The wait was LONG, we are patient people so we usually don't mind but eventually we wondered if we had been forgotten sitting out on the patio. Maybe our expectations were too high from the reviews but we won't be going back.

Not a place for large groups or a hungry group. Hardly any team work in this venue. Our waitress had a large group spread into 3 tables and no one ever came to help her with drink order, run food, check on us ... nothing, while 4 employees are eating and having a great time 4 tables behind us. Complaining to the manager on site was a joke. He clearly is the one that doesn't enforce teamwork, as the leader needs to leader. Won't be back there

Looked like a great place to get a smoothie. Came by after a workout at the gym at 7:20. I saw one of the employees on the phone talking and another mopping the floor. I pulled on the door twice to open and it was locked. Neither one of them looked my direction as I'm assuming they were ready to go home for the night. Such a shame. First time visiting this establishment and they don't stay open until the posted closing time. Great first impression, I won't be back.

I have been to this store multiple times and have had so many issues. The last time I went I got what I needed and went and checked out only to find that they charged me regular price on a LOT of sale items. I called and they said to bring in the receipt to get the $ back. I went in today and told the cashier about the problem and she rolled her eyes and me and started the process of giving the money back. After about 25 minutes of standing there with a long line behind me and only one other cashier open, I thanked her for taking the time to do the returns. She replied "well it would've been faster if you brought in the items" and rolled her eyes again. I was told to bring in only the receipt and the items I had purchased was yarn. Therefore, the yarn was already used in my projects! I left the store by saying "have a great rest of your day". The cashier (Maryann) didn't even look at me and replied by saying "ok". I am not happy about this store and will never come back.

I was overall, satisfied with the service I received.  They notified me of several repairs they thought I should make, but there was no heavy sales pitch to convince me to follow through on the repairs.  The wait time was reasonable, and the service personnel were courteous and friendly.  The reason I only gave two stars, however, is that, without asking, one of the service representatives "zeroed" my trip odometers.  I can understand why someone would think this was no big deal, however, I depend on both trip odometers to measure mileage for business purposes.  Those measurements are vital to my business expenses, and since I hadn't looked at either recently, I now have no idea how many miles to charge for my business mileage.  Of course, I didn't mention to the jiffy lube personal not to touch the odometers because it never crossed my mind that they would.  I mean, all I went in for was an oil change.  Why did they change the trip odometers for a service that didn't have anything to do with the odometers, especially since I mentioned I didn't want any notification of how many miles I had driven for when I was due for my next oil change?  The inconvenience this has caused me is quite extreme.  Please be aware, that if you too depend on your trip odometers, make certain to mention to the jiffy lube personnel that should leave well enough alone!

Only go to this location if you want cold food that takes 60min to come to your table, if you want one of your party members to not get their food, no refills on water or any other drinks. Other businesses should go here to learn how to run a business to the ground. The new server was the only person competent at his job.

When we first moved to the area a year ago, we were sold on this place. The food was decent but always hot and the service was unbeatable. Over the course of time this place has been the one we avoid the most. My partner suggested going and I immediately said, there are reasons why we don't go there.....sure enough those things held true. 
Our food came out lukewarm or cold, our server had to be reminded a couple of times to refill drinks and when we ordered adult drinks, she didn't even bring them until our meal came. 
I really hate giving bad reviews but just do yourself a favor and skip this place. Once upon a time it was not too bad now .... I'd rather go to Taco Bell before going here.

Food poisoning anyone? I used to order their samosas frequently until I got severely sick recently. My husband also threw up all night. The two stars are because those samosas actually tasted good, but the threat of food poisoning again is just not worth it. I can only imagine the food was prepared in unsanitary conditions or/ and with expired products. Either way, I'm done with this place.

Nice atmosphere, great food, poor service!

Let me start by saying THE FOOD IS DELICIOUS (husband had pasta with vodka sauce, mom had seafood chef's best, and I had manicotti; kids pizza was surprisingly good too!)

What brings the stars down was the AWFUL SERVICE! When you are about to walk out at every stage of a restaurant experience, something is wrong! It took 15 minutes to get water, 45 to get our meals, 30 after that to get the check and boxes - which we had to flag down the host for! In the two hours we were there, our waters were refilled twice.

I've tried livery on multiple occasions, thinking each time it will prove to be a different experience, but unfortunately they are all the same. For one, I've never really known what my food looks like considering the lights are so low. It takes about 30 minutes to decipher the menu and that's using google far too much. Besides the poor presentation the actual taste is far from unique or even tasteful. I hate to hate on a local mass ave restaurant but with property being scarce it's a shame some one with more vision and creativity didn't step in on this lot.

Used to be one of our favorite places for a light dinner with a beer (or two) and a glass of wine. We went there often before concerts and theatre evenings. The last two times we have been there, the food was really mediocre. Given how fresh and lovely their food has always been, that was a real disappointment. My partner, a vegan who tends to hit up the asparagus salad, complained that it was mostly (very hard) bread. On our most recent visit, the duck salad just tasted off, not spoiled, but off. The time before the blue cheese and fig salad (alas--has now been taken off the menu!) had poor quality greens. They've eliminated our favorite bruschetta from the menu--which is the picture that is prominent on Yelp. My partner won't be willing to go back for a while. They need to look at their food gig to better serve those who don't just go for happy hour and a cheese plate.
Poor customer service, sloppy car wash job, non professional personnel. Their manager is rude and argumentative with customers. Just bad experience over all.

We made a reservation for dinner almost a week in advance, only to check in and have the hostess sit us at the bar. Not sure what the point of having a reservation is when we easily could have just walked in and sat at the bar on our own. Not having a table was disappointing. Our server was terrible, we saw him 3x the entire night and had to ask for him on 2 of those interactions. The food was great but overall disappointed with the terrible service and not getting a table despite our week long reservation.

Worst experience ever!!! The agent at the counter was rude & arrogant after I told I decided to cancel my reservation because I was not aware of the additional $100 hold on my credit card. When I called the 800 customers service they informed me that the fee that was charged on my card to hold the reservation will be applied towards the cancellation fees. I didn't see any written policy regarding cancellation fees on the printed brochure or on the website. This is the first I've heard of in all the years I have rented with Avis. This is the worst customer service. I do not recommend this place at all. Rent at your own risk.

Never come back. It took them 40 mins to serve the food (I only ordered noodles soup). The noodles was bad compared to other Malaysian restaurants I have been to. The cut of pork is thick and dry. Tom yum soup is too sour.

I was greatly disappointed with the wait. We were told that they could seat us, but after a 40-minute wait and after being passed over by numerous other parties, we were sent away. Not to mention that my wife and I were accompanied by 2 small children. I will not go back, ever!

The food was blah.2 stars at best.staff seemed annoyed. Bathrooms were disgustingly filthy.there was no tea,container was empty,no BBQsauce containers, no clean tables and a very messy self serve area.never again.this was yesterday at 530pm, 8/5/18. Complete waste of money!

We ordered a basic breakfast and we did not enjoy it. Add to that the service was painfully slow and we had to ask 3 times for ketchup and hot sauce before we received it -the restaurant was not overly crowded so it was hard to understand what the problem was. There are so many great places to eat in New Orleans I would pass on this one.
It's in a nice location and friendly service. But quality is okay.. over priced. I supposedly got "gel nails" but i don't recall gel nails chipping after the second day.

I tried the chicken nachos tonight and got a container of soggy mush. I did try the pick up option and picked up right at the time I specified, so I'm not sure why it was so soggy. It smelled so good and I wanted to like it, but the nachos were completely soft and blended in with the queso. I ended up adding a few of my own chips and having a couple of bites and then tossing the rest of it. I'm hoping my next experience is better because I've heard such good things.

Don't go to this one! Every time I visit this Habit I get sick. My sandwich tasted like it was smothered in cold grease! It left the roof of my mouth and my teeth all greasy! Made me sick to my stomach! The fries weren't cooked all the way through and their veggie patties taste funny. It's like you need to taste everything before you leave with your To Go order so you don't leave with crap food and the loss in funds and your meal. Visit the Habit on upper State near Lens Crafters (La Cumbre mall). They are consistent with their cooking and it's always great.

Food was great but the service was too casual. Took a long time for the order to be ready. The waiter complained about the tip sharing policy of the establishment and about the bus boys not doing their job but still getting the cut off the tip. Very nonchalant and unprofessional. 
Nothing wrong with the good though.

Don't order flowers here unless you want rude and impertinent responses after affectionate order taking.  I ordered flowers to be sent to myself at a hotel.  They are OK, boring and not creative after waiting the entire day for them. I waited nearly all day for the order but come about 4 pm, they did not arrive so I called.  I got a guy named Terry who was insolent.  He said "well we had to stop and get matches for the candle".  I was told the candle/matches was no problem in fact I was 'sold' on the candle emphatically which stinks. Terry insincerely apologized and was impatient with the fact that this was a birthday.  This business is a pox on St. Petersburg. I came her to look for a house but all I have encountered is rude, arrogant business people whose attitude is nothing but me first customer last.  If the flowers were actually lovely, that might make up for it but they are just mediocre.  The oversold candle stinky not nice.  And the bit from Terry on matches, a ridiculous and insipidly incompetent and rude comment to make.  So much for trying to have a nice birthday - get yelled at by someone paid handsomely instead.

Gave this new restaurant a try a few weeks back and had a bad experience. Poor quality on the burger, plain pizza, and Caesar salad. Margherita pie was okay. Hoping it was just a case of them still working out the kinks of a new restaurant because it is so close.

Very disappointed. I left a good review in February but I have to change it. I mentioned that I enjoyed my experience and the manager (Rebecca) helped my family when we were new to this location. I also mentioned the fundraising the owner does. 

I don't know what happened to this store it used to be good until the entire staff changed. All these newer employees are extremely rude. One of my good friends (who still visits this location occasionally) said that after the robbery innocent most of the staff left because, according to an employee at the store now, they weren't pleased by the lack of safety and care. 

To my knowledge, the manager left as well but I'm sure they have another one now. This place is disgusting. The floors are filthy, toppings aren't kept well, they are constantly out of things, and their bathroom is even more disgusting than the store. (if that's even possible) The community is surprised this store didn't get shut down by the health inspection but I'm sure it will in a year. During my last visit, the owner was very rude to us. Didn't let us stay a second past after they close. When I used to be a regular this employee with blue hair let us stay until they were finished with their closing routine but clearly she isn't there anymore either. Looks like this place is going downhill and I used to come here about 3 times a week. Tutti Frutti, I am disappointed in you.

I have been hearing a lot of great things about the appetizers.  We ate there tonight and I ordered the chicken marsala.  What a disappointment!  It looked beautiful but was a Tasteless piece of chicken laying in a bowl with what looked and tasted like dirty water with no resemblance to a marsala sauce.  My wife had the fried chicken which was  just as tasteless with a blah gravy  and a ho hum coleslaw.  Don't think we will give this location another try.  We were told that the Dale Mabry location was much better.  I don't know,  $19 for terrible fried chicken or under $10 for Publix or KFC that is very tasty....nah!

I wanted this place to be good, I really did. We had been talking about coming here for ages and just never got around to it. We finally made it and now I'm regretting it. Most of their pre-arranged menu items are spicy options. While I like spice every now and then, it doesn't always like me (old age means we live and breathe indigestion). There is a build your own option, so I thought I would go for that. You get 4 vegetables and anything else is extra. The average price of the pre-arranged menu items is about $10. So I figured the base of a build your own would be about 8 or 9 and then you add. As I'm going through the line, I start to get my veggies and choose avocado. "That will be an extra $2"....... TWO DOLLARS?? I can buy a whole avocado across the street for $2?! I say no thank you and move on to the cheese. "That will be $.79 extra" I mean... okay, that won't break the bank, frustrating that it's not included but okay, throw it in. I move down to the meat, I'll have chicken. "That'll be an extra $3 dollars." .......... ..... seriously??? I very politely took a hard pass on that. Because in order to get anything with substance and taste, this wrap is looking to be close to $20. I understand that you are paying for freshness and convenience, but there is a line. At least I was hopeful for something tasty once my veggie wrap was complete. Unfortunately, it was dry and the only flavor I could strongly taste was some kind of blue cheesy situation (that I didn't ask for so I'm still not sure what it was). We both painfully threw over half of our overpriced meals away, because they just weren't good. On a positive note, the service was great and the workers seemed very happy and polite! The idea is awesome bc everyone loves a good salad, just not quite the right bang for your buck.

I really like how spacious this location is - the different rooms, and the lounge with a full bar. The staff is friendly. However, the food has not translated well from the mothership in Seminole Heights.  
My first visit was brunch, my ramen was barely room temp. when it arrived, and the broth was thick and gloppy - the place had very few customers at the time. I was too pressed for time, to send it back, so I had to eat it as is.
Had lunch there recently and decided to try the Miso ramen.  The broth was ok, but somewhat overpowered by the taste of that prechopped garlic some restaurants use for convenience - it does not flatter the broth at all.  Prechopped garlic is a travesty.
Also, I would much rather have tofu or seitan, than Impossible burger (what little there was).  The final thing that really dragged it down is that there was literally almost a whole onion's worth of barely cooked, large onion slices.  I had to pull a bunch out, so I wasn't getting a giant mouthful of onion with every bite. If there were bean sprouts in there, I really couldn't detect them. With a veg. ramen, it would be nice to have some kind of mushrooms - just more texture in general.  It feels like the keep it boring so you'll pay more money for extras.  It's $13.50 already.  I have enjoyed the Seminole Heights location and feel like the vibe is way tighter and they are much more on top of everything - I will stick to SH for now.
**my main reason for putting this up on Yelp is that I contacted them after the cold noodle experience and got crickets.  I don't expect a ticker-tape parade, but maybe just a simple "thanks for the feedback".

Cruised up to an open lane, Octopus website open on my smart phone to the coupon page...all ready to save some hard earned cash on an ultimate wash. Until... salesman says they can only accept PRINTED coupons. Wait.. what?  You see the coupon here on my phone and won't honor it?! Salesman says print only.  Says it is his boss's rule. 

This is the 21st century and we shouldn't need to be printing much. Octopus' rule is idiotic. I decided to depart and head less than 1/4 mile up the road for a great wash and dry at a lower cost. 

Being that the Octopus owner doesn't care much for the Internet, he probably wont see this review.  I should PRINT a copy for him.

Checking front desk person was not nice and made a rude comment. Not a welcoming first impression. 
Valet was great and so friendly. Fast. 
Good location for Convention Center. 
Room. Fine. 
Best part of the whole stay: the buffet breakfast/ brunch!!
$30 buys you the most delicious spread of top quality meats/ fruits/ pastries/ EU style delicacies. 
The buffet should be on everyone's list while visiting Philly.

SLOW. Declining food quality. The last two times I have ordered it has taken at least an hour to get my sandwich. The last time I ordered, after 50 minutes the driver called me and said he was at our office. 15 minutes later he still wasn't there. When he did arrive, there was confusion with the order. 

Two orders ago - my chips were stale. This last order, there was one small piece of bacon on the club Lulu and the turkey had an odd taste. 

After two years of ordering almost weekly, I am moving on. The speed and quality of the food have declined significantly and there are now better options available.

Hmm...passed by for the first time and decided to stop in.  The space is cute and looks like a great place to hang out, but the overall experience was not great. 

Ordered the oolong milk foam tea, but they didn't have any milk foam even in the early afternoon.  The staff didn't mention that they would be making anymore either.    Instead, I had to order a regular oolong milk tea and also 2 grapefruit fresh teas for my family.  There were maybe two people in line in front of me, but my order took 20 minutes.  Some of the staff seemed to be working hard while others were constantly checking their cell phone.  When I finally arrived at my car, I tried the oolong milk tea and it was literally just milk (lactaid or milk powder?) with tapioca.  There was no tea taste at all.  The color of my drink was white.  The grapefruit juices were just ok at all.  It was also inconvenient that they didn't offer a bag or tray until I asked since I had 3 large drinks to carry out.  Overall, the place is unorganized and definitely has room for improvement.  With so much competition nearby, I hope they can improve since the space is great.

Really bad.  This place was great years ago but is on an extreme descent.  It took close to a half hour to get a few average tacos.  The chips were bland and the verde salsa tasted sour.  The staff in the back were yelling and fighting.  Probably time to close shop and let someone put this valuable location to good use.

This place is complete garbage. Do NOT waste your money! For starters, it was extremely expensive at about $800 for just one room for 2 nights. I think we got ripped off because I have stayed in New Orleans in the French quarter area on several other occasions and have never paid so much! The inside of the hotel is less than impressive, the rooms are old and almost dirty looking, there is no pool or any other amenities. The parking situation is terrible, they force you to valet at $44/night and when we arrived there wasn't even a valet "on duty" per the lady working the front desk. The housekeeping staff didn't even make one of our beds and there was no WiFi password offered. The staff seemed largely incompetent as they told us twice that our room was ready for check in, only when we arrived we were told that it wasn't ready. There is absolutely no inkling of customer service at this place. Trash place. Zero stars.

The trainer pushed my leg so far as to tear my muscle, which has now lead to physical therapy, and possible surgery, I'm disgusted by this gym. Trying to cancel the contact with a doctors letter stating this reason, getting told it will probably be declined because I'm not permanently damaged. So they will only cancel your membership and/or training after they permanently damage your body. Not before. Not when their trainer already tore your muscle. But after. Even asked, so I have to continue paying 350 a month, with an already damaged leg, cause you won't stop charging me, after you have been told by a doctor that I have damage and continuing to push it will cause permanent damage but you won't cancel until you and your personal trainer actually cause the permanent damage. Good business practices LA Fitness. Stay far away from this place. Never have I had a business actually tell me I have to permanently disable myself before they will stop.

This place was once my favorite but this recent experience wasn't the greatest. The waiter left us waiting for 15 minutes without ordering. We waited another 30 minutes for our drinks. It's not excuse for "being busy". There needs to be a better plan on time-management, customer service training, and for proper communication etiquette. Always takes forever for service yet so impatient for the check. Also, there's not enough vegan options and chocolate/caffeine-free desserts.

Nice outdoor atmosphere, big problem with no way to call them. The website has no contact info, only hours open and closed. We wasted our time going there to find the kitchen was closed more than 2 hours before closing time.
This location drive thru is so slow, I've been waiting in line for ten minutes before is started writing this review. There are still two cars ahead of me...

I'm an old fashion girl that really appreciates good customer service. It's very hard to find now a days where a hostess actually does their job and welcomes you to an establishment. This Village Inn was no exception. I'm not really that picky just a simple hello and follow me and I will seat you will work. I should have let that be my que to just leave, but I chose to stay and eat. My food tasted like old grease. I got eggs, bacon and hash browns. My daughters food was cold. I can't complain about the waitress because she did her job. Nothing more, nothing less. I'm really disappointed to write this as I grew up going to Village Inn. I didn't buy a pie because I was afraid it was going to be horrible and the memory of a good Village Inn pie would be lost forever.

I work in the area and have been to this location at least 6 times in the past 3 months. The good: food is delicious, full of great flavor and always fresh tasting. The pita bread is so fluffy and perfect. The bad: the workers here are the most unprofessional and unpleasant individuals I have ever encountered in the food industry. I've visited prior to the lunch rush, during lunch rush and even after.. All the same, miserable and almost like you are inconveniencing them just by walking in the door. So I started ordering online instead to skip the interaction only to find out the two times I have when I go to pick up (well after my designated pickup time) they haven't even started my order. No apologies, nothing just a "we are starting the order now" and this last time "you are going to have to wait I just noticed you're order"!! The woman that works there, mostly from 11-4 Monday through Friday is whom I encounter most and should be switched to food prep in the back or fired. My coworkers have all expressed the same complaints. I am certain this location will not stay open for long and I plan to take my business to Choolah around the corner instead! They are welcoming as soon as you enter the door and food is just as delicious!!! Their naan bread, way better!

Really wanted to like this based on the glowing reviews. But it took WAY too long and the food just wasn't up to New Orleans' standards.Shrimp and grits - Literally 3 little shrimp, no andouille. Compared with the picture of shrimp and grits from another review only 6 days before I'm not sure what happened here. Pork chop tough and flavorless. (Those glowing reviews were from Illinois, New York and California, nice places, but..... not New Orleans.) Sorry folks, can't recommend.

Murphy's prepared "smoked" items need help.

Bought the Murphys cooked smoked ribs on one visit-
they were horrible.

Recently bought Murphys smoked baked beans. From the taste,
appearance and smell ---it seems like they opened a can of prepared
baked beans and added artificial smoke flavoring and sugar. They were vile.
And 24 hours later-I still cannot get the "smoke" smell out of my
microwave.

Discontinue these items or vastly improve them.

If I could give negative zero stars I would. I came here tonight and it was gross. I normally love Taco Bell, but this was pathetic. Soggy tacos, no ice in my drink, no sauces, the drive thru member almost gave me another customers order, my cheese wasn't melted in my cheesy roll up... rude service as well. I will not be returning !

Upon entering the restaurant I was looking forward to enjoying some good company, food and music but shortly after sitting down I slowly was let down. While I did enjoy the music I was first informed they were out of mint so I could not order a mojito, mind you this was around  6:30pm on a Friday night. What kind of Mexican establishment doesn't stay stocked with fresh mint, especially on one of the biggest drinking days of the week. I sadly had to settle for another cocktail. I then proceeded to order the chicken tacos which were a huge disappointment from looking at other dishes served. It was literally dry chicken, rice and cheese. Overall first time dining experience was a major let down.

The service started out great and the food was good, then a shift change happened.  The bar was not busy, and the service was terrible.  Food that was ordered never came out, took 45 minutes to get a side salad before our meal.  May or may not try again.
Just went to hit some balls. A large bucket is $14, so I literally walked out. Plus, you can only hit off mats.

Not nearly 4 or 5 stars. Poor service and under average food. Served my wife who is allergic to bacon (asked for no bacon) soup with bacon in it. I got roast beef that tasted like floppy sandals (bad). Was expecting something similar to Panera but no. Now worth the stop

My wife and I visited for the first time. We got our menus and waited for 10+ minutes and nobody ever came to take our drink order. Other people that came in after us were being helped. Really bad impression for our first visit.

The appetizer we tried was the roti canai and it was like watered down indian food with barely any chicken in it. I got the rice dish with ginger duck as my main meal. The duck was soggy and not flavorful. My fiancé got the spare ribs. They were also really bland and maybe needed some salt/spices. I'm not a picky eater at all and love all different types of dishes. The food here was actually just really bad.

We arrived over an hour before the posted closing time, and were greeted with "I'm closing early."  So much for IHOP, we went to Dave's Dogs across the freeway and had a good meal -- and they stayed open.  If I had pulled something like that when I was in food service I would have been fired!

I had an appointment to replace a tire sensor, a 10 minute job. After a two hour wait I asked the representative what the problem  was and was told they were working on it. At the three hour mark I walked into the garage and was quickly stopped and told I couldn't be in there. I looked in and my car was not even in the garage! I went back to the representative and was told it was in a different area behind the one I had looked at. At this point I walked around the building and they had just started working on on the car. The mechanic apologized and said that he would get to it right away but he was working on three vehicles. 10 minutes later the car was pulled around in front. I walked The vehicle was pulled in front of the shop. I walked back to the representative to check out. I waited while she busied herself with no one, and it took 20 minutes before she checked me out.  I walked out to my car after 4 hours! This experience was unnecessary, unprofessional, and not acceptable!!!!

Got to say was very disappointed with the service. Waitress was rude and food took forever even though it wasn't that crowded. When it arrived it wasn't that good. Don't recommend with all the other seafood places around that neighborhood

Horrible and terrifying experience last year. Don Staten completely disturbed me. He complimented me constantly & proceeded to COME OUT TO MY CAR after the appointment and knock on my window to "let me know if there was anything else I needed" and gave me his phone number. Disgusting. If you're a young women don't go here alone!!!

They suck their staff are super roud and they don't respect customers. They know their service only comes from college kids so they know they have to keep up with basic standards which is pretty bad even for college kids (I'm a student myself). Honestly horrible establishment.

I wanted to like this place as the food was good but they crammed our party of 11 into a single booth which ruined the night. On top of that, the portions were not sized right for our group so most left hungry and the service was poor. The oddest thing of the night was they kept locking the door to the restaurant despite it being middle of service (7pm). Would not recommend.

There was no soy sauce in my order. Barely any ponzu sauce and the tuna and salmon were sliced in correctly. I'm VERY disappointed. How can you slice fish into LARGE cubes? Never ordering from here again. The tuna is brown, the jalapeños are not fresh. I would like a full on refund.

Wasn't impressed, yes it was a Sat night, yes the NHL playoffs were across the street so I expected a wait.  Only waited about 15 min for a table....then came the real wait and I couldn't say it was the waitress' fault she was attentive and sweet but she had nothing to give us, drinks weren't coming out fast enough food was ready.  Disappointed in the prices too, 2 dinners and app $68 no sodas no liquors....just another chain

I ordered here through grubhub and after waiting almost an hour and a half I finally call the restaurant to see where my food is. Turns out they forgot the order. They refused to comp my food and tried to deliver it 2 hours after I placed the original order. I'll never order from here again.
You get what you pay for. Shrimp and vegetable tempura means you get 1 shrimp. Lol. Just FYI.

So they appreciate my candid feedback. Just so you know, as of today, July 30, 2018, this truck is still on their lot and is now marked at $25,900, more than $2,000 less than what I had offered to pay for it, and a full $4,000 less than their original price of $29,900 that they weasled me around on. Car dealerships and salesman ARE all the same, and they will screw you the first chance they get. If Crown Honda weren't so GREEDY, they would have made a sale at $27,986 and be more than $2,000 better off than they are now.
Food is good but expensive for what you get here I ordered a burrito for $11 guess that's just just the flour tortilla beans, rice and lettuce because it's another $3 if you want meat inside.

Long wait time for outside seating. Food was OK. WAY TOO SPICY. Not able to enjoy due to food being way to spicy. 
Waitress too busy. Very friendly but way too busy.

Very disappointed and the gal hurt me! Don't go to Queen nails unless you want to pay for Chinese torture and a subpar manicure that costs $30 dollars plus credit card machine not working so prepared to bring cash. Really annoying!
Your venue is ridiculous. Too many people let on and crappy acoustics.  Maybe I would love it if I were a hipster.

I'd give them a zero if I could. I hired this company for post construction cleaning. They are a bunch of crooks. The owner Larry will come to you first and give you a great presentation as if you'll be able to eat off your floors. Well let me tell you when I saw these 2 jokes walk into my moms condo I already knew this job was going to be a nightmare. They use the cheapest equipment. Stuff bought at Walmart or Target. No commercial cleaning equipment. They used one rag to dust the entire place. I kept telling them I feel a film on all the furniture. Their excuse was that it is post construction and it takes a few times. Well after they left I grabbed a bottle of windex and a paper towel and the film magically disappeared. Then they used a cheap little steamer machine to clean the floors. I looked at them after they dried and they still had debris and dirt on the tiles. Again they said it was hard after one cleaning to get all that perfectly clean. Then why did Larry the owner assure me it would be perfect. They charged me over $330 for a tiny one bedroom apt that I had to clean all over by myself. WASTE IF MONEY!!!!!

!'ve been twice now.  I don't get it.  Lunchmeat sandwiches on kind of stale, too-thick Italian bread with coleslaw and unseasoned fries.  It's not awful but not very good.  The bread falls apart and the sandwich just doesn't have very much flavor.  It would be better to serve the fries and slaw on the side (and season the fries) and just put lettuce, tomato, onion, etc. on the sandwich.  I've also had a burger, which was dry and fell apart because it had too much stuff on it.

This seems more like a place you'd go to for drink specials or because it's convenient, not for the food.

The girl in the drive thru had an attitude with me when I asked about the puppy cup. She wasn't friendly at all. When I got the puppy cup it had one dollop of whip cream.... so then I ask if I could have some more and she barely gives me anything and says sure..like that's not cool. If it's such a problem and hassle I'll pay, that's not the issue. I go to this Starbucks all the time. I don't know what her issue is but she needs to fix it

Tonight was our first visit to The Mason Jar. We'll never go back. The food was OK, but the experience wasn't worth what we paid. Just after filling our drinks, the ice ran out in the drink machine. And both iced teas (both sweet and unsweet) ran out as well. It took 50 minutes for our food to arrive. Tables around us were at no time cleared off/cleaned. We were in the restaurant for more than hour; at no time did they make an effort to replenish the drink machine station. My daughter ordered the fried shrimp platter--it was supposed to come with shrimp, fries, onion rings, hush puppies, and toast. The toast was burned (buried at the bottom of the platter) and there were no hush puppies. We requested the hush puppies--they never brought us any, even though it was part of our order. While were there other customers complained about the service and food. And some left before being served.

This was recommended by the valet guy and was the ONLY bad meal we had.  We waited for 15 minutes to get a table. They put us by the open door even though we asked to be inside because it was chilly out.  Waited 15 minutes before our waitress even came around. We should have walked out then, but we thought the food would make up for it. Wrong!  This waitress kept having her table's food and drinks being returned for being wrong.  She couldn't get anything right.  My friend and I ordered the try 3, which comes out of pots and placed in bowls, so we should have been served quickly. No, we waited an hour.  Every time I saw the waitress, which wasn't often, she said it was on it's way out. When it did come out, the jambalaya was cold and the crawfish etoffee was lukewarm and the gumbo had no meat in it. What a waste of our time. Tourist trap I'm sure because it's on Canal, so stay away.

Our server was the only reason I gave two stars instead of one, he was prompt, polite and friendly. 19 dollars for 3 scallops that were rubbery and completely flavourless de-railed our dinner experience train very quickly but my partner and I stayed optimistic because almost every entree on the menu looked to be a good choice. I got the pan seared sea bream and she got the rabbit. All I can say is that both meals were almost flavourless. The fish tasted like tilapia you buy from Safeway and throw in the oven. My brother and I caught a rabbit when we were teenagers at my cabin in the foothills and bbq'd it after butchering it ourselves and made a much better piece of meat then was served to us last night. Every single aspect of the food was underwhelming, there was no wow factor that a 40 dollar dish anywhere else has. The word bland was used by both of us with every part of both our meals. Our server asked how our meals were and I was completely honest with him. He took it very graciously, and didn't charge us any of our 39 dollar alcohol tab to try and make amends. Highly unlikely either of us will ever go back. Mucho burrito would be a better choice for a night out...

The staff at the spa are incredibly friendly and professional, but the rest of the staff are sub-par. It's too big, I think, to provide good customer service. I got lost getting to my room as the front desk staff did not tell me the correct directions (he even gave me a map where he highlighted the wrong way!!) The food and service at the Conservatory Wine Bar are AWFUL! The Margherita pizza literally was a flatbread with tomato paste as the sauce (and burnt tomatoes!).  None of the housekeeping staff will say hi in the hallways...which is a sure sign they are not happy here! Too bad...what a gorgeous hotel to mess up!!!

Overpriced food. Slow service. Not worth the effort. Mentioned slow, inattentive service to the manager and he said we could always eat elsewhere. Won't be back. There are too many good restaurants in the area to put up with that kind of attitude. This place will be closing soon. Not very busy at the lunch hour.

its closed! Health Department violations.  Does not look like it's going to reopen.
Gone-Goodbye

Picked up a large with sausage, green peppers, and black olives the cost $9.50. The only good thing about the pizza was the crust and the price. As another reviewer mentioned, they don't even out the dough so there was substantial more at the top of the pizza while the bottom was falling apart with the ingredients. The pizza was not hot, even after warming it for 20 seconds, very soggy, and the toppings were horrible (looks like they don't use real sausage). Pizza was very inconsistent, such as not being uniformly warm, sloppy, thin sauce, and cheese that easily slide off the pizza. Some of the guys look like they are in drugs, which is not surprising due to the poor quality of their pizza. This was one of the worst pizzas I have ever eaten! Folks that think this pizza is good need to have their head examined! I doubt those folks travel much outside the country let alone the local area. Delco standards are so low....:(

The staff is nice and the food is Ok, for a fast food lunch.  My issue there is the lack of cleanliness.  The dining area is always dirty, even after the line of customers is long gone.  This isn't the case with McDs, Jimmy Johns or Arby's (all very close by).

Food was way over priced I liked the food but I'll never in my life will pay that much for a taco again that was crazy. $50 was just too much for 4 tacos 2 drinks and I'm not an ass so I left a tip, hopefully they change their prices soon. Good food though.
Awful service burger was raw when asked to be medium well. Waitress was rude dropped the food ran away dropped the check ran away. They werent even busy. Go some where else.

Great food. Drink orders took forever, and for a while my table of 5 were the only ones there. At the end of the meal they informed us that they could only take cash because their machine was down. Didn't offer to take an imprint the old fashioned way. Nope, they said that there was an ATM down the street. We were having torrential rains, and we were told to go get cash. A friend said this happened to him before. 

Not worth the trouble.

I was referred to Greco Rose Beauty for an upcoming event in early August 2018.  I sent an email to their info@ email address in mid-June and received a response from them 4 days later confirming they are available and would love to be a part of the event team.  I thought, "Great!"

I followed up with them in July a few times to confirm and discuss details but have never heard back.  I also left voicemail messages on the only phone number I have for Greco Rose Beauty -- listed in their email signature.  No response.

I am now frantically trying to find new make-up artists for an event next weekend. Really disappointing experience.
I wanted to love it but the mole' was mediocre. I have had many types of mole' and yet to find a good one in Tucson shoot even great authentic Mexican food. What happened to the food here?

I'm not exactly sure how this place is getting such good reviews. Besides the fact that the staff was kind...I ordered guacamole and chips, a chicken taco, and a beef taco. The guacamole was old and bland...it literally tasted like nothing, the chips super oily and tasteless, the tacos were cold. The chicken had a odd taste...possibly nutmeg? Not sure but it wasn't for me. I prefer more spice/heat for my tacos. The beef was also cold and didn't have a good taste. I could of done better with an Old Elpaso taco kit from the grocery store. I'm sad that I wasn't pleased. But maybe it was just me because at least 4 "soccer mom types" were waiting in line for pickup??!!! Haha

Went last night with friends for birthday celebration.  A total disaster for 3 main reasons.  Frist, an dinner was forgotten and we had to wait 4 mins for it to arrive-an eternity.  Second, coffee ordered was ice cold, had to wait 5 mins for hot coffee, an eternity.  Third, it was a surprise birthday and was set up prior to us arriving.  The waiter forgot about  the cake that was delivered mid afternoon, the wait staff started putting down desert plates before the cake arrive blowing up the surprise.  The food was expensive and only average.  Certainly not worth what we paid.  Never again.

So to start there wasn't a single person inside the restaurant and I was still told to wait in the drive through for 4 1/2 minutes. Then I waited for 8 more minutes for 1 item. Fat boy manager was just playing on his phone and everybody who talked to me was in a poor mood. So despite garbage food that tasted 3 days old, I was greeted with garbage customer service. You need a training team or a whole new crew. I will not be returning.

Agree with the other reviews that are unhappy with this location.. I am about to replace all my makeup .. lucky to have several gift cards to help.. this location is so close . I went in Thursday to start looking around .. I was basically ignored and even spent 15 minutes browsing. There was a sales person with a white coat on and was too busy to bothered as she was stocking makeup in the front of the store .. left and decided to come back the next day. a Friday .. even took a ulta bag  from the lobby to show I was getting a few items .. this time at least she yelled to me welcome to ulta but that was it ..it was the same sales clerk and was too busy to come up to me because she was too busy stocking the same exact spot as the day before .. after 10' minutes I left .. with several other ultras are close this one won't get my money

Today, we visited this restaurant in Philadelphia.
We drove from New Jersey to come here not a very inviting welcome. Almost, borderline rude this place will never get anymore of my money!!
If proved you shouldn't go to places you follow on Instagram. Not sure how the food is as of yet didn't taste it yet. Just put off by the vibe!! The lady at covered in longs and scratching her hair. A worker comes in she working in her coat topping food,packing food.. WTH once we finally got our food my husband checked the bag to make sure all our food was in there, It started to leak out everywhere no came over they saw the mess. When, I asked for more bags because it was leaking bad he said what kind of bags......
They customer service suck assssss, we drove from NJ just to come here. What a terrible experience..

My engagement ring has lost 2 stones in 2 years. Jared's refuses to replace the stones despite the fact that I have a warranty specifically for this. They also say that unless I lose 3 stones per year, my ring is not considered to have any issues. I called to speak to corporate who told me they would "rather speak to my husband on these issues"...what??

I have to be honest, I'm shocked at how bad this place actually is. We stopped by here Sunday for some sandwich's to go. Big mistake! We ordered a variety for us and some friends.

Presentation wise, all the food looked good. We ordered pastrami sandwich. It was terrible! Overly salty and covered in lettuce. The rye bread was by far the best part. The turkey club was equally as bad. The turkey was beyond dry and the bacon wasn't very fresh. You could tell it was reheated, it was chewy but rock hard. The Italian hoagie flat out tasted funny. The meat was cut super thick and it was also very slimy. The hoagie lacked seasoning but it was covered in onions. Due to the taste and look of it we trashed it. The pierogis were easily forgettable. They were your typical stuff and not very good. They turkey special, again the turkey was dry. The thousand island was good but again something out of a jar, cole slaw was the same. All
Of the sandwiches are large but that's not always good. I'd prefer quality over quantity but that's just me.  The cheesesteak egg rolls were the best part of our meal. They were actually edible.

Overall it was a terrible experience and we would not return. To say we were disappointed would be an understatement. It's really hard to mess up one sandwich, let alone 6.

I'm not sure if Fiorello's is under new ownership/management, but I've been disappointed in our takeout from here the last three times. This makes me so sad because this was my favorite local Italian restaurant, especially for take out. Their Caesar Salad used to taste homemade and delicious. Now the dressing tastes like it comes from a bottle. Our mozzarella sticks had O% cheese inside, our pizza crust was tough, and the chicken parm tasted off. Usually Fiorello's food is ON POINT. I'm just not sure why their quality has gone downhill.

Service was very,very slow considering it is an order at the counter place. I got the salted caramel donut which was good, but not great. The donut was a little heavy. I also orderd the cinnamon roll which I did not care for. It came swimming in gooey icing and was soooo overly sweet that you almost couldn` t taste the cinnamon. Plus they had sprinkled sugar on top of the roll too!  Sometimes balance of flavors is more important than just throwing everything in. If they had free wifi I couldn`t find it.

COCKROACHES!  This was our first time here, and we really looked forward to it.  Alas, it was a disaster, which had nothing to do with the food. That being said, we will NEVER go back. 
 Sure, the food took a long time to come out, and one entree arrived about 15 minutes after the other, but we can deal with that.  But just after we finally got our food, there came a COCKROACH crawling up the wall next to our table!  We told the waiter and he took a napkin and squashed it.  Then he split, without the slightest apology. Despite that, we decided to suck it up and continue our meals. Not 1 minute later ANOTHER cockroach appeared, this time on one of the PLATES containing our food!  Needless to say, that was just too much. We all got up to leave, and I asked to see the manager. The workers that we told said the manager "just left". Our waiter was nowhere to be found, either. (I suspect they were one and the same guy.) One of the workers (a woman) said "they (the cockroaches) come from upstairs". So obviously this is an ongoing problem. We received not the slightest apology from anyone.  We will never return, of course.  And I will report them to the health department on Monday (today is Saturday).
how about you try answering the phone once in a while. i waited on the phone for so long that i learned all the words to your crappy country theme song. it's a MONDAY not a friday night

Since you don't take reservations, but you accept call ahead seating.  Take the call ahead when a customer calls in.  Don't tell me that there is no wait currently and i will be ok.  Then when I arrive you tell me it's a 45 minute wait.  This is the second time in a row that this happened.

This place is garbage.  The food is awful. I think its the First Chinese restaurant I've ever been to that doesn't provide steamed rice with its entrees.  Worst beef with broccoli and sesame chicken I've had in memory. Beef is somehow hard and chewy at the same time.

So the good part is the burger was great. A bit overpriced ($18) but very good none the less. Everything else at this newer restaurant was a hot mess!!  Many of the staff are new -- ok -- train them -- no one could explain the Tuesday Night specials -- basically a sign on the table stating $4 craft beers  -- which was completely different than the other sign that talks about happy hour from 4-7 -- so, craft beer (as generally defined as Not Budweiser) is loosely defined by the bartender as Local only -- so the "craft beer" brewed in the next town over didn't qualify??  WTF. Another waitress told us everything under $6 (so only 4 of the 20+ draft choices) and another told us all the drafts were essentially half price?

I'll be shocked to see this place still in business in 6 months!!  Unless, of course, they have a celebrity rescue from Jon Taffer or maybe Robert Irvine?!!

Went here for lunch- when we first arrived, they could not seem to figure out who was going to be our server. It took an hour to get our food (it was clear they forgot to put in our order). The manager gave us a dismissive apology and offered us a coupon for the next time we come in, but at this point that's useless because I don't think I'll be coming back. Finally got our food and both my friends' avocado toast looked awful- the avocados were black. The people around us appeared to be having a similar experience, as many of them sent back dishes and complained of a long wait. Also the bathrooms were DISGUSTING. Will not be returning, absolutely abysmal service and basically zero compensation for the wait or the bad food.

Kelly's " for just about anything" is no longer, RIP. First visit since new ownwership. New owners took everything away that was Kelly's; good service, outstanding food, even the unique salt and pepper shakers - gone. Started out waiting for table, we were told 45 min. Ok, Sunday morning 11:00, expected that. However, 90 min later, still not sat. Approached hostess and was told we were next table. Waited another 20 min. watching empty tables not get cleared. Approached manager about wait time, he said, unapologetically, "sorry, my wait staff didn't let me know." Now seated 2 hours later, was met with unfamiliar menu. Where was the Benedict specials of the day? Again, no longer. New menu equivalent to a Denny's, nothing special. The special service you always felt you got at Kelly's, gone, replaced with sad servers and matter of fact treatment. I will forever miss the old Kelly's. Save your time and find a better place.

I have been coming to GSR for a very long time, to the point that many of the employees know me or my husband. I have been to Lex many times, mostly getting a VIP but sometimes just to enjoy a nice out. My most recent visit to see Fetty Wap was horrible, it's sad to me that an establishment like Lex doesn't have a better management and is completely unorganized.  To start we got in the VIP line and our ticket that had our table # was lost, so we waited a good 45 minutes to even get through the door.  I had already given them my credit card when we got there. When the hostess came to our table and took our order she asked for my card, I told her I had already given it and she said ok she would look in the back. She came back about 15 minutes later and said they couldn't find it. Me and my husband had to go out to the front and ask around to look for it. Apparently it was randomly in on of the black books they carry out front.  So now the hostess leaves to get our drinks.  They never brought our mixers or our ice so the hostess had to get everything herself, she was actually working very hard.  I appreciated her. We finally get to having a drink about 2 hours later. 
If that were the last issue I don't think I would be so frustrated. I read another review where the manager responded they don't deny guest water.  I walked to the empty front bar to ask for water and the bartender told me they don't provide water I would have to buy it. After I just paid for my VIP, I see one of the front guys I believe his name was Roman and I tell him. He said don't worry I got you, he sends a bucket of water with a receipt for $36 I told the random hostess I'm not paying for this I just wanted one water cup for my husband who wasn't feeling well. She gets Roman and he acts like he had never spoke to me and didn't know what I was talking about and the girl snatches the water off the table and walks away.

Went there tonight for the first time with a party of 14. We had a pre-determined menu. The food was mediocre to bad. Given the plethora of amazing Italian American restaurants within spitting distance - this was really disappointing. And even more disappointing was the staff. They all seemed really unhappy to be there and unhappy we were there. Rude and unsmiling. (The only friendly person was the bus person - he was lovely.) And they told us quite abruptly after dessert that we needed to leave (immediately) because they needed to seat another party. I worked in restaurants for years - and it was very unprofessional and done very rudely. Sometimes you do have to ask a larger party to move along - but do it with some grace and some forewarning. I will not be going back.

Upon arriving for my 7:30 reservation a bit early I was told quite quickly by the host that it would be about 5 mins. That was it, no please feel free to grab a drink at the bar, have a seat while you wait, nothing. After about 10 mins waiting I made my way to the bar to order a glass of wine for me and my guest. The bartender walked by multiple times without acknowledging me or offering a menu, I took a menu from a guest next to me. When he finally come to take my order there was no hello, no how are you, no sentence at all. It was just a simple word.. Drink? No smile nothing at all to make me feel welcomed.

When we were finally sat, our server came by. Once again no smile, no hello, how are we tonight? Just her name and weather we wanted tap or bottle water. Through out the course of our meal, she was inattentive, in-personable, barely smiling or trying to interact with us. 

The biscuits they dropped at the beginning of our meal where the highlight of the evening, the butters perfect and the biscuits wonderfully fluffy and layered to perfection

We started with some snacks, pig ears came out overly salted, and room temp and chewy. As if they'd been sitting a minute. The conch fritters were good, well seasoned and the sauce added great balance.

We finished up and what I'm assuming was a service manager or floor manager came by with our second course... mind you we had not been cleared or re-silvered from our first course. Instead of turning around and clearing us before dropping food, he simply dropped the courses and walked away.. coming back after a few minutes to clear the dirty plates and drop new share plates. 

Our second courses were the gulf shrimp with Calabrian Chile's which were tasty, and a very good dish... the tuna tartar on the other hand was again extremely salty, maybe due to seasoning before considering that salty tobiko/caviar of some type was going on top which made the dish almost inedible. 

This time our plates were cleared and we did get re silvered. For our entrees we ordered the "acclaimed" curry goat and the red fish dish.

Neither dish wowed me. The fish was one dimensional, there was no textural contrast in the dish. The sauce, the fish, the garnish, was all soft, room temp, and this time extremely under seasoned. It was lacking some sort of acidity and crunch to wake it up. The goat was under seasoned as well and lacking depth. Though the gnocchi was very well cooked and made it was not enough to save the dish. The sad thing is, even though our distaste was apparent, the server made no inquire as to why we hadn't eaten our entrees. no manager came to check on us, it seemed as though the staff was just floating through their night. 

I expected a lot more from the service and food for a restaurant as widely acclaimed as this one is. Nothing about this evening screamed best new chef, James beard award nominee, or eater hot 38. This was appalling service from start to finish and the food to match. Definitely sucks when you're on vacation and this is your one special meal and you get the bill and are out 200 dollars after tip for something you wish never happened.

We ended up skipping dessert and going someplace else.

Edit* Extremely disappointed at the fact that I have yet to receive any response from the management. You would think that they would want to at least try to redeem them selves for this but alas... just floating through on the laurels

If you have any reaction to gluten or any other allergy, I wouldn't bother with this place. Despite their menu stating things were gluten free and my asking our waitress twenty questions before ordering, I started feeling sick before even leaving the restaurant.

On our way out I stopped another waitress and asked her about my meal and she informed that it did indeed contain gluten. We complained and got a refund no questions asked, but that doesn't change the fact that I'm sicker than a dog.

Very poor management. I've been asking for a coffee machine since morning because the one in my room is not working. I called the desk and I went to the dest personally more than 5 times. All they told me is "wait a min, we'll send someone right away" Nobody ever came in my entire stays. Totally waste of money. Not worth it.

Atmosphere is cool, Food is not great , service is terrible. I wont be back, and would strongly recommend you avoid it as well. 
We waited to be set down, then waited to get our drinks, only one refill the entire 2 hours we were here, then we ordered and they forgot to put my food in and said it would be at least 10 more minutes before mine came. My husband ordered pick 2, I said "would bbq be faster" they said yes and quickly brought a pick two like his.. not only did we not get an apology from a manager, they charged me for both meats. Then we waited for our check.. service was so slow. It took us a few hours for something that should've taken at most an hour. 
The restaurant was not very busy, and there just wasn't an excuse for such bad service and lack of trying to make up for this.

We were staying at the Hilton with a group of people. We decided to go down to the bar to have an appetizer and drinks prior to dinner. After hanging out for a couple hours spending around $700 for our group of 10-12 people, the manager approached us to tell us we needed to conduct business there or leave. What in the actual? In my town that's real money. My husband was so pissed he wrote on the check, thank your manager for the tip. In 15 years, I have never seen him not leave a tip. She then had the gall to come berate us for not tipping. Btw, while our server was polite he was not very attentive. For the remainder of the trip, we walked directly across the street to the Intercontinental bar and had great food and service without anyone busting our chops.
They were not very pleasant and this was the worst keot of the 3 or 4 or 5 Plato's Closet stores. I felt disdain from them.
Beer was great, food was okay, service was abysmal. Every staff member besides the hostess was so rude. Wasn't even busy so I don't understand why they were so unpleasant.

Restaurant Week Fail! We met a group of friends to celebrate a birthday during Restaurant Week in January.  After over an hour waiting for food, they sent complimentary soups and bread. The soup was a coagulated mess. When the food finally arrived, it was a disaster and was cold.  One of the guests found a hair fried into their crab cake.  My steak was so dry that when I tried to cut it, it flew off the table. The tiny piece that I tried had an odd taste that led me to believe it was old.  The manager did apologize.  However, she attempted to convince me that the steak was put under a broiler and cooked too long.  I have had steak at every price point from Outback to Maestros and never had something so disgusting.  Pass.

I was really looking forward to visiting Newtown's first French cafe. What a disappointment. There is nothing about it that seems French other than a small assortment of French pastries. My family of 4 was the only order they had to take while we were there on a Sunday afternoon. They made each item (2 crepes and 2 waffles) one at a time and brought them out one at a time, several minutes apart. By the time my daughter got her undercooked (wet inside) waffle, everyone else was done and ready to go. The crepes were just ok, but my children's waffles did not come with the toppings they ordered. One ordered bananas and Nutella, the other strawberries and bananas with Nutella. Both had weird toppings like apple, cantaloupe, blueberries, and grapes. We sent back the last Waffle and left, resulting in a very disappointed child. I will not be back. 
Only positive: my husband says his latte was good.

This place went downhill really fast. The long waiting time for a simple order, and really unclean conditions make this place not worth going to. I used to love to go here but after a while I stopped due to the things I listed at the beginning of this review. I was completely disappointed. The fries at many times were either soggy or burn, and the burger had no flavor. That's all I want to say, thank you for your time.

Unbelievable first time experience here at this Wendy's  in Tucson.  Ordered my meal which came to $15.17. I gave them a $15 gift card and a dollar bill to cover the 17 cents. Simple right? After the cashier called another teenager over because he did not understand how to do the gift card they handed the gift card back to me told me that I had $.83 left on the gift card. I explain to them that the gift card was $15 and since the total was 15.17 they owed me .83 cents. THEN.... The teenage female manager gets involved trying to convince me that I have a balance on the gift card! After explaining twice the SIMPLE math involved she gives me my change which was incorrect so I waited again to get the correct amount of change. Very scary Knowing this is Americans future in making it great again!  I understand now why it has a two star rating For this store. Need some adults here to supervise the children

The reason I give more than one star is that at least I can grab an Upland Wheat on tap. Otherwise, my experiences here consistently fail.

I was a regular at the Bloomington Upland when I was at IU, and I rejoiced when I found out about this taproom upon my relocation to the Indy/Carmel area.

The rejoicing ended once I ordered food and felt the atmosphere. The food is inconsistently average. The atmosphere is not welcoming; it is not the home I knew and loved at the Bloomington Upland. I voiced this once to the manager on duty, and he quickly shut down my opinion. "This is not Bloomington," he said. But, this is Upland. My experience did not match my expectation of the brand I had come to love. 

I am compelled to write this review now that I find out that samples are $1 each. If you want me to become a fan of your beer, you should at least be willing to invest in shelling out .5 oz of the stuff to develop loyalty. 

I am saddened to write this, as every so often I try giving this place a chance in the hopes that my views will change. Maybe next time I come, I'll enjoy it a bit more.

We stopped in here 3 different times.  My husband had a Bloody Mary and really liked it.  On another visit we had a Po Boy.  It was ok, not great, not bad.  The third time we stopped to get a drink and the bartender was one of rudest people I have run into.  There were several people at the bar but only one bartender.  We had been sitting waiting for a while when the bartender asked someone who had just walked in what they wanted.  I said something and the bartender came over, insulted me, and was extremely hostile.  I realize he was busy, and may not have known I was there first but that was no excuse for his behavior.  If you can't be civil then maybe you shouldn't be in a customer service job

I don't get it. I really don't. This is a review for drinks only. My husband and I went after a happy hour down on Passyunk to grab one last drink and finally check out ITV. Our server was a bit slow to get to our table and there seemed to be an air of resentment when we said we were only drinking. We both ordered the drink called 4 down, 7 letters and my husband really liked it. I guess I underestimated the Campari a bit (like a dumbass) but I was not a fan of mine. The service was painfully slow even though a table of 6 had been checked on several times while we were waiting to place our drink orders. From a practicality standpoint I get it- bigger table usually equals bigger tips esp. when they are getting food but how about not being so obvious about it? 

We waited for several minutes and I usually would rather die than return a well mixed drink to the bar but as it was my last drink of the night and I really couldn't get past the bitterness of the Campari, so I waited for more than a few minutes to kindly ask the server if she would mind switching out my drink (a bit of a pain in the ass I know) but she never checked on how we liked our drinks so my husband decided to go upto the bar and ask directly. They were all professional about it but you could tell there was a bit of irritation there. The server wasn't downright rude but there was a not friendly, resentful air to the whole thing. Some of the staff needs to work on their friendliness.  

Did I mention a lot of the menu seemed a bit overpriced even for Passyunk? My best advice is to save your money and just splurge on Laurel one night- its absolutely worth it and the service we received there was not the least bit pretentious or resentful.
Kids talking and being disruptive during the whole movie; staff refused to do anything about it.

The food here is delicious. However, I spent $12 for a sandwich and side and it took over 30 minutes to order and receive my food.  They had 4 kids working the entire place. While eating my food, I overheard several other customers complain about how they are always short staffed. One lady never even received her sandwich-she had to go up and ask multiple times about it, then finally ask for a refund. Good food, but service is definitely lacking

Tried this place after receiving a menu in the mail...very disappointed...ordered a brick oven pizza with grilled chicken and carmelized onions fresh tomatoes and cheese medallions...what I received was burnt, raw onions, a few tomatoes and a few cheese medalions...very disappointing.
We also tried their wings...run away...nasty frozen NOT fresh breaded/coated small wings that weren't even equally coated with sauce of choice.
Kicker was a small pizza and 10 wings was more than $25.00
Very disappointed...won't even try going back if they can't use the ingredients they tell you they will use

7:50pm on a Saturday. Terrible service. Been here 30mins so far and no food, our order was just taken. Took almost 20 mins to get a glass of wine. The wine selection is really small and I would not say good. The wine we picked it terrible. It seems like everyone in here is waiting for something. The food was good, however no one ever came to check on us. Like at all. We are still currently waiting for the waitress to come out. It is very awkward in here, considering my table and 1 other table of 2 are left. Watching everyone clean.

Dear Mary (the owner), I'm very disappointed.   I came here on Sunday (feb 11) at 5:11.  Friendly counter person.  I asked for a dark roast to find it was not ready.  To be accomodating, I said I'd try the last of the medium roast. I tried and found it to be not hot and didnt taste right.  BUT, that same previously friendly counter person replaced with a small instead of the 16oz I paid for.  He refused to replace because he did a pour over.   I'm disgusted.   I left the coffee behind.  I'll not be back.

We have eaten here before and had very good food and service, however , on our recent lunch experience we had poor food. The vegetable of the day was lima beans which were so salty we didn't finish eating them. The squash casserole was bland and tasteless. We paid extra to include a house salad on the veggie plate and it was basically greens, carrots, tomatoes, purple onion with dressing of choice.. no croutons, no cheese, no bacon ... overall poor lunch, but good service.

We will not return to this place. Ordered Fried Green Tomato Sliders and mushroom Swiss sliders!  Bread was cold and hard and most of the sandwich WAS bread!  Meat was flavorless....
Fried Mac n cheese was ok but the onion rings were greasy.  Bill was $39 for two people! Crazy for not good food.  Sorry, Burger Up, we won't be going back.

This place used to be great. Now it's a $10 cover to listen to a live band. Not to be rude, but the lead singer was/is dreadful. To go to the club side, you now need to pay an extra $5.. people don't have that money. I intend to never come again.
Can u say microwave and sushi from last week they found on the floor for reg price aka double the price then say half off lol

This is the dirtiest Saint Louis Bread / Panera I've visited. All the tables we attempted to sit on were dirty. They got the order wrong (which is becoming too common at several Panera's in the past couple of years)

We used to love Brixx Pizza especially the Korean meatballs and the pear martinis but we tried it tonight and it was I'm sorry to say horrible the martini did not have the pear in it and it tasted like a water down margarita and we noticed that our waitress had to make her own drinks instead of the bartender who was sitting there chatting it up with the customers the pizza was okay but the crust was sorta cardboardish the Korean meatballs were sort of bland they used to be very tasty in the sauce used to be very sweet and sticky very disappointing will probably try back again in this summer hopefully it'll be a lot better

What happened Westmont Diner? Made a visit for dinner recently and I'm sad to say that everything was off. Waitress coughed in her hands, food was lackluster, burger underdone and needed to be sent back. It wasn't even a busy night. I'm sorry to say that it was such a disappointing experience that we won't be back for some time. I hope things turn around as we have enjoyed it in the past.

I have eaten here multiple times and really enjoyed it but my last visit was my worst experience. We got seated at around 11 when it wasn't super busy and after our waitress took our order it took 50 min to get our food. We actually hadn't seen our waitress at all and had to ask a different waitress where our food was. People that were seated after us got their food before us. When my pancakes arrived they were extremely cold and when I told the waitress she took them to the kitchen then came back to say : "what do you want us to do with them like microwave them or remake them im not sure what they can do" I was honestly so confused because if you as an employee don't know what the kitchen can do then why and how are you working here?? Once my eggs Benedict came they were alright, the bread was extremely hard and it took me awhile to cut through it. My boyfriend had the chicken and waffles which were good. At the end when we asked for our check we waited another 20 minutes for her to come tell us to stand in line and tell her what table we are in order to get the check. Truly an awful experience. I honestly think it was all because of our awful waitress who if I ever come back I will request to not have her.

I have never in my life been so physically uncomfortable in a restaurant. That the owners of Zeppoli serve 5 star food (and it is) while you are expected to sit in a chair made for a kindergartener is beyond comprehension. I walked in, looked at those $5 wooden chairs with no cushion, no real backs and was so disappointed this is how I was supposed to "relax" and enjoy my meal. Then I sat, and the featherweight chair slid around the floor every time I breathed; also had to put my bag on the hard floor... That everything we ordered was wonderful just makes this all the more frustrating. Why on earth do they not immediately remedy this situation by purchasing ANY kind of decent chairs for this one tiny room??? It's inexcusable. They will never be a really great restaurant so long as they make ignorant, careless choices that directly detract from the dining experience. I'd sooner get my meal to go than make a reservation here again. Please invest in your business. This is all so avoidable.

So won't be coming back. Top coat was uneven on pedi so i have to fix that. I asked about manicure with dip powder bc I feel cuticle never looks super clean and she said don't worry cuticle will be cleaned up with drill when dip powder is done...well that's done and they are not. One of my nails is rough on the tip and I'll have to file that myself. I don't pay to have to go behind their work. For all the fancy nails they are doing the basic pedi/mani I got should've been no problem...very disappointing.

I go there every Sunday all day spent over 1000$ i got kicked out the club because one guy of security don't like me. I will find is name and updated this post. It was my girl friend birthday you guy lost over 800$ good job. This guy called police on me i have never had anything to do with police on my life. I will never go there again.

IF YOU ARE A FAMILY WITH FOOD ALLERGIES...STAY VERY FAR AWAY FROM HERE. I waited the long line to find out if they could accommodate a peanut allergy. I was told they would make them in a separate section in the back. After waiting another 15 minutes, I watched an employee look very frazzled as they realized they hadn't segregated my peanut free order. Another five minutes went by, and I was told they could only make cinnamon or vanilla icing for a nut allergy and that's it.  I have been to Sundaes in the heart of the summer where they would open a new tub of ice cream and wash equipment for my son. I asked for the manager who took another ten minutes to refund my money. When I expressed my disappointment that they wasted my time and seems to be insensitive to the group of children that were just disappointed by not being able to have their order (3 of the 4 had nut allergies). Nobody cared. I asked to reach out to the owner. The owner looked at me and said you got your money back and walked away. Not a great way to run a business. I watched the donuts come out in the half hour I waited and they were sloppy in the prep area and sloppy in the presentation boxes. In this day and age, I would think people would be more sensitive to food allergies and not want to alienate that demographic.

This hotel has charged me twice to stay in a hotel for you one night. I booked through Priceline and apparently that doesn't count for anything. The Manager named Regina was absolutely no help to me what so ever. Refused to refund me the money to stay in a moldy room for one night. This hotel is outdated and in need of a renovation and new manager. I will be telling everyone I know to never come here and spend their hard earned money to be taken advantage of. This hotel also makes a hold in the amount of your reservation on your card for a week long. They will not tell you about this either.

Love staying at Spring Hill Suites....but this one is poorly managed. Good location and price, however checkin was very slow with long line and only one person checking in. No housekeeping to speak of. They do make beds but you will have to get towels, wash cloths, toilet paper, etc off of the carts when you see one. First day after checkin, found note in room stating she would bring towels later. At midnight i called and asked when they would be bringing towels. Told that staff person had gone home for the day, and how many towels and wash cloths did I need. Housekeeping is non existant.  Access to towels for pool was was very inconvenient. Could not open door to pool area. Went to desk for assistance, he made me a new key, low and behold, that key did not work either when he tried to use it. Had to go outside and enter pool through outside entrance. They do have a good breakfast, which is why I am giving them 2 stars.

Sorry for late review went about 3 weeks ago.  Disappointed.  Ordered two meat platter.  Pulled pork & brisket.  Pulled pork Ok, brisket was just like the pulled pork .  Pulled, I was expecting slices of tender juicy brisket.  It was a pile of pulled meat. The sides,  slaw and potato salad have a lot o be desired.  The corn bread is like a piece of stale cake it was nothing but crumbs.  Sauce good stuff.
