We turned around a walked out. If the owners of Moxie's are reading this, if you are going to have a smokey bar, please make sure that there is no way the smoke can get into the restaurant.
Nice place, some poor employees. Feel bad for the way their customers are treated. Being in the business, would never want any customer to experience the nasty attitude of this bartender.

Don't order take out! The portions are Smaller but the price is same. Hibachi wasn't worth 25 dollars. If your gonna get this place eat in. The meat and sushi is good. Just wish they portion it right.
If you can't come to work with pride and energy and enthusiasm then don't work at a McDonald's where people are in a hurry to get somewhere else.....so disappointed in the behavior of humans!

The food is good the service is terrible i went there about 3 times with my cousins and the people workin there were on the phones or talking to the other employees i didn't know if i should go and pour myself a refill or ask the waitress that was working at the time for a refill she took forever to come and check up on us and i would understand if it was busy but me and my family were the only ones in the restaurant and i think i understand know why were the only ones in that place i thought i came in to dine in not to get up and refill my drink myself if i wanted to get up and refill my own drink i would have went to McDonald's is this place a fast food place or a dine in restaurant and truly believe McDonald's has better service. Only thing that's holding me back from going there again is the service it's sad to say

Average food with a really good location. I went for breakfast once and lunch another time. Breakfast was average, same with lunch, which was a choice because the first two places we picked were closed for lunch hours. For the lunch visit, we split a patty melt and a corned beef sandwich. The menu made it sound like the corned beef was a hot open faced sandwich, but it was nothing more than cold lunchmeat and dressing. Everything was bland and under seasoned. Wait staff hung out by the counter a lot to talk, but seemed friendly when they approached our table. Food wasn't 'bad', but the only reason I'd really go back is because of the location and if I was in a hurry, no other reason to really go back, and I live in the immediate area.

Terrible mixed drinks. Our table got four different drinks and no on like their drink. I got the desert highball and it smelled like the fruit mix was spoiled. On top of that it was just bland, totally watered down.

Terrible terrible terrible. Out of 6 meals we ordered to go, 5 had to be thrown away. We were missing half the components that were supposed to be part of the meal (no buns for our burgers, no fries that were supposed to come with it) items which were described as vegetarian came with bacon, it was just a major fail all the way around. The few components that we did try were completely flavorless. We will never go back or order from here again. Waste of time and money as I then had to go home make make dinner.

I was very excited to try this place. Went at 2:30 on Saturday. They are supposed to open at 2. After ordering, my friend and I were told that "nothing was prepped" and it would be 25 more minutes. We said we did not mind waiting. We waited an hour but nothing was ever "prepped", except Mac and cheese or charcuterie. We had the charcuterie and left. There was no attempt to make things right or explain. Very strange experience and poor/ no customer service. The waiter was nice though, and I felt sorry for him.

I've been doing DIP powder for years. Every time it lasts 3-6 weeks without chipping. I did my nails here for the second time and within a week I had two broken nails. I went back and they fixed it but within two days more nails were chipping off. The pedicures are nice with the stones but after spending almost $70 in everything and my nails looking this bad after only a week I will not be going back here again.

This was so disappointing. I love Chick fil A. My son even works at the Avon location, which is fabulous. This is not the same. I tried to order my usual, that I get several times a week in Avon, and they received to accommodate. I only wanted the bread from the mini rolls. Go to Avon, very close and such a wonderful place to eat.

Waiter brought me a plate with yellowish stream of food. I asked for a clean plate. He returned what appeared to be the same plate with a greasy streak. It appears as though the places was wiped. My husband then asked for another plate. He brought another plate and said it was handwashed 3 times. I didn't trust the waiter after the second plate.

Easy to get ahold of and things taken care of as a potential tenant... impossible to get things taken care of once papers are signed and they get their money. Very disappointing.

Update. Service just keeps getting worse. Unbelievable.

I'm a partner so I know the standards and I'm usually pretty understanding since I know what it's like. But the minute I walked into the store the girl on bar had an attitude with another customer. The store wasn't busy and I was the only one waiting, the Barista at the register didn't acknowledge me. I probably waited a good couple minutes before being greeted. The guy didn't give me my discount after I told him I was a partner.... luckily I mobile ordered my other drinks. Even then I didn't even drink my caramel macchiato because it was gross.
I just don't get it. Waiting an hour in line for mediocre pancakes, eggs that are under seasoned, and bleh coffee? I get it's a Nashville institution, but our city has better to offer these days.

1) carpet is sticky 2) didn't give us enough towels 3) phone doesn't work to call down to front desk 4) we asked them to clean our room five times, never happened 5) asked for sheets and blankets for the pull-out bed at least eight times, never happened. Don't waste your money here.

Worst concert experience I've had. Buyers, beware. They're only interested in your money NOT your experience. My husband spent A LOT of money on an Imagine Dragons VIP package and it left much to be desired. The "gift bag" was filled with a small, cheap crumpled poster, plastic sunglasses, a pop socket, and a phone charger fit for a circa 2015 android. The "crowd free shopping" consisted of about 200 people crammed in a small area with general admission goers, and the "hassle free entry" took 45 minute. So, all in all I sit here really pissed about the experience, feeling bad for my husband who wanted to surprise, and the concert hasn't even started yet. Bravo CID. Thank you for seriously putting a damper on my night.

What has happened to Target?  I shop weekends and my experience starts with walking into a hot store. Then I have to weasel my way around all the employees stocking shelves with huge flatbeds that block the aisles. I can't ever get everything on my list as there are always out of stocks and heaven forbid I ask a stocker for help! I then end pulling up to a long line at checkout, max ever 2 checkers, I am then asked to self-check. I am guessing limiting checkers is a ploy to force this..my answer is always no and usually everyone around me! With all the online competition I would think making the in store experience would be high in the list of priorities!

Went here for the great food I had experienced before. 
After HORRIBLE service, flagging down the waitresses, & being told they were out of all drinks except alcohol & water, my friends and I left leaving cash at the table to cover our tabs but did not tip. The staff proceeded to call my boyfriend a nigger & follow my friend outside threatening to call the cops.  I was disappointed in the wait staff but their intolerance & bigotry will definitely prevent me from ever going back.

Never again!!! 
This ceviche was not fresh. And the corn nut were stale. Very gross.not to mention it took 25 minutes to get our check so we could leave. The other waitress could not even find out waitress.

The pizza had no taste and the wings that I ordered didn't even come buffalo, they came plain which I know for a fact I asked for mild wings... even the chicken was flavorless. Won't be ordering again.
Restaurant is very clean who was delicious have steak and veggies with sweet tea very fast and friendly service

I hate to say it, but other reviews were right. Burgers were decent, onion rings inedible due to grease, my kid's fries needed to be pressed with napkins, and the service was terrible. Service was... terrible. Waited over an hour with a 3 year old for our burgers. I love their wings, but don't think I'll eat in there again. We actually tipped another server that took care of us. I think "Ryan" was his name. Place was not busy when we got there.  Damn it! It's so close with such a good beer selection! Sorry, "Pub"... you're almost there, but need some efficiencies put in place or a talent review.

This is the worst hotel I've ever been too. You wake up to big booms coming from the hall ways and house keeping knocking at your door at 8am. We got a room and once we walked into it, it smelt like someone else's body odor. The furniture here is from the 80s and there is some nasty crap on the streets. I do not ever recommend going to this crappy hotel again.

OMG....worst hoagie I've ever eaten. Stale roll overloaded with sesame seeds. I ordered the Italian. All I could taste was salami and lettuce! If you want an excellent hoagie, go down the street to Lillian's.
Terrible selection, even worse quality. Big mistake. Skip this place. Not worth the price!

Ordered the Turkish hummus and corn salad as appetizers. Corn salad was great. The hummus was the saltiest item I've ever ordered from a restaurant. But we then ordered the meatballs. It was like a salt competition with the hummus. Barely edible. Nice general vibe and the feel of a nice restaurant, but the food doesn't back up the experience. One and done.

Ghetto af. All these chicks that don't even work there came in with McDonald's and headed to the back. Another chick and her kids came in and didn't even have to check in but got to go to the sinks. Stylists standing around on the phone while people wait. Horrible customer service and rude employees. Yelling across the salon and gossip. Please don't go. It's not what it used to be.

Nice Yukon XL, but extremely dishonest billing. I returned the SUV and received a final, time-stamped receipt for a 3 day rental (see attached image). I also received an email with an attached receipt for the same amount. However, on my credit card they charged me an extra $113.32 for an extra day without my approval and AFTER I returned a car. It turns out they changed the return time after they gave me this receipt. I called the next day and the manager wouldn't take my call. Fortunately I was refunded by disputing the charge with my credit card company.

Rude, inattentive, uneducated and they always make you feel that you are bothering them. I have started using mobile order because it's one less idiot to deal within the chain. When they start making $15 an hour we will be ordering from kiosks and maybe dealing with one person.

They don't even deserve a star worse service ever very disorganized place my mom use to work at little caesars and they always have pizzas on stock but this place always either runs out or they don't have it ready very disappointed with my visit and it's always packed

This is the ugly stepsister of the three Marriott properties in the Reno Area. The rooms feel worn out and in need of an update. I am a Marriott Gold member and honestly surprised by the prices that Marriott charges. If they charge those price shouldn't their customers expect more? 

There are plenty of places to eat nearby but remember you are not close to downtown.

The person at the front desk told me that they would be updating the hotel soon. 

I might check back in 2019 but in the meantime will choose somewhere else to stay.

Beware !! Check your lug nuts before leaving they forgot my front passenger lug nuts they never tighten them which after 3 days of tire wobbling my hub bearings in the passenger front tire started making real bad sound which they said I need it replaced which they claim the loose nuts would not cause it to go , so it cost me $300 
  Plus alignments are not done there they drive your vehicle elsewhere to have it done and don't give any print outs on your alignment , just found out another customer tire fell off because they forgot to put lug nuts on his front tire

And don't bother to complain to corporate-----you receive a standard
"thank you for your feedback" letter and NOTHING improves
at this location!

Came in for salmon, Mac and sweets, which was "okay". The salmon was burnt/hard and way too oily. The Mac was oily as well. The yams were actually good. The buttered roll was hard and cold. Customer service is absolutely horrible at this establishment. The cashier was very rude and unprofessional. She was on her phone and conversing with staff in the back without acknowledging the people waiting in line. Also, the food took every bit of a half hour to cook. Will not be returning.
Food was prompt and is what it is - nothing unexpected there. WiFi is worthless. I'd add a star if they had a changing table in the Men's room.

Although our server was nice, this was some of the worst service I have ever had at a restaurant.  Waited 20 minutes for water, then 40 minutes for a to go order.  Food was okay, not worth the hassle.  Still like their beer.

Interesting I had no issues getting my prescription filled timely at Walmart... I move it here and the won't let me fill it until 3 weeks after it runs out. Taking my business back to Walmart for prescriptions.
Hmmm, wonder why they (management) will not address this post and they do the other negative posts . . .

I had lamb biryani and it was not a biryani. In stead it was fried rice with some lamb chunks. I could see that the rice was Jasmine or even lower quality rice unlike in other Indian restaurants where they use quality basmati rice. Biryani did not have any biryani masala or smell. 
The rice was fried with cumin seeds. It was pre cooked like long time ago and they microwave in front of me instead of heating up in the cooking pan. The lamb pieces were so dry and over microwaved multiple times. Overall I was given some random foods. Certainly not biryani.

Went back a second time just because It's in a great location and I really wanted to like this place. My noodle was under cooked and the pork had way too much fat. I am done with this place. Kin and Nomiya are my places for ramen.

We heard they had the best tacos in town. They were very mediocre. Ordered refried beans and rice. The beans were just okay and the rice was cold and hard. They only brought out one meal (there were 2 of us) and did bring our other meal out fairly quickly but still forgot an item we had ordered. Very disappointed.

Worst Wingstop ever! DIRTY, small, and slow service. The biggest issue is how DIRTY this restaurant is! There where tables with food, sauce and bones left on them. It's a small restaurant so they have limited seating and at least 3 tables were covered in trash. There was no trash can anywhere available for customers dispose of the food/trash and staff never came out to clear and clean the tables. The restaurant was filled with flies and nats . I'm sure the dirty conditions added to the amount of flying pests. They have windows into the kitchen...and you could clearly see them use sauce bowls and the put them back on the shelves dirty with sauce dripping down the sides...attracting flies. Floors were dirty. Overall a very poor experience. I will never go back and urge everyone avoid this location of Wingstop.

Visited The Mustard Seed on a Sunday evening and went in with high expectations given all the great reviews. I'm certainly not an expert on southern food, but I definitely know good food from bad food and southern food aside, this place just didn't meet my expectations or standards. I'm baffled as to how they have received such good reviews. 

Things started off poorly when we were seated without menus, silverware, or waters. My friend and I tried to order a glass of wine. They were out of every wine by the glass (except white zinfandel and I'm not really sure who actually drinks that anymore), so we were forced to order a bottle of white wine. The wine bottle shows up to our table and is warm. The waiter apologizes for the warm wine, but proceeds to tell us that all the cold bottles are already open. We're confused, because they previously told us we had to order the entire bottle and couldn't buy the wine by the glass. So which is it? 

Our food arrives and everything but the fried catfish is cold. Like it just came out of the refrigerator cold. The fish was over battered and my friend's fish batter had a piece of okra in it. Huh? The corn bread was so dry and stale. And then to top it off, mid-dinner the staff starts mopping the floors and cleaning the restaurant with pungent smelling chemicals, which I could  taste in my mouth as I inhaled the toxins while eating.

It was a huge disappointed overall and a total waste of a dinner out. Sorry folks, but this place needs a lot of improvement.

The first time I went to pita jungle was in Phoenix. They had an amazing jalapeño cilantro hummus. It had lots of spice. The next time we went to the one in northwest Tucson. The jalapeño cilantro hummus was bland. We got a falafel and a salad. Surprisingly none of it had any flavoring. The salad tasted like lettuce with oil.

We stopped here for an impromptu lunch.  Pulled pork was tasty And both bbq sauces, sweet and spicy were delicious.  I actually mixed them together.  Our sandwich came with  a small bag of chips and nothing else.....not even a pickle....we ordered. Side of drilled macaroni salad Nd Cole slaw.  They came in a very Small styrofoam cup which was maybe half full And they charged $2.95 for each!  I had water and spouse had one beer.  Our bill was $38.00.  Quite pricey for what we got.  Place could use some cleaning and a little painting would help.  Won't be going back or recommending to anyone.
Sitting in the downstairs bar and they refuse to close the door. It's freezing out and 60 degrees in the restaurant. They don't care people are walking out because it's cold

$50 for an incredibly average meal and two beers. Actually, it wasn't good enough to be average. I got the 16 ounce ribeye with a baked potato and applesauce. 

The steak was thin and fairly bland. I got it smothered with onions, sautéed mushrooms and cheese. I assumed the cheese would be crumbled, like blue cheese is in most steak places, but it wasn't. It was basically thick liquid cheese poured over the steak. I would not recommend the cheese on the steak. Maybe I didn't pay close enough attention to the description of the toppings in the menu? The applesauce was out of a jar. The potato was what you'd expect. 

I sat at the bar. The girls working the bar were very friendly, but very busy (and very, very loud). They should have more help on a Friday night because I had to wait several minutes for my second beer and then again for my check. The manager was also behind the bar but she didn't seem to be motivated to do any actual work. 

In future, I will cook my own steak (bought from Publix for about $15) and drink my own beer (6 for about $10) and spend half as much. 

I will not be going back.

I really like Korean BBQ. When I heard this place was opening, I was very excited to try this place. When I finally tried it, I was very disappointed for a few reason.

1. This spot is probably one of the most expensive Korean BBQ places around town.

2. The side dishes were horrible. The kimchi was also not good. 

3. The meets had some flavor, but it feels like they don't marinate 

The reason I couldn't give this place 1 star is because of their service. They were very informative.
I was attracted by the reviews which were enticing. The service was deficient by delivering the order by piecemeal and lukewarm food. Wrong choice.
The food was ok nothing that special.  The coffee did not taste good.  Even with a lot of creamer.  Everything was way over priced.  $21 for a 3 egg scrambler and a cup of coffee?

Bread great! Steak was not cooked to order at all, but it was comped after we said something. Cioppino was in a dee red paprika like sauce.  It was ok.  Mahi was good.  Kids grilled chicken was terrible, overcooked and dry. Kids popcorn shrimp were good.  I'd skip it for the price and find elsewhere. The giant fish tank you can view from the outside hallway and the gift shop is worth a view too.

First of all, this fingerprint service is actually embedded within an insurance agency.  I understand that the fingerprinting business is a side gig, and that it has unexpectedly caused this agency frustration and been detrimental to their ability to conduct business.  However, this is a terrible place to get fingerprinting done.  The employees are rude and treat us as a nuisance, even commenting that our fingerprinting is interfering with their insurance business.  All of us waiting were professionals in the field of psychology, education, and even coaching, and did not expect to be treated so rudely.  In fact, the Identogo website lists this location as a service provider but does not give any indication that it is located inside of another business.  The office environment itself was dark and dirty, and the employees rude and discourteous to each other and the fingerprinting customers.  They do not greet you, and have posted the sign below indicating that walk-ins will only be serviced in the afternoon.  This differs from the Identogo website information, which clearly lists 9:00 am - 11:00 am as walk in hours.  Bottom line - this agency took a contract to provide fingerprint services, now is wishing they did not have this hassle, and will take it out on you if you go there.
Food is good. But service is one of the worse I've ever had. I highly doubt we will be back again.

Absolute Worst Hotel I've ever come across! Booked a room 3-4 months in advance for a convention and trade show I was attending. And arrived to the hotel to have the staff tell me and everyone else in line that their hotel is "first come first serve" and that our reservations apparently don't mean anything. They had given our room away, and gave us vouchers to stay at a hotel 20 minutes away! Front desk staff had a shitty attitude,  and the manager didn't seem to care much that they overbooked the hotel and had to send everyone away! Decided to give their vouchers back and stay at a Hilton, rather than give them anymore business! DO NOT STAY HERE!!!!!!!

No alcohol...wtf?  I wanted a draft beer and the server said they don't have draft beer.  I then said no problem, I will just have a vodka tonic...."we don't have alcohol either"...lol.  So I just had an iced tea which was fine.  The food, however, was terrible.  The restaurant looks like it hasn't been updated in 50 years and was just a dump inside.  Being from New Jersey and being a chef I have had great Italian food in NY, NJ, and many other states. This was very poor quality Italian...the red sauce had no flavor and tasted like they just opened a can of sauce.  The cheese was a cheap mozzarella also with no flavor.  The menu was very limited and it was hard to order anything because everything sounded so basic.  I had the chicken parm,  the serving size was small, it was overpriced, it didn't come with any pasta under it or on the side...just chicken on plate.  Very poor presentation as well.  I had a side salad with the meal and McDonald's makes a better salad than his place.  If you want good Italian food...don't go here:

The restaurant had a nice atmosphere upon entering. The fish tank was really cool. The wine list was nice. Our food was cold on the first order, we sent it back. It was warm when they returned but it wasn't that good. Overall it was okay at best.  Wouldn't go back.

Always mass confusion when picking up take out. They need to hire expeditor...ordered shrimp Alfredo pizza. Had so much sauce it pooled in center and never cooked. Unable to pick up a slice as it ran off entire pizza. Threw it in trash. Never again. I do have to say, they offered to make a new one, but as I live far away, it was not possible. Always a delimma......wont see me again

This place is a Getto playground. Rude service, filthy tables , sauce bottles are sticky and disgusting. Grab some of them rude ass employees and put a wet soapy rag in their hand . Biscuits were hard as a rock and burnt. No honey for the biscuits ? Chicken was good but had no flavor. Popeyes at least has spice and is half the price . We had a 2 piece and a 3 piece strip and 1 dessert, came out to $30 bucks , that's crazy. I guess you need to pay for the armed guards protecting the bathrooms somehow

Maybe the pizza is good?  Had delivery of classic lasagna, where's the meat? Marsala was the second dish and never saw anything so small! Ordered the Italian wedding soup. NOT ANY meat in two bowls. The meals arrived COLD after a 45 minute eta and it actually arrived eighty minutes after ordering. This is the first time I've ever given a bad review but feel like $35 including tip was extremely high for this food. Will never eat this food again and will definitely not recommend it. Hope I don't get sick tonight!! If there was a zero rating, that's what it would receive. Yuck.

Pics looks nice online, do be fooled! The bathroom floor clearly had not been mopped or even swept in a long time. Long hairs everywhere and the dust/dirt was everywhere. I had to cover the entire floor with towels. The a/c is good but where the beds are it literally can only blow right down on your face/head.
$6.42 for a 24 oz iced vanilla latte seriously highway robbery cheaper at Kahwa caffeine buddybrew and Starbucks won't be back unfortunately until I become a millionaire

I read a number of bad reviews before I went to Momo, but decided to try it anyway because we were in the area. First off, the place was empty but I had to keep looking for my server. Every time I ordered, she'd come back ten minutes later saying they were out of whatever I ordered. When I finally decided on something they weren't out of, my entree showed up. This place says they serve ramen, but this isn't ramen. It's a bowl full of chili oil and onion water. I was pretty disappointed.
Good beer selection usually but unfortunately they serve some of the more desirable beers in ridiculous goblets and don't switch when you request a pint. Also service is pretty poor. Sad.

Wed 6 pm run in to get a to go order and drink. Sit at half filled bar. 615 pm leave with neither. Watched bartender not move from the register except to look at her texts serve somebody else and answer a phone order. 15 mins I walked out told the hostess great customer service..no reply...went across the street full bar busy had a drink and asked for my order 2 mins. Have a business on Manchester take clientele out weekly and Joey bs obviously doesn't need my business. Great customer servicer

My god waiting for the kitchen is one thing waiting on slow service is another. Tonight was rare form of a totally inept waiter who literally seemed like they couldn't care less. Gave the typical lip service such as thanks for coming, but seriously this guy will starve if he plans to earn anything from tips. Sadly there's no way to get that message though to management except if they read these reviews. Enjoyed the menu items but that's about it.

Terrible food great location (Hyde Park)
Italian Restaurant ?the bread is Burger mini rolls???
Kids' chicken fingers:Almost black(Fried in very old oil)
Calamari:Almost Black 
My daughter (8 years old) suggested me not to go there anymore which I agree.

I really wasn't impressed... We missed the breakfast by minutes. So we ordered po boy shrimp and po boy oyster, to my surprise I ended up with pop corn shrimp on a big bun. Very disappointed! My drink was suppose to be a concoction like a spike lemonade and man was it so watered down I thought a was drinking plain water... the upside was our waitress named Adrianne was just the best. She is the only reason I gave  this restaurant got two stars.. Come on new Orleans and redeem yourself... this restaurant is far below average, just my opinion

Well, if u just can't get enough of that rude NY attitude that the rest of us Americans love so much, then this is the place for you!  Service was beyond awful. We were one of 3 tables in the place, and the tall female server was short with everyone, had a bad attitude when a few members of our party were being friendly, and just seemed miserable. I'll spare the details, but we all agreed we'd never be back again. One of the 6 of us owns 6 restaurants, and he was saying it's just shocking how many bad restaurants - like this one - come and go in his business. The location is the only Hail Mary for this place he was saying, as the one time tourist business is their only hope, since the pizza was sub par also, and none of us will be back. A couple with a young child actually got up and left after an initial interaction with our same rude waitress. Not sure what was said, but that's just award level bad business practice. Summary: Not good pizza, Rude Service, and overpriced. I never thought I'd ever recommend Hooters in my life, but it's next door, and any place that serves food and drinks would be a better experience than this place. Trust me. EDIT: I had to come back and point out to look at the 36 yelp reviews that are not recommended (for some reason - or owner antics?) THEY ARE ALL 1 STAR about "unbelievably rude service" and bad pizza. Check them out and avoid this place. Kicking a mother and her children out while her husband picks up food. As a kind business owner in Tampa, who loves this city and the people, go back to NY with your garbage pizza and rudeness. At least get a clue Precinct. My Lord.

Our server, Brittney, has zero respect for patriots. I told her that the way she talked about customers was unacceptable and rude. She could only say OK. Her coworkers fed into it and discussed others within our ear shot. We will not be back to this location.

Very very poor communication, posts on social media of my dog clearly not happy and harness on wrong, set off security system and did not notify me--I found out from the alarm company first, brought in new walker without telling me, didn't tell me my dog was peeing on the floor and sofa out of fear when she was greeted by them--had to find out from roommates (thank god for them or I would never even know of these issues). I work in a stressful ICU and want to be sure my dog is safe and happy, but these walkers only added more stress.
I think this place is going out of business, they didn't have any soda, ranch, or curly fries when I went in. Guess they're having a close out sale?

We were told a 45 minute wait, after 40 minutes we asked for the status and were told we had an additional 21 minute wait. The girl at the front desk had an attitude. They had open tables the whole time we were waiting, didn't end up staying and just left. The food that was walked past us looked good, shame we couldn't have any.

Yikes, man. This place does not live up to the hype at all. They have rude hostesses, food is "meh" and they only have one decent bartender. Seems to be a major issue with finding good bartenders in this area because Bru burger down the street has lousy bartenders too. The location is nice if you live in the building, but otherwise, parking is terrible and if you  park across the street your odds of getting run down by a speeding car while crossing are probably 1 in 3.

El Charro Cafe was recommended to us by the concierge at the JW Marriott. We, unfortunately, had a poor experience. Of our four dinners, only one person really enjoyed their meal. The rest found the food really non-descript. The chimichangas were limp. And the dinner was not super expensive, but not cheap either.

Our waitress was stressed out and cranky.  She seemed much more interested in pushing add-ons than serving. Even though it was a weekday night, our dinner took a very long time to arrive.

In the end, it was a $100 family dinner that was not worth the trip or expense.

This Qdoba is probably the worst place I have ever been to. I placed an online order and when I showed up to pick it up, no one had even started on my order. After they realized I was there, they could have cared less. It still took 15 minuets to get the order filled. There wasn't even anyone else waiting. And then I saw one of the employees cleaning the counter by brushing all the crumbs and spills onto the floor. The whole restaurant was filthy. If I hadn't paid, I would have left. You couldn't pay me to return to this location. One star is way too much!

I usually like this place. It's where I go to get my haircut. Today they gave away my spot three times. I checked in online like they asked me to do the last time I was in. They gave away my place before the 30-minute window that I had to get in. It only took me 20 minutes to get there. When I voiced my concern to the girl, she told me that I would be next only for the next Barber to come out and call the other person. I was in a rush I tried using their system and it's so disorganized with no communication in a one-room building. How do you even manage that? You can't turn over your shoulder and say oh this was an issue by the way. I'm over this location. All I needed was a quick haircut. I guess it's going uncut another day and I will find a new Barber.

Not worth the wait... I've worked in several restaurants in touristy areas and believe me folks, it's hard to screw up breakfast in a place like this. They have a great view of the water.  It's a cozy "feels local" kind of place.  All they need to do is smile, be courteous, provide attentive service, and halfway decent breakfast food and it's a 5 star place. Unfortunately, our experience was lacking in all of the above.  I walked in to record my name, party and acceptable dining location. Done. Waited 20-25 minutes. No big deal. Was seated at the "counter" despite requesting to be seated at a table...wait, seriously? no backs on the stools, no counter service to speak of. We were essentially sitting at the server bus station surrounded by bins of creamers,butter, cartons of juice, extra ramikens.... After another 10 minutes, a server reluctantly asked us for our order... as we were listening to the wait staff be "cut" since there were open tables - why are we stuck here?  Another 15 minutes and our "food" arrived. Powdered eggs, store-bought bread, canned OJ, undercooked eggs, cold food, congealed cheese, plastic plates, plastic condiments... it was only edible to my 9 year old son.  There is a Dunkin Donuts in the same strip mall. Grab an egg and cheese bagel and pull up a chair along the water - trust me, it will be a better experience.  Hope the food and service was just a one-off today... if not, your regulars must not have any taste buds or self respect left... good luck.   I have pictures to back this up - just haven't figured out how to add to this post!!

The sandwiches are minuscule and have a ton of bread compared to sandwich ingredients! I had a chicken, zucchini (who puts zucchini on a sandwich anyhow). Anyhow, I ordered ir and this was a major disappointment. There was probably a couple tablespoons of chicken on 1/2 of what I ate. My husband had procuitto and hi was pretty much the same. 
  So I'd recommend ordering cafe and croissants 
here.

My wife and I stopped by the past Sunday (Memorial Day Weekend). When my wife asked the server as to a possible available table? (larger young woman with black hair) she launched into a stern warning that we "better not sit at any table that hasn't been cleaned!" Taken back by this attitude by the server we complained to the bartender ( blond hair) about the server's behavior and she first placated us but then began to gossip about us to another woman helping her at the bar. We left without finishing our drinks. Oh, and the anemic jazz band was inaudible!

Small place tucked away on lower state.  I really like the order first then sit down aspect.  We had the French toast and the Chorizo Hash Special.  You can't really go wrong with French toast.  The chorizo hash was disappointing and not an "off the chart" breakfast choice.  The coffee was just ok.  I probably need to try another menu item before abandoning this option.

Ordered delivery, post writing tip amount and signing - driver states "management says mushrooms came out weird.  Gave you more.  Tried to call."  They tried to call once.  The mushrooms were burnt and clearly were defrosted at one point or something, just a big mush of nothing.  When we called back to complain they actually charged us for them they lectured us about not answering out phone and said everyone likes their deformed burnt mushrooms.... not me though!  I've probably had delivery from them over 100 times and in the last year it's gone downhill.  Oh and its hard to tell if they gave more or not as it was just one big gross mass of dough with some over cooked mushrooms floating in there somewhere.

DO NOT GO TO THIS PLACE. they are disgusting! and i'm not meaning the food. the food is decent, but if you want to feel unwelcome and uncomfortable then this is the place for you. the whole entire place is TERRIBLY unprofessional. i'm 16, and even i am just appalled. they are all thugs. they are running the place into the ground. i watched them take a woman's register to put orders in, and put PORN IN. THEY HAD PORN ON THE POS SYSTEM, WITH KIDS AROUND TO SEE. i am completely amazed at how horrible this place is. for this bad of service, do not go here. even though the food isn't exceptionally terrible, it's still nothing you should spend money on. completely insane. i am begging you guys. DO NOT BRING YOUR KIDS HERE. let alone yourself!

Website was wrong all week, came to see the same movie twice, was wrong both times. Had to break my 4yr old's heart TWICE trying to see Isle of Dogs. Customer service unwilling to do anything to make it right. 
Also, theatre covered in trash.

Stopped in on a Sunday afternoon because I was craving oysters.

This visit was a train wreck from start to finish.

They bring the oysters out and instead of sitting on crushed ice, the oysters themselves have regular drink ice poured on top of them.  I can't make this up.  

Then the waitress proceeds to tell us that they're out of:

Bottled Water
Lemons
Horseradish 

The oysters just weren't that good. It fact, I had to spit one out because it tasted bad.

We were two seconds done from eating and were still finishing our beers and two workers came out and started picking everything up off of our table. Not just plates, but everything...napkins, ketchup, paper towels, etc. like they were closing.  

All of the good reviews are from tourists.  Locals do not eat here.

It was just a very odd experience.  I'll never return.

We were staying at a hotel not far from here, so with the four star rating you figure it's above average. HUGE disappointment. Looking for some good fish so we both order grilled fish. Although the fish was pretty much spot on, the sides were Very Poor. Cajun seasoned corn on the cob seemed as though it was sitting in a luke warm pan of water for a while. No freshness what so ever. Off the plate it was room temperature and had no flavor. The Cajun fried potatoes (too many), were also of poor quality. As though they had been sitting for a good while under a weak heat lamp. Off the plate, again had cooled to almost room temperature. Now these folks are pricing these plates above twenty dollars, and the quality just isn't there. All three of these items could have been cooked at the same time. I'll pay the money, but I want the quality it commands. You can't be charging restaurant prices inside a bar. Nice wait staff. Confined restroom. This place is a prime candidate for one of those shows where Robert Irvine comes in and does a menu and interior overhaul. No. I will not be back.

My family has been shopping at Kane's since I was a kid. This has been the most unorganized and unprofessional experience I have ever had. I paid IN FULL for my furniture  that was suppose to be delivered 3 weeks ago and then changed to the 28th and now on the 27th one person said they were coming tomorrow and would call today to confirm between 4-5 and now it's 8:30 and no call. Very disappointing. I should of went to American Signature Furniture.

One of the first times visiting Santa Barbara pier, I walked over to this restaurant, The sign was outside the doors open, when I went in and asked where to order, the guy said we are closed miss, to which I said I'm sorry and left. As I was walking out this guy started laughing and saying can you believe that lady? She thought we were open and laughed. So I tried to get back in and the door was locked so I told the guy from the open window that I heard what he said and i thought it was rude! His reply was I couldn't believe you thought we were open, the chairs were on the table and the door was locked. I replied by saying that I walked right in and I had never been here before, there were customers eating also. Anyway he follows me out and says what is your problem. He never apologized or anything. I will never try to eat here again and let everyone know how rude they are!! There are many nice places to eat on the pier! So whatever you do don't eat there!!!

Visited this place while taking a vacation. The theme was right and it made me expect something that tasted like pizza from the greater tri state, and this just didn't do it for me. Garlic knots were good but the pizza was just off... far off... if you're expecting pizza like that it ny or nj don't bother. If you're not then I'm sure it's not bad, however next time I'll just keep walking.

Let's see I had ham egg & cheese croissant. Small for 6 bucks 
Raspberry tart with the same croissant 3 bucks 
Asked if they had regular whole milk  received hot milk out of espresso machine 2.50   Wanted cold milk   Only other milk was nesquick so I asked how much the cashiers says 6 bucks lmao   I said no way. Ask if the chef was the owner she says yes   Owner tells me 3 bucks...I say again no way just give me my money back. I have 30 years in restaurants such as Emerils Delmonico & commanders palace as a cook    This place has been open for a month and will probably be closing sooner rather than later. Prices way out of control for a fast food McDonald's sized breakfast sandwich. I will not be going back and told the cashier to look for another job because they won't be open long in river town   Oh I stopped at a gas station for milk same size same milk 2.17 wow

Found what we needed. Had a larger selection than the home depot down the street.  The reason for the two stars was an employee talking on her cell phone yelled at us for ignoring her. She asked "do you need help with anything?" We all assumed she was talking to the person on her phone. When we did respond to say no she proceeded to bad talk us to the person on the phone as "rude customers."  Seemed very unprofessional. Never had this sort of experience at a Lowes or Home Depot.

We used to go to Landry's in the French Quarters. It was one of our go to places during Jazz Fest. We noticed that it has re-opened on the north east side of the Jax Brewery Building. It looked good because it had an upstairs and an outside seating that overlooked the Mississippi River. That was the pros. Now the cons. When the hostess seated us she cleared the table but never came back to wipe it. There were no place settings and no dishes. Even though they were not busy everything took forever. When the crab bisque came out it was lukewarm as was the char broiled oysters. The oysters were seasoned with  way to much salt. We ordered bruschetta six oysters 2 cups of bisque and a beer. The bill was $77. Ouch. Too many great restaurants with great service and great food for far less money. Will not be back.

I honestly walked 20 minutes just to get to this place and was excited to give it a try...  First I was set down at the only place they had available, the balcony.. it was mid day and super sunny and it took them 20 minute to just come say hey and ask if I'd like to drink... after they moved me in I ordered, the hash were super yummy and my waitress was sweet, Id give them that. I guess if you are willing to wait 60 min in line and than another 60 min inside just to eat an egg sandwich than this is the place for you. Maybe I just had a bad experience.

We love Pita Jungle typically, but this was the worst experience we have had. Food was way over salted, ran out of three of our four choices and could not seem to handle a large party along with normal business. Really disappointing from one of my favorite restaurants.

Horrible service!  Restaurant was recommended so we decided to check it out.  First time in Nashville so we wanted to see what the downtown experience was, and we were greatly disappointed; mostly due to our unfortunate experience at tavern.  We waited for 20 minutes without any acknowledgement from our waiter.  When we finally saw him in our area he greeted a table who had just arrived, skipped our table and went on to another. We ended up leaving the establishment.  I repeat...horrible service!!!! I guess I can take that back, it wasn't horrible, there WAS NO SERVICE!

My wife and I have visited twice, and another time with friends. While we like the food and beer choices, the service is inexcusably very slow. We visited on a Saturday afternoon around 5:00 and the place was only 1/3 full. Took a while for our server to greet us, arrived just when we were about to get up and leave. Ordered a beer for each of us and waited at least 10 minutes before I finally got up to ask the bartender about our drinks (after watching him not making any drinks for several minutes and serving a few others who just arrived at the bar). I could barely get the words out before he says they'll be right up. I sit back down, and he still doesn't pour them. We were about to leave again when another bartender made eye contact and she poured the drinks and brought them to us. While our waitress was friendly, she should have been checking on our drinks. Same slow experience with the other two visits, this time we are certain we will not be back.

It's unacceptable to wait 2h30 to have a table, the welcome waitress said 45min at the beginning and then nothing, everything is closed after 10pm so we had to wait... the worst place to end our vacations in New Orleans !

A couple of months ago my coworker and I checked out the menu before arriving so that we could immediately order when we arrived, as we only have a one hour lunch. The place is only about 5 minutes from our job. We were Immediately seated.  I ordered seafood tacos and she ordered a cheeseburger. After waiting for 50 minutes the food still had not arrived at our table we decided to just cancel the order and head back to work and get chips and soda from the vending machine. We were told the food was now finished cooking, so we decided to just take it to go. Well you know fish tacos and fries and not the same when reheated. We were not given an explanation as to why the food took so long nor did they offer any type of future discount or compensation. I'm writing this now because my coworker thinks we should give the place another try which I agreed to. So I shall be back with another review later this week. Wish us luck

Do not get Comcast if you live in nashville/brentwood  area. I have been having intermittent outages for weeks. The automated customer care bot simply resets the signal and doesn't let you talk to a real person. If you do get through to a real person, they tell you there is an outage and they can't do anything about it. This is not even the worst part,when I told them that I want to end my service and break my 1yr contract, I was told that I would be charged an early termination fee. I asked the agent ' so let me get this straight, it doesn't matter whether or not Comcast gives me internet service, I still have to pay no matter what?' To which she says ' a contract is a contract'. I hung up the phone. They wouldn't even send a tech to take a look because the system doesn't let them during an outage. Worst company ever!

Do not eat here.

I ordered online and got three sushi rolls. After an hour of waiting we called to check on the order. They said they were behind and it would be there soon. We waited an additional twenty minutes and when it arrived I was starving and started eating very quickly. Then I found a bone in it. Then another. Then another. On the third bone I stopped eating it and realized it was turning my stomach. We called and complained and in their defence they sent someone out to give us a refund, so at least I got food poisoning for free.

I've came here a few times and the last 2 times my order have been incorrect. I checked the receipt and the correct order was listed. I suggest to better train your staff and make sure they are paying attention to detail if not you will continue to lose customers. This is consistent trend.

Came for dinner tonight. We were quickly seated and the chips and salsa are very good. We ordered and I feel the food came promptly. I had a chimichanga with carnitas, my husband had the steak burrito, and my mom had the nachos. All the food was at best a 5/10. It wasn't bad, but just nothing to write home about. The meat in each item had very little flavor. The rice was bland and the beans were basic. The service was pleasant but slow. I can't say I'd make the trip to come again.

we have been at this chilis many times over the years. We did  boycott  it a few years ago due to our shitty waitress making us wait over twenty minutes to come and see what we wanted. We actually ended up walking out of Chilis..So we decided to give it any other try and we were happy with food and service till last night. We ordered well done hamburgers and they came out raw!!!!. So we had to wait another 25 minutes for our meal due to their mistake and we had to pay the full bill which was B.S. We feel they should of given us a break on the bill for their mistake and us having to wait another 25 minutes before we got to eat.. We again are boycotting this place and will probably not be returning..Our server was Monica and she did a good job.... Your cooks need to read before they just assumed we wanted raw burgers.........................
I'm really not sure how this location is still in business.  Staff is uninterested in actually helping you.  Food is ehhhhhh!  There are so many good places to eat.  This ain't one of them.

My Thai ice cream WAS DELICIOUS BUT may I point out how bad of a customer service I received that Sunday I went. No customers were in there. The employee DID NOT GREET my husband and I, as if we interrupted his time from his phone. I had asked a question and he replied with a attitude as if I was annoying him. I asked because it was my first time having Thai style ice cream. Then as he handed me my ice cream I said thank you, he didn't reply or even looked up at me. So RUDE, I def regret tipping him. Will NEVER return to establishment. What sucked was we don't even live in Philly but still went since I was craving for Thai style ice cream.

I know, what should I expect from a rundown Burger King at 8th & Market? But today's experience was really beyond pathetic. 

I waited for 20 minutes this morning for my simple order of 2 breakfast sandwiches and hash browns. The workers showed no interest at all in helping customers or making food. The cashier took an order, then slouched off to do something in the back, no apologies. The line extended to the door. 

I could see in the kitchen they were slowly cooking a couple items, and frying a small basket of hash browns. With the number of people in line they should have had a double order of everything on the grill and been hustling to get it all done. 

It took 10 minutes just to get to the cashier and place my order. Then I stood against a wall and waited another 10. I watched 6 people who were behind me in line get their food first. When I finally asked if they'd skipped me they said "no your order is almost ready." But there was no reason mine should have taken longer. They were just apathetic, half asleep and verging on mean with their annoyance at customers who didn't come when their number was called. 

After all that, the sandwiches were sloppily put together, egg hanging out the sides, and wrapped with the inside of the wrapper on the outside. 

So if by posting this I can get even ONE person to avoid this place, I will feel I've done my job.

Walked in from shopping to grab a round of drinks or two before we headed home to Clearwater today. The young lady bartending clearly saw us sit down at one of the side tables by the bar by the front window but for some reason choose to never speak or acknowledge us while we were there. I had to use the restroom while my girlfriend waited to order drinks and by the time I came out, at least 10 minutes while waiting to use restroom, she still had not been greeted or asked for an order. If we were suppose to order drinks at the bar and go back to our seats that is perfectly fine but the bartender could have at least informed us of that while we waited. I have been in the Restaurant Industry for over 15 yrs and I have never treated any guest with such a lack of hospitality. As new residents in the area, I can promise you we will not be back and we will not be recommending your establishment to anyone.

I went to eat at this so called great diner the food was disgusting plus we ordered takeout food it was all wrong the order plus I complained and they told me well what u want me to do very rude workers I will never go to eat there again u will not get a vote from me for 2018 worst place to eat tell ur workers to treat there customers with dignity and respect worst 2018 diner

Took our appointment and over booked and told us they could get us in by noon.  2 hours after our appointment!! On a Thursday morning!  And while we were leaving another women came in with an appointment...

Customer service at this hotel is negative stars if I could give it. My husband and  I just got off the phone with the front desk after a weeks stay at this hotel to talk to them about why they took $1700 out of our account when they were only supposed to take 700. The woman I spoke to on the phone was extremely rude to me would not let me finish what I was trying to explain to her. All of her responses seem like she had a big attitude over me asking the littlest of questions just trying to figure out what was going on with their establishment and our bank account. Come to also find out that we were charged over $50 for " mini bar use" when my husband and I did not even touch the small refrigerator located under the TV the entire stay. I was hoping to write a good review about our stay here but this absolutely ruined any good remarks that I had on this hotel. We have yet to receive our "incidental "money back when the lady insisted that it was already in our account. Absolutely terrible customer service. Would never recommend.
Not the best , corn bread was definitely unappetizing... same with the rest of the food . Won't be coming back.

I had hoped for authentic Mexican food, even a Spanish flare to Mexican.  Anyway, no chips or salsa brought out, house margarita was fruity and small, and overall non impressive bland/artsy flavor.  

I ordered the Chili Rellenos,  which the server brought out and asked who was having the "chili dinner".  I've never had a fruity Chili Rellenos, but this one was filled with raisins and pine nuts with very little spice or sauces such as Chili Verde or Rojo.  

My opinion, being raised in New Mexico, and extensively traveling Mexico and Spain was that this was an artsy attempt to upsell Mexican cuisine.   

I heard reactions to the enchilada meal as being very coconut heavy in flavor, and even a Taco Bell Reference.  

If you wanted more authentic Mexican food I'd direct you to the closest Applebee's, Chipotle, Taco Bell...and that's not Mexican food as well.

One of the worst places in terms of both service and food I have ever been to in my life. Absolutely terrible the waiters and waitresses walk past you as if you don't exist and the food does not warrant such an attitude. Absolutely terrible establishment from the top down. 1000% percent do not recommend.

The displays are good and informative.
 Wet here to buy a tv for my husband's birthday tomorrow. A senior lo

The pizza was undercooked bottom line. I ordered a medium with bacon and pepperoni and I'm sorry to report that the toppings were very scarce. Not cool.

At least the employees were friendly.

Second worst restaurant experience I've ever had. I waited 10 minutes before a waiter (who smelled horribly of B.O.) acknowledged us. We had to ask a different server to get us drinks. The waiter went to one table that got there after us and said he'd be right with us then made us wait 10 minutes and went to another table that was there after us after seeing his coworker pick up his slack and get our drinks. I had to stop him because after waiting a half hour to even be seated we were starving. Then the people who came after us got their food a good 10 minutes before us. Food came out Luke warm. Sausage gravy had like 10 pieces of sausage. Took 11 off our $60+ bill and couldn't figure out how to split a check. Took 2 hours start to finish for subpar food.

DUNEDIN BAGELS & DELI
I picked up bagels here EVERY week & loved them! My very first job, at 15, was at a bagel shop in NJ with New York owners, Norman & Miriam Fleischman. I know a great water bagel when I taste one. However, I bought a half dozen cinnamon raisin bagels that tasted like onion. The first one tasted like onion. I thought that it, perhaps, came in contact with an onion bagel; no problem. The 2nd one tasted like onion & I thought then that they didn't properly clean their oven. After tasting the 3rd bagel, I called them to ask for 6 more. Well, the owner was angry & inappropriate. He sniffed each of the 3 bagels that I returned & said, "they don't smell like onion!" (Accusing me of lying?! Really?!?!) I would have simply apologized & replaced the 6 bagels...that simple. He said, "you take bite, you taste onion, you bring back!" I tried to explain that I thought it might have just been the one bagel. He got angrier & forcefully threw the remaining bagels in the trash before handing me a new bag of 6. Well, he lost a loyal customer for nothing!!!!!!! BEWARE; do not cross the boss!!!!!
Terrible food. Took 25 minutes to get our food. We ordered blueberry pancakes with a side of 2 eggs. Pancakes were overdone and had almost no blueberries. Left with stomach aches and disappointment

Frankly, I don't understand how anyone has had a good experience at Heffe.  The staff was inattentive and unfriendly right off the bat.  That being said,  places can have bad service and still have good food, and we had been interested in stopping by the Fishtown location for some time, so we figured we'd give them a shot anyway.  I ordered the Almost Pastor tacos, my friend ordered the Fat Man burrito, and we got the poutine to share.  The tacos were bland and boring.  The pineapple was less than fresh, the pork was tough, and it seems they completely forgot any seasoning whatsoever.  I took a couple bites and just didn't feel like it was worth the calories, so I gave up.

The burrito was sizeable, so my friend suggested we just share that instead.  The burrito and poutine however, were completely the opposite.  There was plenty of flavor, and would be great if your preferred flavor is salt, and only salt.  The poutine was so salty that the other flavors didn't come through at all.  I think my blood pressure went up 20 points by the first bite.  The Fat Man burrito was just totally inedible.  Unless you happen to be a horse, or some other animal that enjoys a salt lick.  It was seriously gross.  After a couple bites, we actually decided to toss all the food and went next door to Stockyard to split a sandwich instead.  We didn't see the point in complaining since the staff was less than cordial from the beginning.   

I was hoping that maybe it was just an "off" night - it would be really cool to have a decent taco place in this neighborhood.  Unfortunately, based on the other negative reviews and how truly terrible our experience was, it's just not worth another try.  The tacos really do suck, and so did everything else about our experience.

Don't order wings from here! We ordered some recently and generally you would not complain about a large chicken wing but these were like small turkey legs! And the tips were still attached so they were impossible to eat but the worse part was there was a feather still on one of the wings. It was pretty gross!!

Im giving this a 2 start because the staff is friendly, other than that it receives a one star. 
I have a beautiful hand crafted and designed white gold engagement ring with 121 diamonds and a center stone of 2 ct; needless to say it is very valuable. On my honeymoon a little side diamond fell out so I researched places to take my ring for a small repair and saw good reviews on here and decided to go with them as they have in house repairs. Unfortunately this was a mistake. 
From the moment I walked in they were nice, yet their work does not match their attitudes. As I explained to the lady my issue she tried to sell me on her insurance when I was telling her that I already had my own and I am here to repair it, not buy new insurance. 
Then, she gave me a week and a half time frame for the repair but said it would really only take a few days. Two weeks went by and I had still heard nothing so I went in to pick it up hoping it would be ready, they just forgot to call, but no, they had not even STARTED!!! The next day it was finally ready (after I complained) and they did a horrible job. The diamond they replaced is of far less quality, they 'squished' it in place and ruined the prongs holding it. They also rhodium plated it for me, however my ring is two tone and they covered the yellow gold in white gold when doing it... Just really upsetting. Luckily I have a jeweler back home I will be seeing over the holiday's that I will have fix what they did.. 
Lastly, I called to let them know I was unhappy with their work and Will was not very helpful and almost did not even care. 
They may be great when you're buying something that makes them a lot of money, but NOT when its a small repair. They put it on the back burner until they have time. Very sad.

This is the second time i have been to a Miller's after the first disaster in Christiana, Delaware. So i gave it another chance. The service was the worst service I have experienced.  The food was cold, the baked potato tasted like it sat for days. Server did not bring required condiments. Refills were never filled. Don't waste your money here. Better quality service around that area.

What's good fam!! Iight sooo, I was walkin up in dis establishment lookin Like I play for the Eagles "Fly". I had my Fitted Cap on, Gucci belt, down to my Nike boots!! G'd up from the Feet Up! 
I got me one of Der "famous pizzas" and let me tell you Somethin!! The Waitress was lookin hella fly too but she had the audacity to put a slice on my plate for me like I couldn't do it myself! Rule number one don't touch a mans food! 
Anyway I got over it cuz I'm a G. The pizza was lookin good so I went to take my first bite; and Dat ish burnt the top floor of my mouth clean offf. It took me a lil to gain back my swag but I found it. After the feelin came back I realized The whole pizza was burnt, like Black as the asphalt burnt. It tasted like straight BOOOOTTTTYY!!! 
Idk bout y'all but dis G ain't payin for no over priced pizza that's burnt.

Food is decent. Waiters were awesome. -2 stars because of the manager (Adam?) who was a total prick. 

We had a party of ~15 and had just finished dinner. Just as we had the credit card/bill returned for signature, he came out of nowhere and rudely told us to hurry up because there was apparently a party that had waited an hour at the bar for our table. What's your deal man?

1) We had just received the credit card/bill for signature. We weren't just occupying the table for no reason.
2) There was no prior indication that he needed the table back. Why not give us a 20 minute heads up? Nobody would have taken issue with that. And how were we supposed to know that people were waiting at the bar? That's not our damn job - isn't that what Adam gets paid to do? Do your job bud.

I have been renting at PHL national for one year and I have to say it has slowly gone downhill. Drop off last Friday was a 20 minute wait with the line extending out to the service road and wrapping around the corner.  There were cars parked everywhere in the lot.  Pick up on Monday was a choice of 4 cars; one had no key (which makes me question how it got to emerald aisle in the first place), 2 muscle cars and a Nissan which had not been cleaned on the inside or the outside. I took the filthy car due to weather. 
 The area for returning cars was still full of parked cars, and some even blocking the exit lanes. Too many cars and not enough employees?

Warning: this review is only getting 2 stars because I've had good service in the past here, but today was a nightmare. 

So my SO and I show up to Don Pablo's at 1:30pm on a Sunday, as soon as we arrive, I can see about half the tables are not bussed and dirty old plates and cups cover most useable seating. The host took about 15 minutes to seat 3 tables before us due to him scouting which tables were clean. After being seated, we were not given a drink menu and after 10 minutes of waiting for a server, I decided to run to the restroom. I overheard the host talking to a server about how he sat her section and she had no idea that had happened. I returned to the table 2 minutes later, the server dropped off a drink menu finally. We order our drinks and food at the same time, after 10 more minutes we finally received our margaritas. So after being there almost 40 minutes, we got our drinks in a restaurant with only 1/4th of the tables taken. I open my silverware and find cheese stuck to the knife, told the waitress and she replaced them with another knife covered in cheese. It took 4 tries to get some decent silverware. The waitress then brought out our food, she apparently heard chicken fajitas when I definitely ordered steak fajitas. So I waited 25 more minutes for my correct order to come out while my SO was basically done her food. The fajita was good, the drinks were good, but the service was god awful. I'd be embarrassed if I worked there today, I won't be going back for awhile.

Possibly the worst service and food EVER at a restaurant. True - it was the college playoff game day. It was super busy. Wait!! This is New Orleans next to a stadium!! They should know how to work crowds right? Extra staff? Extra service. Oh no. It was awful. Dreadful. Embarrassing I was even there. But after the horrendous wait for a table I felt then trapped. Ignored, lied to, dreadful food even when it did come. Seriously. This awful 'chuckie cheese for adults' should be shut down. So sad I even paid. Should have just left.
Good food but had horrible service Sunday night around 8 pm. Sad because I love the place but we were just treated with no importance when the restaurant was empty besides us.

The saddest part of this review is that I used to like Axis and frequent it all of the time but my last experience was telling. In ordering a chicken finger platter, I asked for a side caesar salad along with BBQ sauce and honey mustard for the fingers. When I get back to my office and open my meal, I find that instead of the salad, I received chicken noodle soup and instead of BBQ sauce, I received maple syrup. What's even more annoying is that I paid extra for the BBQ sauce. When I call them and tell them of their mistakes, they only offer to remake the salad. I still had to travel back to the restaurant and exchange my food myself with no reimbursement for my time and inconvenience. Axis, do better.

Usually Texas Roadhouse Restaurants have pretty good service and the one of the best steaks.  However, I feel this Texas Roadhouse stands by itself as the worst service restaurants in the chain. I live very close to this restaurant, but will go to Greenwood location instead of going here.  The workers at the Avon location are constantly messing up the food orders. The managers will give some shortsighted excuses without any apologies and/or compensation. I will never be back.

I am really surprised with all these great Yelp reviews. This place is mediocre at best. And way too overpriced!!
Good concept, really nice space and ambiance but very poor execution. 
First the food. It is definitely overpriced. We went twice for breakfast. 
Oatmeal they serve is Trader Joe's organic quick cook oatmeal in packets. They just add hot water and a few slices of bananas. Twice I was told "sorry we ran out of steel cut oats". 
The silver dollar pancakes and scrambled eggs are just ok, wouldn't come back for that either. 
They had some oatmeal chocolate chip cookies which were really good but again overpriced. 
Coffee was ok, nothing special but I have to say that they do serve organic half and half and organic almond milk. 
View is great, nice outdoor seating and very pleasant space inside. But... service is terrible. They seem like they have no idea what they're doing. Everyone is doing everything-from taking orders to cooking to serving. It seemed very chaotic. I waited the other morning for 15 mins just to order-even though I was first in line because the guy was making smoothies and explained the older lady what she should be doing. She was munching on the dates while making smoothies, not wearing gloves and one of the guys who was supposed to do all the cooking (I guess) was taking orders using the same glove for handling credit cards that he uses for preparing food...The two guys also seemed a bit annoyed and unpleasant-probably because they cannot handle that many customers... 
All in all-menu looks interesting and different but the food my group had was just ok. Won't be coming back. Please do something about the service!!
I had a really bad experience. The Biriyanis we ordered were definitely not fresh. My stomach was upset after eating here. Never coming back. Sorry.
Eh. Cool ambiance. Rude bartender. Okay drinks... maybe go on a busier night........ maybe.
If I could. I'd give no stars. For them to take so long you'd think food was fresh. No. Not at all. Highly upset.

Try the gluten free at your own risk. My husband and I got it and now have good poisoning. He usually has a steel stomach and gets gluten free so I can eat his pizza.. 

Decided to enjoy a pizza on a hot afternoon, but options for gluten free are always limited. Ordered a margarita pizza on gluten free crust and was sorely disappointed... the pizza was very, very sweet and missing ingredients. The other pizzas that my family ordered were below par. Now to find an edible dinner.

Really disappointed with my experience this time around. We ended up being there for about 2 hours and not by choice. While they were busy it didn't help that I could see our server shooting the breeze at the bar. I am familiar with the style of the restaurant but was aggravated by how long it took everyone to receive their food at our table. The butternut squash was amazing as always but my main dish literally tasted like gruel. We saw our actual server maybe 3 times during the entire visit. When we received our main dishes it took about 5 minutes before we could flag down someone to give us forks so we could actually eat our food. When we were brought the utensils the server made a rude comment. We finished our food and patiently waited for the server to come and check on us and give us the check. Since we weren't asked if there were going to be separate checks at the beginning of the meal we asked if it was possible to split the check. (On a side note we have had our check split before there). Our server said I can only split it evenly as many times as you want. He repeated it again and this time he was more rude. I understand that this place is busy and popular but the service has totally ruined the place for me. It's a shame that they care more about being cool and hip over treating customers kindly.
Not the best experience I had the Thai Shrimp Salad. I would just say I am reminded why I never go to this Applebee's.

Really deserves 0 stars for customer service, ability to diagnose issues properly, and price.  Incorrectly replaced 2 tires to correct a problem they diagnosed that had nothing to do with the tires.  Asked for a discount to do the actual repair and they offered a few dollars off that still left the price higher than their competitors.  Don't let them do any auto repairs unless you want to pay more money for poor workmanship and service.

Update:  I was offered a refund for the 3 tires they replaced.  The catch is that I had to bring 3 new tires and pay for having them put on the car.   Can anyone explain how that makes any sense?  Neither could they.    Laughable.
Worst cheese steak I ever had.Tasteless with crappy roll and tiny size for the money.My local pizza place makes a way better and bigger  sandwich for the same price
Philly cheesesteak has no flavor but the mustard they put on it. And too much pepper. Not a good example for the home of the creation.

There's always wet floors from soda machines they always leave it wet. And popcorn all over the floors no one cleaThe theaters a lot of times people aren't quiet they just act stupid all loud laughing. People are gushing them and nothing is done. And a lot of the reclining seats are broken. There's a young African American manager I tried to talk to and he just walked away instead of dealing with the issues. Had to wait to speak to another manager when they came in hours later. 
This AMC needs to have someone check on people. There's people there that just come in for free.

My family and I took my mom here for her 61st birthday. It was her first time experiencing the habachi grill. Our chef was amazing and the food was delicious, which Is why this review even got 1 star, but our server was the absolute worst. We were a party of 12 and when we were seated the table did not have enough dishes or menus. Our server was very rude when we requested more. My aunt has a mushroom and shrimp food allergy but the server proceeded to give her a soup full of mushroom flakes anyway. Once the chef began preparing our food, we did not see our server again... she didn't stop by to check on our needs and even the chef was looking around for her. All of our cups were empty and in need of a refill, so I had to get up from my seat and search around for our waiter to inform her that we needed refills. She exclaimed that she had other tables to tend to... which is fine but she never returned to check on us. I'm not sure if her customer service skills sucked because she knew gratuity was included regardless if she works or not, but thanks to her we will choose a different habachi restaurant in the future. Oh, and to put the cherry on top, my husband wanted a to-go water, since we had a 1 hour drive home, and of course our server was absent after we paid, so I proceeded to ask another server near the sushi bar, and he and his coworkers laughed right in my face and told me to ask my server... at this moment I was disgusted knowing I gave these people our hard earned money. Never again.
Not the best check in. It took forever. For the price they charge maybe they should keep the rooms a little better. For top dollar I expect a little better.

Did not mind going to this restaurant though I don't consider it one of the best seafood places. But because it's less than a mile from my house and convenient I go. I do not participate in their $40 Buffet because I cannot eat $40 worth of food. And of course you cannot take it home with you. So I normally go in and order Seafood by the pound and take some home and make other meals from it. Last Friday I went, and it is busy because of Lent. However I  did not mind the  40-minute wait, Until they seated us and told us we could not order crawfish by the pound. They had a sign on the wall that stated how much crawfish was by the pound. Do you think they could have told us they were not selling it by the pound. Well if you think you're going to bamboozle me into a $40 Buffet you have another thought coming. I went to Perino's their crawfish is much better anyway tho it does cost more.  I will likely never go back to Zydeco's. I just think that was extremely disrespectful, inconsiderate, and rude

I wish I could give worse than one star because this place deserves it.  We were there on a Saturday night and had to pay a cover to get in. 15 minutes after entering we were told we have to leave. We wanted to wait inside for an for one minute. The bouncer came over and started yelling at us to get out because they were closing, however there were many people still inside. He proceed to call my friend a "f#%king p~$sy" for not wanting to stand in the cold. Would not recommend

This restaurant is in my neighborhood and I love coming here for good beer and food. I've been really turned off from coming to the 8th ave location in the past 3 months because the service has been pretty bad. It takes 15 minutes to put in a beer order and the servers usually are standing around talking and ignoring my table. I go with my boyfriend and we are both very patient customers who work in restaurants so we try to be understanding but I really don't think I plan on coming back anytime soon. The location on Charlotte has way better service and is less busy so I plan on going to there down the line. I live 5 min from the 8th ave location and 20 min from the West nashville one and I would rather drive further for the service. It's that bad at 8th. Food is great and so is the beer so it's a huge bummer.

Was excited to go here because of its location but I ended up getting food poisoning after and was throwing up all night. I know this was the cause because it was the only thing I ate since breakfast so about a 6 hour window. Then got sick about 1 hour after eating. Also, nachos were the weirdest and worst I ever had. Truly disappointed.

Lunch buffet is gross and has not much variety. Chicken tikka masala is Campbell's tomato soup base. They replenish buffet by dumping bowls of refill into trays, not replacing the whole tray. Ambiance is pretty so it's a shame. It's basically Indian fast food.

I've been coming here for a while as i work across the street and i will say the food is good and the staff is nice. My only issue is I've never had an order from here that was correct. There's always something missing or something added that i did not want. It got to the point where i didn't even call to let them know anymore. Now nobody from my office will be returning there and we will go to Plaza Azteca instead.
