Absolutely a no go.  Used to be a go to.  Food and service are all in the gutter.   Last time I got carryout, raw pork dumplings, brown spots on the broccoli, no spice to the chicken noodle soup.  Never again.

We had spicy miso ramen and spicy tonkotsu ramen. Both were equally spicy. The spicy miso noodles were thicker than spicy tonkotsu noodles, which looked like thin sphagetti noodles. Unfortunately, they were not quite the type of noodles I like in my ramen. Other than a few slices of pork, half an egg (semi-hard boiled), and some corn, there really isnt much else in the bowls of noodles. Pretty plain for the price. Personally, I think their prices are too high. Overall, the ramen didn't impress me. 

We also ordered octupus balls and they were ok. Nothing spectacular.

I must add their parking is not suitable for big vehicles like a toyota sequoia. Parking lot is very cram and not enough space. We ended parking along the street.

My first time trying this place and I will never return. We've had catering from here for many many meetings and it has always been yummy so when I had to grab lunch on the go as most grad students do I thought this would be a good spot. 

To begin, I stood for about 5min (no one else waiting in line) before someone acknowledged me so I could order. I ordered a pesto chicken sandwich- no changes or substitutions. I go to pay and after a few minutes an employee places the sandwich on the counter and gestures to me. I ask "pesto chicken" to which he replies "yes". I grab my carrots/sandwich and run off only to discover after walking about a mile to work that I was given the WRONG sandwich. If I didn't find the smell of tuna passionately disgusting and it was a turkey sandwich instead I might have just eaten it but I'm sitting here now nauseous from the smell, without a lunch, and out $9. 

I highly doubt I will get a refund and I will just give this sandwich to the sweet homeless woman who sits near my building. Only positive outcome is that she will get a warm lunch today!

This has to be the worst place for customer service around! I keep going back for that damn stuffed crust, so i can't give it up altogether. However, each time i order, it takes 2-3 times the original quoted time to actually arrive. They tell me 30-40 minutes and it's at least 2 hours EVERY TIME. I usually do pickup, but there are times that I can't. I wish someone would whip this place into shape and at least give REALISTIC wait times!

It's was 6:40PM and they had the doors locked to the dining room. We awkwardly made eye contact with the employees inside working... then two little kids came and opened the door. The employees didn't attended to us at all and pushed us off and made us wait (nobody was in the drive thru). Of course shake machine was down; like anywhere else around here. We just got two tacos and left.

St Patrick's day, they bombed. Went for lunch on St Patrick's day. Big mistake. Service was extremely slow. I was craving a rueben, not on the menu, so I ordered a BLT figuring it would be quick and easy. The music was very loud and we didn't want to stay any longer than necessary. I took a bite of the BLT and realized there was NO bacon on it, not just a small amount, NONE. Our waitress never came to check on us, empty drink glasses and all. By the time she showed up we were ready to go. I pointed out that there was NO bacon on my sandwich. The manager took a few dollars off a sandwich I didn't eat. As we left, parched from no refills, I noticed several people eating ruebens. Seriously, we weren't even told about the specials. Left hungry and thirsty after paying a hefty check. Please, if you advertise a St Patrick's day party, BE PREPARED, staff up and don't act surprised you're busy.
The sign says they are open till 10pm! We were there at 9:50. And it was closed. Fix your signs please, or stay open till the actual closing time frame. Thanks.

Cute little diner and I was so hoping it would be good.  
I had coffee, two eggs, bacon, toast with a hash brown.
The eggs were okay, the bacon was stone cold, and had been deep fried when cooked, rye toast (with some sort of butter type thing that was NOT butter...it looked like melted cheese wiz....I never even attempted to eat it. It was absolutely DISGUSTING looking), the hash brown left a fair amount of grease sitting under it on the plate and the coffe was weak.  There are too many good Breakfast places in the Bay Pines, Seminole area to consider this less than mediocre breakfast place.  I was VERY disappointed.

Tonight I attempted to order food from this restaurant despite the bad experience I had in the past. So I placed my order online, payment took off my card, once I got in my car and was on my way I received a call from the pizza hut stating We can complete your order because we don't have any product, when I was trying to explain my frustration the unprofessional young lady hung up the phone on me. Avoid this location if possible. The food is subpar and the service is very poor. Hope the owner or manager read these bad review and re-vamp his/her team, or the owner re-vamp the whole staff.
The food is always good here but the employees are very very slow. There's always a massive line,  of because of an influx of people but because of sluggish service

We came here on a Tuesday night. Not busy at all. My boyfriend went to the bar to get a vodka Red Bull. She poured the vodka and then poured out of a ROCKSTAR energy drink can that I saw her drink out of  multiple times. I just want to know why she thought this was ok and why this was allowed.

Sitting here right now.  Floor is so greasy it's like skiing. No bathrooms here so had to go across the hall and someone had puked in the sink.  Bathroom was dirty in other ways too.  No way to dry your hands, dryer or towels. Server was nice so one star for her.
The food was ALRIGHT. Chow mein was totally disgusting. Noodles were over cooked and too soft. I would have rather ate top ramen

We started off the experience with spotting a cockroach on the ceiling above another couples table. We told the manager and they spent some time figuring out what to do before moving the couple. They ended up moving the couple and having a waiter grab the cockroach with a napkin and throw it away. It really freaked us out and made us question about the cleanliness of the place. Next we ordered the royal street salad and mr b's salad with chicken. The salads were decent, but we had to send two back to get them to remake the salad and add bacon/blue cheese to them. The other girls ordered seafood gumbo and pastrami sandwich. They were disappointed with their meals. The service was just okay. In addition when we got our check it was wrong and we had to send it back. FYI to add a 3oz grilled chicken breast it cost an additional 7 bucks. Overall I would not come back here. It doesn't live up to all the great reviews.
The service was very friendly. The food just ugh. We got 4 grouper sandwich with a handful fries and a soufalle cup of plain old Cole slaw three waters and s tea 80.00 FOR 4 OKAY SANDWICH not again

So, this used to be one of my favorite restaurants. I wanted to try it since they finally have a franchise in the metro area. I have to say that I was truly disappointed. I don't normally do any reviews less than 4 stars, but unfortunately.....
First, I have to say the customer service was amazing! I felt it was the behind the scene area that greatly affected our meal. I save this restaurant for this occasion alone. Only because we've eaten at other franchises across the board and it was our favorite. The crab cakes were cool when brought out, but it was reissued and removed from our check. It was okay. The manager Soliel came to check up on us and he's was great!

The steaks were mediocre and that was to say the least. I've never had to add salt to a steak and it was the first time it was not hot. The sides were okay but not up to par. 

Our waiter Alex was phenomenal at trying to please us. He made sure we had everything that we needed. It was the kitchen that may have slipped tonight. Not sure if I will be back for a special occasion, but maybe just to pass through.

It has now been twice where I have called in the attempt to place in order to go & told no go.  This evening I called around 8:42 and was put on hold. Hours posted say they close at 9pm. After a long hold, I was told that they lock the door at nine, start shutting down the sushi bar at 8:45. So I was out of luck. So great that with so many outstanding sushi & other good restaurants nearby they feel okay with turning away customers. I will never dine there or order carry out from Wasabi ever again. Horrible customer experience!

it took them over an hour and fifteen minutes on a carry out I ordered and they served people that walked in off the streets before they finally got mine made. If you have the time order the pizza, it's solid.

First time coming and the last time this place sucks
I bought spaghetti and meatballs and a margarita pizza spaghetti and meatballs was all full and the meatball taste like it was sour and the margarita pizza was cold and soggy I felt like this place took my money

Not a very comfortable bed, no coffee or microwave in the room, and the ac unit smelled. Also the sheets were scratchy and I had to use my own blanket. Also not all of the lights worked in the room. A little disappointed.

5/19/2018 tried calling this place at 5:10am to 5:30am for take out. No one would answer. I arrived at 5:31am there was no patrons in the restaurant 2 female employees appeared to be nonchalantly getting ready for the day. One wearing a pink camo ballcap admitted they turn off the ringer, a bad habit of theirs,hmmm. I placed my order and she casually walked to the break area told the cook. He comes out looking like he just crawled out of bed or something. My wife said she could see his bloodshot eyes from the car! As he moved around like a snail, while the other waitress made coffee chopping on her gum acting suspicious about something. Turning off the ringer to their phones must be common practice for the area. I tried calling the Lebanon Waffle House on 109 at the same time couldn't get an answer there either! People that do take out I would guess have somewhere to be, I do!! I wonder what their headquarters would think about that?

My daughters and I did the jazz dinner cruise last night. The cruise itself was nice and informative. We learned some very interesting things about New Orleans such as it is six to eight feet below sea level! We were informed that this is the reason for the above ground cemeteries because if you dig down six feet, you'll hit water! So interesting! 

The staff was very friendly! The lady who led us to our table from Gray Line was very upbeat and enthusiastic! I wish I could remember her name. Jamie, our waitress was also very nice. 

The cruise itself was $48, with dinner,  $83 per adult. There was salad with a vinaigrette dressing already on the table, which was pretty tasty. The food was available buffet style. I chose the green beans almondine, creamed spinach, cajun pasta, prime rib, roasted pork loin, and chicken gumbo. 

The reason for the two stars is the food. I was surprised at the poor quality. The green beans were tough and borderline stringy. The creamed spinach and the cajun pasta were bland. I'm wondering if they were from a can. The prime rib had a lot of gristle and the roasted pork loin was very dry. The chicken gumbo was unremarkable, to say the least. As for dessert, the bread pudding was inedible. Aside from the salad, the bananas foster was the only thing I enjoyed. 

As much as I don't want to tell you what I was thinking about the food, I must because if you're like me, you depend upon Yelp to help with your choices. That said, the food reminded me of what would be served in a nursing home for a holiday meal.......no kidding. 

I wouldn't advise bringing children on this cruise as it was crowded and the rails are a bit lower than what I'm used to. My grandchildren are well behaved and I wouldn't bring them. 

I would highly recommend the cruise itself for the information, sightseeing, and live entertainment. Do yourself a favor, save yourself $35 and eat before you get on the cruise.
They were invited to join our school event with 15% of their proceeds benefiting the school. They were the busiest truck and never donated the amount they agreed too. Total bummer!

Stay away from this place! Worst hotel ever. Motel 6 next door is a safer place. A lot of truckers here, lots of noise and the worst staff you'll ever meet. Sour and belligerent. You'll want to change hotels the minute you arrive. The woman who worked here refused to help with a key card that wasn't magnetized n told me to wait in a line of 10 people when I had a child waiting at the room door. And then she came up to my room - not to help me but to yell at me. Bizarre staff here. Actually frightening . Stay Away.

So I love their pasta bread bowls-  and they have never messed up my order- but they DONT deliver to my address like what is that- I live in Crystal Beach and no Dominos in this area delivers so to have it I literally have to pick it up. It's insane, like literally the opposite point of a pizza place that's known for delivery it that it doesn't deliver to your place. I've never heard of that.  This is sad lol.

I was waiting for a table with many other people and nobody come. It was 9:30 pm. We call the restaurant and they said it was open. After that someone appear to attend us. The guy start to walk to guide us for our table and a lady appears saying that the kitchen was closed. It was disrespectful and unprofessional.

Sad when I am forced to drop two stars from an old review. 

First the have force out the old cook and the lady who ran the counter. 

The new lady who works the counter burns incense.

Next the food quality and portions dropped but the prices went up. 

All of this was executable. 

About a month ago I ordered a sandwich the Grand total of which costed over $16. 

I paid $2 for bacon it came with 4 2 inch slices. 

Really the only reason I bother to eat there was because I could get dinner food at 6:30 am 

Well as of today I guess you can no longer order a cheese steal till closer to lunch. 

Left will go on but I be going to other locations that are willing to cater to the late night employ getting off work.
2 orders of Dry ribs brought them out 2 times and they was the same way. The waiter was very nice though.

My family and I haven't been here in about 5 yrs ... we will not go back again.. I don't know if there is new management or what, but the ceiling has a huge hole in it right near the tables where we sat.. it was constantly leaking and no bucket was being used. You can't tell me no one noticed it ??  Also the bathrooms were a mess.. the floors were sticky and one of the toilets wouldn't flush.. the water was leaking out of the joints and running all over the back of the toilet. 2 our if the 3 sinks were broken. We were really disappointed in the look and feel of this place... very slow service when it was dead also..  sorry but go elsewhere..

Dump! Without a doubt the FILTHIEST restaurant I've ever stepped into.  Slow night, but every table was still dirty.  Instead of cleaning they wanted to seat us at the ONLY table that was clean.  They did not want to clean any tables. I found out why when I passed by the kitchen: they had HUGE PILES of dirty dishes piles up in the back.  The cooking station was filthy.  We couldn't get out of there fast enough.

This is the worst eye doctor's office I have ever been too. I ordered glasses a month and a half ago now and they have still yet to come in due to clerical errors on their part. They were supposed to be here in 7-10 business days. It has been 22 business days and still counting. 

  I called after 10 days only to find out that they had never even placed the order for the glasses I picked out. Apparently they had ordered contact lenses for me instead.  Very confused about that since I handed them the frames for the glasses and paid for them, so I have no idea how they would order a box of contacts from that interaction.  On top of that, they told me they wouldn't have placed my order until January 1, 2020 due to insurance guidelines (this ended up being their mistake, they could order them!  The insurance company was so confused when I called them about this!).  It would've been really great to know that they didn't plan on placing my order for an entire 18 months after I paid for them.  After getting that sorted out, 10 days later, they called to tell me the glasses finally arrived. I went to pick them up to only find out they messed up the lenses. So now I am waiting. AGAIN. 

  I wouldn't mind the problem with the glasses so much if they were the least bit professional there. Every time I called the office to inquire about my glasses, they told me they would call back later that day. Well, I would wait an entire 24 hours and would not hear back, so I would have to reach out to them again. If you are going to promise a patient you will call them back, then you have to actually call them back! 

  I truly cannot express how much you should not go here. I've been wearing glasses for 25 years now and have never encountered a worse office.

Friendly staff. Didn't like the food. I went for breakfast one morning and disappointed after hearing such rave reviews from people I know frequent there. I'm one to give places a second chance so I'll trying going during their lunch hours.

Had a 4 PM appointment. Came in 5 minutes early and told them I had an appointment for a fill at 4. Waited for 30 minutes and left. Two people left before me... They try to market themselves as a modern,  fancy. not your typical nail salon but they need to do a better job with their customer service. Too many good salons around to pay the extra they charge and have too wait even with an appointment.

Mediocre all the way.

We were looking for a good bfast, and was sorely disappointed. The food was mediocre at best and the service was terrible. We waited for 40 minutes for our food, all eggs and pancakes. When it came out it was not very warm, and was blasé. The server did not check up on us and only mentioned in passing that they were busy and that was the reason for the delay, which is interesting as a group who came in after us got their food, ate, and left before we got our food.

My doctor is good, but every time I'm actually sick, even for a chronic condition that only requires a refill, dealing with their staff is a nightmare. I've been misdiagnosed by a PA, hung up on while a receptionist was fighting with her significant other on the phone for choosing the 'emergency' line during an emergency, and denied a prescription causing me needless suffering and multiple phone calls. If you aren't able to help me when I'm sick, why are you my doctor?

As a frequenter, I had high hopes as the West Nashville and Midtown location are our favorites. I always get PBMS nitro- it was kind of flat, along with the other IPA we got. One of the things we love about Tailgate is the personable service. The bar service was equal to going to broadway- order, get the drink, and they walk away after you get it. I'm not expecting a full conversation but some interaction would be nice- especially since it's a new location. "Hey, how are y'all? Have you been to Tailgate before? Would you like to sample anything? This is what we have new, you should try it?" BASIC restaurant conversation- we got none. I would have asked for a new beer if it didn't take having to reach over the counter just to flag down the bartender in order to order our pizza (for which we got charged $1.99 for swapping a meat- that we do at other locations with no charge). Pizza was lacking toppings too. I would suggest y'all get on the same page for every location. I don't mind paying extra for ranch when it's homemade (like other locations) but not a fan when it's from a jar. We just hurried up and left to go elsewhere. Don't think y'all were ready to open yet- maybe we will come back in 6 months...

So disappointing! We booked a reservation in advance only to wait 30 minutes for our table. Once seated our waitress made note of our lengthy wait and apologized but it still took another 10 minutes to even fill out water glasses! No sort of compensation was offered for our delayed seating. Unfortunately, the service tanked even further from there. The few times our table was even checked on they didn't stay around long enough to allow us to get a word in, or to ask for basic service such as refills in our empty water glasses. 

The food was as ordered, but hardly seemed worth the bother or the price. Two hours later we finally concluded our underwhelming brunch experience.

It appeared nice and clean.  The prices are reasonable.  It would probably have been good if the cook had taken out what he burned and cleaned his pan.   However he left the burnt onions and burned oil.  Therefore the entire plate of food was burnt flavored.

Pretty marginal. She did inform me that she had a broken wrist but that she could still do nails just fine. I wanted to get my fingernails and toenails done with the French polish. She told me when I got there that she couldn't do French because of her wrist. By the end of the appointment I knew everything about all her many health issues. Pretty sloppy application of polish. Big space between my cuticle and the polish. Won't be back.

We made a reservation in October, for this trip now in April. The reservation was made for TWO double beds. In addition, knowing that we were arriving late, the room was fully paid for to secure the requested room, and a follow up phone call was made two weeks prior this trip.

Upon arrival, there was only one full bed. Due to the late arrival, they were unable to accommodate any room switch. When calling in the morning, I was told that people still needed to check in and they would see what they could do. Considering the fact that we were here for a rather large conference, I knew the chances of obtaining a room as the day went on. Further more, I do not understand why they "needed to see who else needed to check in" when our room was reserved and fully paid for. 

This room also is a handicap accessible room, which means that there are shower accommodations, and there is a handheld shower head. When the shower head is on the stand, it shoots right at the wall which makes it difficult to just shower. 


I know that Loews has a great reputation, but this visit is very disappointing and just unacceptable. Clearly, despite having reservations, they blatantly do not have any care for their paying customers. 

P.S. Thanks for the roll-away bed, it is awesome (read sarcasm)

I have been here several times and each time there is some sort of issue. Well today was the worst and last time I will be going here. I was with a group of four and everyone but one person ordered something that needed to be cooked/warmed up. The person that ordered the veggie sandwich (lettuce, tomato, cucumber, onions, peppers) was last to get hers and it was past 30 minutes. We had to ask about it before they even started making it. The are so unorganized and get overwhelmed by the lunch rush.

Disappointed. I've been wanting to go to this place for a very long time and was hoping it would be a new go-to for excellent Chicago style pizza. We had the cheese curds as an appetizer and the Deep dish Capone for our meal. The curds were very good but the pizza wasn't knock-your-socks-off like I was hoping. The crust and cheese were good but the copious amounts of sauce and scant toppings left much to be desired. The flavor just wasn't there in the sauce and what little toppings were present were very over powered by the tangy sauce. If I lived closer, I might would give it another try but we're about 40 minutes out so it's highly unlikely. Maybe requesting light sauce would be a good idea. I love deep dish pizza and get it for several meals on every trip to Chicago. Unfortunately, this experience wasn't the local fix that I was hoping it would be.
I would never go to the place again. The food is processed right out of the can. Chicken wings have wings, the stuffed crab cake was extremely cold. Please save your money and don't waste your time.

Don't waist your money. I hate giving poor reviews but this location deserves it. First off, when I walked in I stood at the counter, without being acknowledged, long enough to fully read the menus. After I ordered to go, a couple walked in, who also waited to be seated and no one acknowledged them either so they seated themselves. Lynsey, waitress, walks up from the back and says to the couple... "you were supposed to wait to be seated, but what ever sit where you want" in a very nasty rude tone. They wouldn't of had to seat themselves if someone had been at the front to welcome us into their empty restaurant at 2:45pm on Sunday June 10th. I ordered the hummus trio and received trio soup. The worst looking soupy slop they called hummus. It's very clear why they had no customers. Pour service and terrible food. Never again.

The only good thing about Casino Del Sol is Ume. Rooms are ok , but could be cleaner. Definitely not worth the price. The award winning steak house is ok again not worth the price. Slots are pretty much the same theme. Desert Diamond has a lot more slot machines. The pool water was a light shade of green. Forget having someone bring you drinks. We were there 2 hrs before someone offered. We were so unsatisfied we checked out the same day we checked in. Management is worthless they don't care if you are unhappy.

I had high hopes after all the reviews and it's literally down the road from my new job. BUT, sadly my dip powder mani only lasted 8 days. Day 8 & 9 I had a nail pop right off. I usual make it at least a little over 2 weeks. The women who did my nails rushed through and my squoval requested shape was not uniform on all my nails.
Disappointed! Good color choices and clean are pluses.

Was in Nashville this past weekend with some friends. Decided to try this place as it was close to where we were staying. 

The place is very quaint on the inside. Dark lighting, the type of spot that could suffice a first date, a work event or a family get together. My friend and I showed up around 3pm and strangely there was a ten minute wait (Which is weird, because it's that awkward time in between lunch and dinner, but whatever.) 

Our server is super friendly and attentive. I order the pan seared tuna with a side of the sweet potato fries with jalapeno ketchup. My friend orders the tavern burger. 

Our food comes. I take a bite of my tuna and it appears raw, almost entirely uncooked. I try again and can't bare it. The waiter has no problem swapping my order for the salmon which is very kind of him. My friend appears to enjoy the burger. The fries are fine-- not seven dollar side worthy fine, but decent enough. The jalapeno ketchup tastes like regular ketchup. The salmon doesn't particularly taste like fish (almost like an overly marinated chicken, which wouldn't be a bad thing if it wasn't brought under the guise of fish) but I run through it because I'm starved. We pay and the meal for me was at its best below average. Especially for the cost. 

Naturally the evening/early morning hits and I've got all types of food poisoning and stomach bug type issues (diarrhea, nauseous, headache, puking.) This was Monday morning/ Sunday evening. It's now Thursday and I'm still ill. Not quite sure how these people are cleaning their meats, but I won't be back anytime soon. Nice, attentive staff and sweet vibe. Food was awful.

I don't think my order has ever been right on the first time before... live nearby so I go there but it's so frustrating. Wish they'd work on things. Also ice cream machine is "broken" a lot. Ketchup station is always messy. This place needs new management or owner or something. Just needs help.

Waited 10 minutes to be seated.  No one seated us.  Found a seat.  Was rudely thrown out for having a. Outside drink.  Slow poor service resulted in us wasting 15 minutes of our life and then probably 100$ in food sales.

I understand, but a lot of place on bourbon do allow outside drinks.  So you either 1: need a sign.  2: make sure your customers aren't waiting 15+ minutes to be greeted and seated. 3: if you do blow it and your host is on a break,be a little flexible for wasting all my time due to your lack of posting rules and being attentive to customer.

My only complaint with this location is the disgusting bathroom. Any other Target close by such as Sicklerville & Deptford are way cleaner!  This bathroom has only 3 stalls, the toilet seats look like they need to be replaced and the entire restroom is obviously never cleaned during the day. 

They are currently renovating the entire store and hopefully they make the bathroom bigger with new toilet seats at the very least.

Used to be good when the Asian family owned it. Now it's a bunch of red neck looking kids. Blizzards have NO chunks of stuff any more. Basically a $6 dollar cup of ice cream. I had to stop at Wawa to buy more Reece's cups, chop them up and redo the entire blizzard. From now on I'll just make my own.

Truly terrible service. The hipsters have the urgency of a tortoise and couldn't be less engaging or friendly. We waited forever for an old fashioned cocktail and after watching a majority of the staff work to do menial work like stack crates I eventually called them over to tell them I had been waiting 20 minutes for a drink though the place was virtually empty. All were confused and them took another 10 minutes to figure out what to do about being slow and incompetent. Would never return.

Not impressed with management yesterday around 5. I came to this venue for some food with my coworkers, and ordered a brussel sprout salad which was good. I then ordered macaroni & cheese, and it was cold. I kindly told my server who was extremely attentive and great and he got it out of my way. He brought a new order of mac & cheese out, and it was the right temperature but there was shredded pork inside. I had one of my coworkers try it, and they confirmed it was salty pork. It smelled of pork. As a vegetarian, I quickly lost my appetite and had it returned. The manager came out and assured me I was wrong about the pork and that it was the rind on the gouda. The manager also told me they don't even have pork on the menu, but I looked and they had a crispy pork option as well as a charcuterie board. My coworker corrected him about telling me I was wrong, and the manager stuttered and said he checked with the chef and it wasn't pork. It looks to me like they reused a utensil to heat up my mac. I told him I didn't want anything else. Then, he brings out a salad from their other restaurant which completely confused me because I just finished eating a salad. I didn't touch it, and I was over the experience. I paid for my brussel sprout salad, tipped my server, and left for good.

Horrible place! Do not stay here! I don't even know where to begin. We got two rooms for 3 nights and they both were terrible. One room smelled like a sewer the entire stay and the other where our baby was sleeping had first size cock roaches roaming around. They do Not clean your room during your stay. They'll claim it's to keep the costs of the room low but reality is that they're lazy. I mean, the office is only open from 10am-1pm. Everything management related jus screams lazy. You pay for the proximity to the beach. That's it.
This is the worst Dunkin'. Coffee is never right food has a weird chemical taste. Rather drive a few more miles to avoid this place.

Went into Petit Piquant to get something to eat and needed to use the restroom first and they said we don't have one you can try the library, which was closed. Needless to say scary part of town walking next door to the library! I went back and said anywhere else? They said gas station down the street. No thanks! Homeless people and sketchy outside everywhere! Now was going to go to the bathroom after breakfast. Ordered the short rib Benedict that was on their menu and they said they didn't have it! They didn't have a restroom for customers or food that was on their menu!  I won't be back!

Bland and lacking. When you order cauliflower rice as a base it's expected to get more than a tablespoon or so of it. Tofu was tasteless and not cooked long enough (seemed to be cooked on only one side). Even with the dressing (which was good on its own) it tasted pretty boring. I don't expect much from vegan options in Ta, and it seems it will be that way for a while. The staff was very friendly at least.
Not sure how  this gets high marks. Food was bland and just covered up by lots of spice. I don't mind spicy food at all but this just had no taste. Was very disappointed.

I will never, ever place an order from this restaurant again. This is my second time placing an order through Uber eats at sassafras and the second time there has been a problem with the order. I placed an order for chicken wings. One order for 12 wings. Ninety minutes later and I still have no chicken. I called the restaurant and was told that they don't control the waiting times placed on Uber....so who does? Terrible. They have the customers telephone numbers when you place an order through Uber eats because I have been called by restaurants when they were out of an item. And I can't cancel because I'll be charged for the food as the restaurant indicated that it's being prepared. They should have cancelled this order knowing they couldn't fulfill it in a reasonable time period. Two hours is unreasonable to wait for chicken wings.

I made an appointment online and was confirmed for the next day (Thursday) at 12-1pm. At 11:30am I received a voicemail saying they wouldn't be able to make it until Monday evening. I called back and explained that this was unacceptable seeing as how I was confirmed to be seen at 12. During that conversation I was assured they would come later the same day (Thursday) around 3/4 pm. At 3:45 with no update on where he was, I called and after explaining everything I was asked to leave my phone number And told the repairman would reach out directly. It's now 5:30 pm with no idea of where this repairman is, a broken iPhone and a wasted day of waiting. Terrible communication and customer service.

Well... the girl at the counter did not know what a pour over was. That should tell anyone looking for a good coffee how much of a "coffee house" this is. So I ordered an iced americano instead, extra room for cream. She brought me three little creamer pods.... Anyway, I've had worse. But I've also had much much better. Not a coffee house with an expertise in coffee, that's for sure.

my family members have been here before and loved the food so i was interested on trying. right off the bat, we were seated at a table that didn't have a designated server. so when another server didn't have a table they come serve us. after 15 mins we gave our drink order. then another 15 mins to give our food order. food came out fast which is a plus but the service was weak. i saw a waitress drinking and walking around with a milkshake not doing her job while we wait to place our order. when the food came out it looked pretty good but when i ate it i kind of gagged. i got the chicken parm (which i knew i shouldn't of gotten bc it was pricey) and the sauce used was too peppery and bitter. the chicken was good but the mozzarella was barely melted and rubbery. the penne was not al dente and straight up gross. i could taste the dirty water they probably boiled it in. while i wasn't happy with my dish i picked off of my family's plates and what they had was not bad. they got sandwiches and i had a feeling i should of got that too. i'm giving it two stars for the fast food and good sandwiches and fries. i'm not giving it stars for the poor services, crappy food, and high prices.

This establishment is disorganized and has terrible customer service. After waiting 30 mins to be seated we sat an additional 15 mins while our waiter helped two tables that were seated after us. We had to flag down a waiter from a different section to get us drinks, and then our waiter still didn't even come greet us. After waiting a few more mins we flagged down our waiter to put our food order in. Once the food got to our table it was not hot. We spoke to a manager and she didn't seem too concerned. She gave us a small discount and then walk away. The hostess couldn't figure out how to split our checks. Don't waste your time here.

Definitely the worst place I've had the pleasure of visiting. We literally waited an hour and a half for all of our food to reach the table and not all of us got our food. My burger that  was supposed to be prepared medium well should have been ordered rare because what I got was a rock instead of actual meat. Most of our orders were wrong and the waitress, bless her heart was trying to correct all the mistakes. The manager did speak to us and said it was a weird transition of shift change, which in all honesty is unacceptable. Personally, I returned my food, had it removed from the check and will be getting my dinner elsewhere. An hour and a half for food to come out and orders wrong makes for an extremely disappointing experience.

Leasing agent refused to show us around because it was too far away from our target move in date.  She was playing on her phone.  Don't waste your time.  This property is too old and far away from everything anyway.

This facility was the worst I have ever experienced. The hotel staff were lackadaisical & unconcerned. The property looked like it was out of a post-apocalyptic movie. All the rooms appeared to be unoccupied &/or ransacked. There were rooms that were tossed with multiple beds stacked in the window & others that appeared to not have been occupied in some time. There were bed frames leaned against walls, rooms with open doors (not occupied), debris everywhere & this place was super eerie. When I got to my room, I noticed a very stale smell. The room seemed less clean as much as it was straightened up. When I went into the bathroom, I realized that the bathroom light did not work. The furniture in the room was circa 1970. As I looked at the outdated room, I noticed something disgusting. The bed skirt was covered in mold (pic). I immediately asked for another room. The attendant did not apologize but did move me into another room. This room was on the back of the hotel and it looked abandoned (pic). There was debris all over and was untidy. The room was marginally better and since it was almost midnight...I reluctantly decided to stay. The facility felt unclean and grimy. I slept on he sheets from both beds because the sheets, pillows & towels appeared to be the only thing that was clean. The TV wasn't HD and the channels were basic. When I left I realized that the cars in the lot were for airport parking...not guests. I should have stayed at Motel 6. The sign says it all (pic).

What can be wrong with a movie theater with food? Well I went there on a Tuesday and it's their 5$ for amc members so I knew it would be crowded! But this place was so filthy and there were trash on the ground popcorn everywhere and no one was cleaning it. I had to literally walk as slow as possible to avoid slipping on popcorn butter.
Closed on Sunday July 8th. Not sure why but this restaurant is closed when supposed to be open 11-6 today. Really wanted to try it out while visiting the area.

Yikes! We came to NOLA for great seafood and this place was SO disappointing.  We waited about 15 minutes to get our drink order...and decided to go ahead and place our food order because we didn't know when the waiter would return.   The food was terrible.  Like truly terrible. We ordered a platter... the turtle soup was disgusting... like really bad.... the fried frog legs, crawfish tails, and fried alligator had no seasoning and were very bland.   In fact, no one at our table finished their food.  The service was few and far between because the staff were so over worked.  Two of us ended the night throwing up an hour after eating here. There are so many better places!

Ate here last night and the food was not very good.  I had calamari as an appetizer and I think this may have been the worst calamari I've ever eaten.  If not, it was close.  Had the clam strips for dinner and they weren't very good either.  Over fried and didn't have a bit of clam taste at all.  I've been here several times over the years.  Most recently would have been roughly 5 years ago.  Had the clam strips then and they were great.  Maybe it was a bad night.  Maybe I should have sent them back and given them another shot. I do want to point out the service was great!   I'll return to a restaurant if the food is great and the service isn't.  I'm not about to return after bad food for good service though. There were a few others at our table who had similar opinions of the food.  Just not very good.

I was not happy with this hotel and their service. Their credit card system has bugs and said one card was denied, so had to pay on credit card. Turns out the card that was "denied" was charged. So now we got charged 2x and it didn't come up on their system so had to file a claim with the bank because manager said there was nothing she could do and blamed it on the customer. Also was charged several days later a random fee which did not show up on the receipt or had any reason for this $11 fee. The manager was no help. 

The room was terrible. the AC did not work, only the fan was working. The beds were really squeaky and bouncy and not comfortable. 

Overall, terrible customer service and room. Will never recommend or stay here again.
I would pay money NOT to go here. It's like a bad joke and you are on a hidden camera show the whole time. Go here, I dare you.

In Baton Rouge I would say this is one of my favorite sushi places, in New Orleans not even close. The service we had was quite awful, the server was complaining a lot about her shit and how they had to pay for parking themselves ($25) to work. The food is just alright. The lighting is so dark you can barely see what you're eating. It's just not that great for what you are paying for.

Was there on a Friday evening. Took over an hour to be seated, when we were told 1/2 hr. wait.. Had music, but was so loud, could not hear each other when trying to talk. Food was ok, I had the tavern burger, cooked
the way I asked. Waitress was friendly and efficient. My spouse had the crab cake sandwich, said ok.
Probably will not go back. Don't like loud music, especially Folk music! 
Prices were a little on the high side for the type of restaurant it is supposed to be in that area. If you like loud music you will like it!

I use to love going here but service has severely fallen short recently. The food and drinks are still good. The problem comes with if you actually get what you ordered. Wrong drink and food given. When I come into the store to tell them of the issue I'm having they talk to me like I'm to dumb to understand what's going on. Even though they were the ones that handed me an order through the window with a girls name on it and not even close to my order. Don't be condescending toward your customers. The friendliness from this place is sorely lacking when it use to be one of the better places to go too. It's a shame.

Terrible OLD outdated hair salon. I'd give you a zero if I could. Have some pride in your work. The stylists need to go back to school. I am highly irritated. I tell my ex to stop taking her here because it's terrible but they were at the mall and I guess they decided to do something spontaneous. My daughter had her hair cut at the salon by Kim. She asked for a pixie hair cut and highlights. For the record, My daughter is beautiful, but this haircut is awful. Seriously? A pixie hair cut is supposed to be very short, search it,  but this? It's long in some spots, and feathered in the bangs- we have no idea how to style this mop it's really sad. My daughter was in tears today trying to fix your terrible botch job... and where are the highlights? I let her stay home so we can get it fixed. Her whole head is brown there are no highlights at ALL, what a rip off, if I had been there you would have never got away with charging them but alas her dad was there and is too nice to offend or shall I say be honest. Please Go back to school and learn how to cut and highlight hair before you mess up any more. You did a bad job with it. Thank the Lord you didn't cut it too short like a real pixie cut cause now I have to pay another stylist to fix your botched job!! I will not come back. Also the couple times I was there, your attitudes could be a little friendlier, very sour service at the front desk, I'll never return!!!

I try to taste boba drinks every where I go because I'm a boba enthusiast, so when I saw that there was a boba place by the movie theaters I was going to, I was a little hesitant but was down to try it. 

Going into the store the girls where on their phone laughing and didnt even greet us for 5 minutes straight until we went up and started ordering. 

I got a jasmine green milktea while my friends got a matcha milk tea. When my friends got their drinks, the matcha green milk tea was a different green. It was like a candy apple green and the taste was even worse!!!! It had no matcha flavor at all! Just tasted like straight up candy. it was so sweet but the boba was chewy so thats at least the only good thing. 

the Jasmine milk tea, was already pre made and had a slight taste of jasmine but also, straight up sugar. All in all i dont think i'll ever come back to this place and you shouldn't either!

I was really looking forward to Luke, but ended up leaving disappointed. I had heard such good things so my husband and I came to dinner on a Monday night. We were seated at a table backing up to the bar, which wasn't ideal but we dealt with it. We had two servers who were friendly enough, but for some reason just seemed very overwhelmed and unable to handle the tables they had. I had a bubbly to start and my husband had a beer. Both were fine but not special. I moved to a red wine for my meal, and it wasn't very good, especially not for the price point.

To start my husband got the stuffed oysters with shrimp and blue crab. They were very bready and underwhelming. The only crab to be found was small slivers. For our mains I had a shrimp, crab, and cavatelli étouffée. I expected more of a shrimp dish with some pasta underneath, but it was more like a pasta dish with minimal seafood. The shrimp was small and tasted like typical frozen shrimp. Like the appetizer, there wasn't really any real crab meat, just small sliver here and there. The pasta was fine but felt a tad overcooked. It honestly tasted like a pasta dish I could make quickly at home. And for around $26, that's ridiculous. My husband had the jumbo Louisiana shrimp with jalapeño grits. Luckily, his shrimp were large and flavorful. But the rest of the dish fell flat. The grits had very little flavor. 

Toward the end of our meal a very large group came into the bar, it almost seemed like a post-wedding thing. They were very rude and kept backing into not only our chairs and table, but the people around us as well. A lot of us were getting frustrated and the staff couldn't have cared less. They did nothing to remedy the situation. We left as quickly as we could. All in all, the food was mediocre and this place felt like a tourist trap, which I hadn't been expecting. I'd go elsewhere while in New Orleans.

Slow, forgettable food and high prices.  We stopped in for brunch, fairly busy: 1 hour and forty minutes, and no one even apologized for the wait.  My stuffed french toast was not cooked all the way through, and my fiance's breakfast sandwich was a mess.  I was also frustrated that my meal was served with imitation maple syrup in a plastic cup, considering our meal was $30 dollars before tip (you can add real maple syrup for $2, lol).  The hash browns were just terrible, they were slimy and tasted a month old.  The food was almost as good as a quality diner, but not quite.  The space is charming, but it seems like they have far more tables than the kitchen can keep up with.  We sat near the kitchen door and during our lengthy stay you could see the kitchen staff was barely keeping things together.  It's a shame to see a small kitchen working so hard with no hope of getting out of the weeds. The army of servers was very friendly and took our order promptly.  We had high hopes for Blue Plate, but have to say we won't return and wouldn't recommend it to others.

Not the best quality today in my arugula
Salad.  The avocado was bad (gray) and yet still served on top of the salad.  Usually much better.  Staff mis rung our order and changed it from salad to wrap.  While walking out, we were stopped and asked for $2 difference.  Not very professional nor customer friendly.

I came today for brunch. I've been for dinner before and thought it was just okay, so I figured brunch couldn't be half bad. I was in the area, the weather was nice, and there was no wait, so we decided to stop.

Pros: dog friendly patio and a very nice (albeit slow) waiter. He also brought a bowl of water for said dog.

Cons: everything else

Service was very slow. Parties that ordered after us received their food first.

We ordered an omelet and the French toast. First of all, the French toast is deep fried. Nothing in the description on the menu alluded to the fact that I would be served deep fried bread for breakfast. In what world does French toast = deep fried bread? It only tasted like oil, and when I poked the bread oil just oozed out. So essentially you're eating oil soaked bread for breakfast. Drowning it in syrup didn't help with the flavor either. 

The omelet also came out and was clearly covered in oil. Surprise surprise, it also just tasted like oil. It was served with 2 cold pieces of toast.

Unless you enjoy eating oil for breakfast, you're better off waiting in line at Fido or heading down the street to J Christopher's. You'll get much better food for a similar (if not cheaper) price.

We ate at Giordano,s Wednesday night and shared a small sausage, pepperoni and mushroom pizza. It was just ok the cheese and toppings were good. The crust was thick and chewy not flaky at all even though it was cooked thru. The service and atmosphere was fine nothing to special.

THIEVES!!! 
Took my 16 Jeep Grand Cherokee several times. But will never go back again. Stole my all weather Jeep floor mats from my vehicle during ref a wash. When I approached the staff o was forced to go through such bullshit just to get $94 back for the mats. The owner hung up on his employees several times and outright refused to even speak with me on the phone. When I finally did approx the manager with proof of purchase he still tried to tell my fiancé that her receipt was new and that we JD just purchased the mats. She had to correct him that it is currently 2018 and not 2016 as the receipt read. In a very annoyed manner he finally yelled at the desk clerk to give me my money and stormed away. He was VERY RUDE AND IGNORANT.  REVIEWS SHOW SIMILAR INCIDENTS FREQUENTLY!!

VERY disappointed in the service here  ! My daughter and I walked into the store and were ignored by the girls holding the little carry bags. As we walked around the store we passed many ladies holding the little carry bags and still were not offered one or even asked if we needed help. Alas, we actually didn't need a little carry bag after all because we walked out and headed straight for the MAC store.

NEVER. AGAIN. ever. again. charged me for my nails that i have never been charged that much in my life. said she has the color that she wanted but wasn't the color in the slightest. seriously never again.
Waited 1:30 minutes for an Uber Eats delivery and finally had to cancel. Don't quote 35 min if you can't deliver! Very disappointing.

I used to belong to a Hand and Stone in Morristown. I ended up abruptly moving to NYC and needing a new phone number and assumed my membership cancelled when I never received an email from the spa. I called the Marlton location while in town on business and asked if those credits would transfer, to which they told me yes. I booked a facial and a massage a week in advance. I left both my phone number and email and when I received a confirmation email about the appointment I assumed all must have been well. I arrived early to my appointment to ensure that my credits were still okay to be used. The receptionist said she had to call Morristown, but did not stop me from going into either my facial OR massage. 

The esthetician, Karen, was incredibly friendly and had a gentle touch. I wish she had done more extractions and really gone to work on my face. I appreciate the gentle-ness, but there's always a painful time during facials that you just have to grin and bear for better results, and I was hoping for more of that. Otherwise, I thought Karen was lovely. I was dismayed that between my facial and my massage there weren't any robes to transfer between rooms, so I got dressed and waited for about ten minutes while Karen tried to find my massage therapist, and then while she turned the room over until he came to get me. 

My massage therapist asked about my concerns and then left  me to change. By the time we started the massage it was already about 2:15. He was good about asking me how the pressure was, but I felt like I've gotten better massages from an airport chair massage. He used a lot of forearm, and little else technique wise. The massage was not thorough in the slightest. No scalp massage, no middle back, parts of my arms and legs were barely covered. I've had enough fifty minute massages to know that this was lacking. The massage ended at 2:50, not even close to fifty minutes (nor sixty if you're counting the ten minute changing time). After I got dressed my massage therapist was outside with a bottle of water, but he did not walk me out the door. He said goodbye in the hallway and I was left wandering in circles (ended up in an employee break room!) before finding my way out front. 

When I went to check out I held my tongue on the massage because I figured I had paid for it a while ago, I would suck it up and chalk it up to a bad but free (minus tip) experience. I was then told by the receptionist that she had yet to get in touch with Morristown regarding my credits. I had a bad feeling about this. When she got ahold of them they told her the only way to access my credits was to have me sign up again. There is no hand and stone in or around New York City (where I live). I was NOT prepared to pay for two services, I would have never made the appointments, and I certainly would have cancelled them had I known the circumstances. I asked why this was not checked ahead of time,or even during my first appointment before I went into a SECOND appointment, and I didn't think it was fair what was happening. A manager was brought over who said she would take care of things and would give me a call before running my credit card (I wanted to leave my tip on it). I assumed she would call me to work out some sort of price. Which is when I would have addressed the poor massage situation. 

I checked my credit card today and they ran my credit card after the appointment without my permission. I am beyond furious and refuse to ever return to this location, and plan on telling everybody I know in the area to avoid it as well. This was an unacceptable situation and I hope that anybody reading this knows to make 100% sure their services are covered before going in.

Ordered 2 pizzas for pick up.  I repeated the order 3 times; one cheese pizza and one pizza half pepperoni and half sausage. The pizza was cold, soggy, salty and I got one cheese and one pizza that was 1/2 cheese and half pepperoni sausage mixed.  I called and was told if I paid by credit card the price would be reduced. I paid cash. I had 5 kids waiting for dinner, it was raining and said I couldn't get back. The person I was talking to said "ok" and hung up.I can't say I will return.

The atmosphere was great.  Sat outside on a nice night.  Music playing and a good crowd. The service was also very good.  We had a party of 12 with lots of drinks ordered and the servers got it all right.  The problem was the food.  Prime rib was tough and overcooked.  The deviled eggs were dry and tasteless.  My husband did enjoy the wild boar ribs but the rest of our party was very underwhelmed by their meals.  Stick to drinks and appetizers and enjoy the atmosphere rather than coming for dinner.

This place was only okay. I have high expectations for a brunch place, especially one in Nashville. I ordered a salad, which was $13 dollars. All it had on it was about 4 blackberries, arugula, two cubes of cheese, and a teaspoon of granola. No meat or bacon or anything. Disappointed to say the least. We were also rudely kicked out by the male worker in the front by the hostess stand when we were trying to purchase a T shirt. No explanation, just told he was clearing out the restaurant. Won't be coming back here and you shouldn't either.

Went for brunch today. Nice atmosphere with jazz band playing which was really cool and the gentlemen playing were talented. Food was mediocre at best and for the price I'd say was a major letdown. We had the duck spring rolls which were okay but at 7 dollars per roll left much to be desired. The bbq shrimp were okay and again for nearly $25 again left much to be desired. The eggs and bacon were decent. Two bloody Mary's were watered down and bland. The one star review is reflected by the service. We had some of the most inattentive service in NOLA (in about 10 trips over the past 5 years) and that's saying a lot as things here move at a much slower pace in general. Forgot coffee order, forgot Bloody drink order, no coffee refill, no follow up whatsoever from our waitress on anything and had to ask for literally every single item needed including utensils. The closest thing to a modicum of service I had was from the water guys. Walked out with $100 check for brunch and a feeling that they could care less about us as a customer. Also I should have known going in when I saw the host berate a more junior team member to nearly tears for supposedly mishandling customer checkin. Unfortunately they can likely get away with it because the place was packed.......sorry Mr. B but we won't be returning or recommending you.

I just don't want to write a bad review, but after talking with Stephanie this afternoon and getting no resolution I feel it's worth it. No need to name call, just the facts of what happened. I ordered 3 round cakes for a baby shower. All vanilla cakes with vanilla buttercream icing. One was a naked cake. It was supposed to be simple with slight scalloped edges on top. It was a disaster and looked so unprofessional everyone who has seen it couldn't believe that I paid money for it. We were going to stick the naked cake on top of another round, however all the round cakes came with a ring of buttercream roses on top. I was never told that there would be roses. Apparently this is their standard, but no one mentioned it to me, so how would I know it would be on there? Also when I stacked the cakes, the naked cake icing was a different color than the other two cakes. All the same icing, one super white and the other two were a yellow color. They tasted different and I know what the frosting should taste like since I had a sample of it before ordering. Obviously they messed up the icing on two of the cakes. Stephanie explained that they didn't know I would be stacking it so it didn't seem like it would matter. All the cakes were also supposed to be on cardboard that was cut to the size of the bottom of the cakes. Stephanie and I spoke about this on the phone and I emailed her a confirmation that this would be done. Naturally, they weren't cut so they stood out terribly on our cake base. Plus we had to take the naked cake off of its cardboard base so we could stack it, which was just annoying and unnecessary. Also the cakes were dry. It was just so disappointing all around. I really wanted to like this bakery, but for how many things they got wrong and then to not give me a refund considering the issues were their fault, I'm astounded.
Extremely rude customer service and uncalled for.  What happened to the friendly people here?!?

My buddy who eats meat got a burrito which was large, fine-- but as he commented, largely flavorless.
And don't go here if you want something non-meat. They throw on some barely cooked random veggies that tastes like they're microwaved and put it on some rice with no flavor.
The music was quite loud, even when there were so few people in there. IMO there are far better taqueria style spots in Philly, whether in S Philly, Italian Market or by Bella Vista.

Amazing dosas. Terrible everything else. I ordered a chicken curry and the chicken pieces in it were breaded (Were they originally chicken nuggets? Who knows!). Biriyani was bland and featured cheap cinnamon sticks instead of cinnamon bark and obviously frozen mixed veggies. I've heard they've cleaned the place up a little since my visit but the interior was horrendous and dirty.

We used to love this place, but not so much after tonight. Everything was cold, the ribs were dry, the Portabella mushroom was tiny, and they didn't even bother to include a bun in our take out order. I'm not sure what has happened to this place, but we will not be going back.

Had a very negative experience.  It was 10am on a Thursday and they were training someone so it took a bit for someone to take my order.  I ordered 2 donuts and an iced vanilla chai latte.   Apparently it comes frozen not on ice.  This was not explained to me.  I would not have ordered it if I had known.  The person was rude and didn't understand my complaint just said there is crushed ice in it.  So frustrating. Was not good.   Wouldn't order any coffee drinks here.   I got to my car to take a drink and it leaked out all over my off white suit shirt.  I will not be going to this store ever again.  I have told all my friends this is not good.   It will be awhile before Dunkin Donuts gets my business.

This is my favorite home cooked food in town, I love Boston market and always have been a loyal customer. Sadly, I got an individual meal and found a hair in my mashed potatoes. I will have to find a new location but I'm pretty upset by this. Although Erica is a great worker and really helped accommodate to my lengthy order!

OK - so let me preface this with the understanding that my experience was likely dissimilar to most people (or I really hope so!) 

I had eaten here a few times, and the food is pretty good. The honey bar is amazing. 

That being said, last time I went here, *I don't remember what I ordered, honestly* I took it home for my husband and I, and when I opened my container, a beetle crawled out.... I was so horrified and disgusted, I didn't know what to do. When I dumped out the container, there was another one in the bottom. I had not touched the containers or opened the bag prior to getting home and there is no way they came from anywhere but inside the restaurant.

I don't know what happened or how they got there, but despite liking the restaurant as an option, I cannot bring myself to go back. 

Hoping this was an isolated experience, but it was horrifying.

This place has gone DOWN HILL! We went here in December and it was fairly decent. We went there today and it was horrible! We were one of 6 patrons in the entire restaurant and still had AWFUL service. We went with my son, and the asked if we were doing all you can eat. We told them yes for my husband and I. Then they asked for our drinks and we replied water. They brought me and my husband a water and nothing for my son. Even after asking, still no drink for him. The sushi chef never made eye contact with us. We just had to talk at her, which made us feel rude. The only good thing we had was seared tuna. The rolls were HUGE! Way too big. So much rice and dripping in Siracha. Everything had tons of jalapeños and siracha. They never offered to take an order for my son. 
We used the restroom on our way out and it was FILTHY! Something you would expect to see at a gas station or port a potty, not a sushi restaurant. Needless to say, we won't be back.

The service from
Here is great as all the people that I have met at this resort seem to be always helpful, but the food is subpar for price and would be simple to elevate but instead I had an upset stomach for next 12 hours. Such great potential being wasted is said. There are many places within minutes that are far better. I hope for the people that work here they improve their food standards.

I wanted wood-fired eggs from sister venue Lucky Penny and was hoping Helena Bakery would have them, but they don't. So I ordered an espresso drink to go. I waited 15 minutes for that drink! Why only one barista on a busy Saturday morning? The owners should re-open Lucky Penny for breakfast because Helena Bakery is busier than they can handle (and I want my wood-fired eggs!) They have improved their selection of baked goods since last year.
Thanks, I wanted to order but they won't deliver 4 Miles from their store. I don't understand that one,  but perhaps they don't need the business. Looked great too! Very disappointed for sure.
Waited for over 15 min for an açaí bowl.. the orders kept getting mixed up (4 ppl got the wrong thing).
Morning crew is pretty good. They are quick and make all the drinks the correct way. Afternoon crew is extremely slow and always mess things up. I will not be going back since I work nights

Disappointed We visited on April 1 2018 Ordered stuffed crab with red beans and collards The crab came in two little tin shells Looked more like appetizers I could not find or taste crab. They can do better for a 19.95 entree. The tiny portion of beans and the overcooked soupy greens completed the meal. The cornbread was not good. My spouse was kind enough to share her shrimp poboy which was not bad. Againhave to say I was truly disappointed I wont return to this place on my next visit

The two waiters/cooks were sitting down in the dining area when we arrived. Noticed there wasn't any else and that should have been a red flag. The waiter was loud and awkward. Their phone rang multiple times and they ignored it. They were out of tea, but brewed some. Noticed a lot of tables had not been wiped down. Others walked in and waited,  but left after not being acknowledged. Then noticed the section that was closed off awaiting vacuuming. Staff were loud about their job dissatisfaction. We should have left, but I was hungery. Brought out one pizza, no silverware or napkins. Had to ask for them specifinally. Food was okay. They finally answered the phone and talked with a customer who never received their order. Pepsi was off,  so they gave out litre bottles.  This was the strangest, most bizarre place I've ever visited. They lied to customers calling in about how busy they were and openly complained about customers. It was intriguing to watch, but never going to eat here ever again.

Service by Heather and hostess at time . 
I will write about the food which was great in another review later on  to balance the offset.

They put me in a pedicure chair and I sat there for 45 minutes in cold water while they kept starting in other customers. I finally got up and said forget it and they were like "oh you are next" but didn't seem to care I had already been sitting there for almost an hour.

The food is delicious but unfortunately the service was horrible.  Our first time here was a great experience however our most recent visit today ensures that we will never return. When we sat down the menus were tossed to us followed by " what do you want to drink" no hi hello how are you today my name is... We were not offered water. We were brought the bill without asking for it first as if we weren't welcome. The other patrons asked for their bills before they were given to them. We will never spend our money here again.

Me and a friend stop by for happy hour today and I was extremely disappointed and will not be back.  We arrived around 3:45pm on a Wednesday; they were in no way busy and we figured this would go smoothly. I order a glass of Merlot from a new male waiter.  A female waitress comes by and says she's training him and they are out of merlot.  I say that's okay and request a Cab instead; she returns and says they are out of Cab, I request the Pinot Noir, she returns again and says they are out of the Pinot Noir, I end up with the Malbec (4th choice). My friend got the 2 for 1 beer; in 90 degree heat (seated inside, but it's warm) she brings both beers at the same time.  After the food was delivered and finished, no one had checked on us.  I had to go to the bar to request a second glass of wine.  At this point there was a max of 6 people there with 3 at the bar.  The food wasn't good enough to make up for the lack of service.  I brought the lack of service to the "bartenders" attention and no one seemed bothered.  I won't be back; there's many places in Nashville with better food, better wine selection, and MUCH better service.

So I read all the reviews and was having second thoughts about signing up for our second band event but decided to give them a try. We arrived along with 48 of our band alumni. There was absolutely NO parking. Very frustrating. Parked in someone's lot, didn't get towed. Phew!  Wa told to go to the back. Partly the fault of organizer since the room we were in held no more than 40.  I was squished and had no room to move. I was thinking Yelp had it wrong then the unthinkable happened. As I came to the buffet line, there was no food. I mean every hot plate was empty. This has never happened to me at a buffet, ever. It took a good 20 min for new food to arrive, meanwhile everyone was done eating. The food was OK and for $50 per person was overpriced. Hence the reason for 2 stars. The desserts were cookies and little brownie like things. Tasty but I was expecting more. Appetizers were tasty. Chairs were covered nicely and waitresses were nice. If not for the great acquaintances, I would had spent the $100 elsewhere. There are several people who may disagree but read all reviews.

Great atmosphere, decent drinks.  However the management needs to train bartenders to look customers in the eye to see they want service.  The music is loud so they can't hear you and they interact well with each other which is great but when you have to get their attention by turning a finished drink upside down that sucks.  Then they get attitude and tell you that was disrespectful and this is your last drink.  Given it was my only drink of the night and first time there, it became my last.  Management can feel free to contact me I can explain more.  I had three restaurants I can help you save this new place is you care.

Ugh, what happened? This was always my favorite Food Truck and we'd drive an hour just for their amazing Cheese Curds! But I just had my first order of 2018 and they have definitely changed since last fall. The batter now has an overly pronounced cornmeal flavor and consistency and it really changes the crunch of the curd crust and overall taste. The cheese itself seemed a bit off too. There was always a mix of white and yellow cheddar curds in each order. This visit all the curds were yellow cheddar and had a "Velveeta" feel and taste to them, instead of the normal rich and stringy cheddar cheese. As a fan of the original version, I hope this was just a temporary change of the recipe or perhaps an off-day.

I used to live around the corner from the foodery, and after yesterday I will never go there again. 
If you want an expensive ass 6 pack (very close to what you'd spend if you got the same beer at a bar), old tastycakes, or to spend double what you should because the prices are so high, feel free to go waste your money here. I walked into the foodery and asked the guy behind the counter to use his phone to call a cab (my phone had died and at 11 am on a Sunday, cabs were not really around) because I had three massive bags of groceries and I couldn't carry them all the way home. Well needless to say the guy said well I'm using the phone, I offered to wait until he was done, but he just said there's cabs outside all the time and turned away. I had told him that I had already waited outside for 15 minutes and saw none available, And he just said no can't help you. Horrible customer service, and considering it's a neighborhood spot, I'm shocked at the total lack of class from this store owner, especially considering I've been shopping there for years.

I have always loved Landry's. The food is always good. Even this time it was very good however the portions are a joke. I ordered the seafood platter and substituted the fish for shrimp. I got 6 tiny shrimp 2 oysters 2 hush puppy's and 1 stuffed shrimp. Very tiny "platter " for $30. Usually very full of food. Now the biggest problem was the service! 25 min to be greeted by waitress and 10 more min to actually get the drinks. Refills were given if you were lucky enough to flag somebody down. Very disappointed! She even had a trainer. Three times drinks empty over 10 min. I'm sure they won't be there long if service does not improve!

Decent pizza.... incompetent and childish staff. Employees are constantly goofing off and do not pay attention. We ordered to-go and waited TWENTY minutes before we asked the staff and our pizza had been sitting there the entire time. Meanwhile the staff was goofing around, throwing around dough, and acting childish. Manager was goofing off as well...

Horrible!  Had to stay here while on town for a conference. People fighting in parking at 5am, called front desk and after 10 rings the person answers as if he just woke up. Tried to check out the next day and couldn't because the front desk person left at 650am and i had to wait until the 7am person came in. I would avoid this place like the plague. Horrible customer service!  And forgot that elevator was also broken!

Visited again 8/6/2018 around 11:20.  Received food around 12:25.  Brandon apologized for "The rush had everything behind".  We watched others come in, eat and leave.  We were forgotten.  2nd bad experience out of 2 attempts.

Awful awful smoke in food court and everywhere we went. Wasn't very impressed with atmosphere even in non smoker section either. Food in food court was amazing though at Cuban place, but wouldn't recommend any of others.

It was a very disappointing visit.  Our first and last time here.  We ordered the grouper bites for an appetizer and it came with an already opened packet of buffalo sauce that we had them take back.  The monster fish sandwich was a total disappointment; the leaf of lettuce was wilted, the top of the bun was stale, the bottom of the bun was soggy, and the fish was flavorless.  The only good thing was the fries.

DO NOT EAT HERE!!! Management is horrible, the restaurant is understaffed. I feel bad for the friendly employees here. I ordered one beer and boneless wings. I got here at 10pm and didn't get out until almost 1am. I spoke to the manager who apologized and promised to comp my meal, but it still took ANOTHER 45+ minutes just for the bill and nothing was discounted. I didn't need a discount, no big deal, I told him I just wanted to leave, but he clearly couldn't uphold his promises and I was held hostage unless I wanted to walk out without paying. I will never come here again.
They have really great customer service i just prefer the food on south street better

Food isn't that good as it is, but there's so many things on the menu I just deal with it sometimes. I ordered from here last night pretty late, by the time I got my food they had either closed or there lazy employees didn't want to answer the phone... they did not include my ice cream or travs. Like I stated I tried calling, but no answer. With ice cream and missing travs not being on the top of my list I went to work this am and remembered to call when I got home. The lady hung up as soon as I told her i had an issue with an order, called back and she said she can't do anything about it because it's another day... we'll if you would have answered I wouldnt have this problem today, correct? She hung up again. I dont like to hate on people's businesses but after the rudeness idc, the building is "SUPER DIRTY", there food isn't good, and there employees are trash. I'll make sure to copy and post this everywhere I can. Whoever was working the phone today sounds like she needs to be a Walmart greeter.

Not happy with service or meal. I ordered Bayou Red fish with Crawfish etouffe topping. There was no etouffe sauce, just a cream sauce. I asked for green salad in place of potato salad. When bill came, i realized...I was charged for the green salad. The taste wasn't what I expected in New Orleans.

So the manager was the one who messed up my hair.. a simple comb over with a hard part fade.. fairly common.. before we started I told her not t9 disconnect my ledge cause that's where my hair rests and what does this woman do?? Took the whole damn thing down.. now I'm buzzed on both sides and the long top.. looking like some kinda country ass bumkin with a rebel flag waiving on my truck as u drink bud light driving down the road.... really really not happy with this one.. I don't think I'll ever let that woman touch my head again and honestly I doubt I'll ever go back.. 
What pisses me off the most is the first time I went Becky cut me up and it was proper and clean.... this woman... messed me up on Valentine's day.. and I have a date tonight... Thanks, thanks alot.... #neveragain #trustno1 #wontbeback

I love this establishment and I come here very often.  However, on several occasions, the host (who looks like a younger Mitch McConnell - but he's still old - and wears glasses and is blonde) has not only been rude when getting seated, but he has also touched the waitresses inappropriately.  He makes the entire environment very uncomfortable.  He is the only thing I dislike about this wonderful place and it makes me so sad to to give this place 1 star.

Had better buffet in Reno for breakfast. They should really learn how to properly make an omelet. Take lessons from charlie's buffet at Atlantis Hotel! Cook ingredients before putting the scrambled egg. County Fried steak was hard.

The armature works location thinks it's okay to not wear anything on their head... there was hair baked into my pizza. When we informed the employees all they had to say was "oh" and had the nerve to ask if we wanted to take it home. Spare yourself the extra hair in your food and try somewhere else.

Very disappointed when we visited this restaurant on Saturday. First off you pay for parking I think $5.50 an hour (we bought two hours which was unnecessary, machine had small sign say Buy one Cocktail get one Free at Sculleys). Hostess asked where we want to sit, we said on the water, she said first come first serve, and we were pointed to the 3rd tiki and take a right to a dock with a platform of seats.
